 vulnerability appears to have been fixed in after commit add531a1e55b0a739b0f42582f1c9747e5649ace.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2018-1000802\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"3.4.3-1ubuntu1~14.04.7\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"python3.4\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"3.4.3-1ubuntu1~14.04.3\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2020-26116\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"http.client in Python 3.x before 3.5.10, 3.6.x before 3.6.12, 3.7.x before 3.7.9, and 3.8.x before 3.8.5 allows CRLF injection if the attacker controls the HTTP request method, as demonstrated by inserting CR and LF control characters in the first argument of HTTPConnection.request.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2020-26116\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"3.4.3-1ubuntu1~14.04.7+esm8\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"mysql-5.5\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"5.5.47-0ubuntu0.14.04.1\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2017-3600\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Vulnerability in the MySQL Server component of Oracle MySQL (subcomponent: Client mysqldump). Supported versions that are affected are 5.5.54 and earlier, 5.6.35 and earlier and 5.7.17 and earlier. Difficult to exploit vulnerability allows high privileged attacker with network access via multiple protocols to compromise MySQL Server. Successful attacks of this vulnerability can result in takeover of MySQL Server. Note: CVE-2017-3600 is equivalent to CVE-2016-5483. CVSS 3.0 Base Score 6.6 (Confidentiality, Integrity and Availability impacts). CVSS Vector: (CVSS:3.0/AV:N/AC:H/PR:H/UI:N/S:U/C:H/I:H/A:H).\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2017-3600\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"5.5.55-0ubuntu0.14.04.1\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"python3.4\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"3.4.3-1ubuntu1~14.04.3\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-0772\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"The smtplib library in CPython (aka Python) before 2.7.12, 3.x before 3.4.5, and 3.5.x before 3.5.2 does not return an error when StartTLS fails, which might allow man-in-the-middle attackers to bypass the TLS protections by leveraging a network position between the client and the registry to block the StartTLS command, aka a \\\"StartTLS stripping attack.\\\"\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-0772\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"3.4.3-1ubuntu1~14.04.5\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"python3.4\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"3.4.3-1ubuntu1~14.04.3\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2019-20907\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"In Lib/tarfile.py in Python through 3.8.3, an attacker is able to craft a TAR archive leading to an infinite loop when opened by tarfile.open, because _proc_pax lacks header validation.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2019-20907\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"3.4.3-1ubuntu1~14.04.7+esm7\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"python3.4\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"3.4.3-1ubuntu1~14.04.3\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2017-1000158\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"CPython (aka Python) up to 2.7.13 is vulnerable to an integer overflow in the PyString_DecodeEscape function in stringobject.c, resulting in heap-based buffer overflow (and possible arbitrary code execution)\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2017-1000158\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"3.4.3-1ubuntu1~14.04.6\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"python3.4\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"3.4.3-1ubuntu1~14.04.3\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2018-14647\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Python's elementtree C accelerator failed to initialise Expat's hash salt during initialization. This could make it easy to conduct denial of service attacks against Expat by constructing an XML document that would cause pathological hash collisions in Expat's internal data structures, consuming large amounts CPU and RAM. The vulnerability exists in Python versions 3.7.0, 3.6.0 through 3.6.6, 3.5.0 through 3.5.6, 3.4.0 through 3.4.9, 2.7.0 through 2.7.15.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2018-14647\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"3.4.3-1ubuntu1~14.04.7\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"mysql-5.5\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"5.5.47-0ubuntu0.14.04.1\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2018-2771\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Vulnerability in the MySQL Server component of Oracle MySQL (subcomponent: Server: Locking). Supported versions that are affected are 5.5.59 and prior, 5.6.39 and prior and 5.7.21 and prior. Difficult to exploit vulnerability allows high privileged attacker with network access via multiple protocols to compromise MySQL Server. Successful attacks of this vulnerability can result in unauthorized ability to cause a hang or frequently repeatable crash (complete DOS) of MySQL Server. CVSS 3.0 Base Score 4.4 (Availability impacts). CVSS Vector: (CVSS:3.0/AV:N/AC:H/PR:H/UI:N/S:U/C:N/I:N/A:H).\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2018-2771\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"5.5.60-0ubuntu0.14.04.1\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"mysql-5.5\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"5.5.47-0ubuntu0.14.04.1\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2017-3651\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Vulnerability in the MySQL Server component of Oracle MySQL (subcomponent: Client mysqldump). Supported versions that are affected are 5.5.56 and earlier, 5.6.36 and earlier and 5.7.18 and earlier. Easily exploitable vulnerability allows low privileged attacker with network access via multiple protocols to compromise MySQL Server. Successful attacks of this vulnerability can result in unauthorized update, insert or delete access to some of MySQL Server accessible data. CVSS 3.0 Base Score 4.3 (Integrity impacts). CVSS Vector: (CVSS:3.0/AV:N/AC:L/PR:L/UI:N/S:U/C:N/I:L/A:N).\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2017-3651\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"5.5.57-0ubuntu0.14.04.1\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"python3.4\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"3.4.3-1ubuntu1~14.04.3\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2019-10160\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"A security regression of CVE-2019-9636 was discovered in python since commit d537ab0ff9767ef024f26246899728f0116b1ec3 affecting versions 2.7, 3.5, 3.6, 3.7 and from v3.8.0a4 through v3.8.0b1, which still allows an attacker to exploit CVE-2019-9636 by abusing the user and password parts of a URL. When an application parses user-supplied URLs to store cookies, authentication credentials, or other kind of information, it is possible for an attacker to provide specially crafted URLs to make the application locate host-related information (e.g. cookies, authentication data) and send them to a different host than where it should, unlike if the URLs had been correctly parsed. The result of an attack may vary based on the application.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2019-10160\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"3.4.3-1ubuntu1~14.04.7+esm2\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"mysql-5.5\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"5.5.47-0ubuntu0.14.04.1\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-2047\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"The ssl_verify_server_cert function in sql-common/client.c in MariaDB before 5.5.47, 10.0.x before 10.0.23, and 10.1.x before 10.1.10; Oracle MySQL 5.5.48 and earlier, 5.6.29 and earlier, and 5.7.11 and earlier; and Percona Server do not properly verify that the server hostname matches a domain name in the subject's Common Name (CN) or subjectAltName field of the X.509 certificate, which allows man-in-the-middle attackers to spoof SSL servers via a \\\"/CN=\\\" string in a field in a certificate, as demonstrated by \\\"/OU=/CN=bar.com/CN=foo.com.\\\"\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-2047\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"5.5.49-0ubuntu0.14.04.1\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"sensible-utils\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"0.0.9\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2017-17512\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"sensible-browser in sensible-utils before 0.0.11 does not validate strings before launching the program specified by the BROWSER environment variable, which allows remote attackers to conduct argument-injection attacks via a crafted URL, as demonstrated by a --proxy-pac-file argument.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2017-17512\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"0.0.9ubuntu0.14.04.1\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"mysql-5.5\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"5.5.47-0ubuntu0.14.04.1\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-0643\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Unspecified vulnerability in Oracle MySQL 5.5.48 and earlier, 5.6.29 and earlier, and 5.7.11 and earlier and MariaDB before 5.5.49, 10.0.x before 10.0.25, and 10.1.x before 10.1.14 allows local users to affect confidentiality via vectors related to DML.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-0643\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"5.5.49-0ubuntu0.14.04.1\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"python2.7\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.7.6-8ubuntu0.2\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2019-9740\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"An issue was discovered in urllib2 in Python 2.x through 2.7.16 and urllib in Python 3.x through 3.7.3. CRLF injection is possible if the attacker controls a url parameter, as demonstrated by the first argument to urllib.request.urlopen with \\\\r\\\\n (specifically in the query string after a ? character) followed by an HTTP header or a Redis command. This is fixed in: v2.7.17, v2.7.17rc1, v2.7.18, v2.7.18rc1; v3.5.10, v3.5.10rc1, v3.5.8, v3.5.8rc1, v3.5.8rc2, v3.5.9; v3.6.10, v3.6.10rc1, v3.6.11, v3.6.11rc1, v3.6.12, v3.6.9, v3.6.9rc1; v3.7.4, v3.7.4rc1, v3.7.4rc2, v3.7.5, v3.7.5rc1, v3.7.6, v3.7.6rc1, v3.7.7, v3.7.7rc1, v3.7.8, v3.7.8rc1, v3.7.9.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2019-9740\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2.7.6-8ubuntu0.6+esm2\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"python2.7\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.7.6-8ubuntu0.2\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2019-18348\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"An issue was discovered in urllib2 in Python 2.x through 2.7.17 and urllib in Python 3.x through 3.8.0. CRLF injection is possible if the attacker controls a url parameter, as demonstrated by the first argument to urllib.request.urlopen with \\\\r\\\\n (specifically in the host component of a URL) followed by an HTTP header. This is similar to the CVE-2019-9740 query string issue and the CVE-2019-9947 path string issue. (This is not exploitable when glibc has CVE-2016-10739 fixed.). This is fixed in: v2.7.18, v2.7.18rc1; v3.5.10, v3.5.10rc1; v3.6.11, v3.6.11rc1, v3.6.12; v3.7.8, v3.7.8rc1, v3.7.9; v3.8.3, v3.8.3rc1, v3.8.4, v3.8.4rc1, v3.8.5, v3.8.6, v3.8.6rc1.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2019-18348\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2.7.6-8ubuntu0.6+esm5\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"python2.7\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.7.6-8ubuntu0.2\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2021-3177\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Python 3.x through 3.9.1 has a buffer overflow in PyCArg_repr in _ctypes/callproc.c, which may lead to remote code execution in certain Python applications that accept floating-point numbers as untrusted input, as demonstrated by a 1e300 argument to c_double.from_param. This occurs because sprintf is used unsafely.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2021-3177\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"mysql-5.5\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"5.5.47-0ubuntu0.14.04.1\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-8283\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Unspecified vulnerability in Oracle MySQL 5.5.51 and earlier, 5.6.32 and earlier, and 5.7.14 and earlier allows remote authenticated users to affect availability via vectors related to Server: Types.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-8283\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"5.5.52-0ubuntu0.14.04.1\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"python2.7\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.7.6-8ubuntu0.2\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2019-16056\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"An issue was discovered in Python through 2.7.16, 3.x through 3.5.7, 3.6.x through 3.6.9, and 3.7.x through 3.7.4. The email module wrongly parses email addresses that contain multiple @ characters. An application that uses the email module and implements some kind of checks on the From/To headers of a message could be tricked into accepting an email address that should be denied. An attack may be the same as in CVE-2019-11340; however, this CVE applies to Python more generally.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2019-16056\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2.7.6-8ubuntu0.6+esm3\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"mysql-5.5\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"5.5.47-0ubuntu0.14.04.1\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-7440\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"The C software implementation of AES Encryption and Decryption in wolfSSL (formerly CyaSSL) before 3.9.10 makes it easier for local users to discover AES keys by leveraging cache-bank timing differences.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-7440\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"5.5.53-0ubuntu0.14.04.1\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"python2.7\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.7.6-8ubuntu0.2\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-5699\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"CRLF injection vulnerability in the HTTPConnection.putheader function in urllib2 and urllib in CPython (aka Python) before 2.7.10 and 3.x before 3.4.4 allows remote attackers to inject arbitrary HTTP headers via CRLF sequences in a URL.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-5699\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2.7.6-8ubuntu0.3\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"python2.7\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.7.6-8ubuntu0.2\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-1000110\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"The CGIHandler class in Python before 2.7.12 does not protect against the HTTP_PROXY variable name clash in a CGI script, which could allow a remote attacker to redirect HTTP requests.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-1000110\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2.7.6-8ubuntu0.3\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"python2.7\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.7.6-8ubuntu0.2\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2018-20852\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"http.cookiejar.DefaultPolicy.domain_return_ok in Lib/http/cookiejar.py in Python before 3.7.3 does not correctly validate the domain: it can be tricked into sending existing cookies to the wrong server. An attacker may abuse this flaw by using a server with a hostname that has another valid hostname as a suffix (e.g., pythonicexample.com to steal cookies for example.com). When a program uses http.cookiejar.DefaultPolicy and tries to do an HTTP connection to an attacker-controlled server, existing cookies can be leaked to the attacker. This affects 2.x through 2.7.16, 3.x before 3.4.10, 3.5.x before 3.5.7, 3.6.x before 3.6.9, and 3.7.x before 3.7.3.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2018-20852\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2.7.6-8ubuntu0.6+esm2\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"mysql-5.5\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"5.5.47-0ubuntu0.14.04.1\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2017-3653\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Vulnerability in the MySQL Server component of Oracle MySQL (subcomponent: Server: DDL). Supported versions that are affected are 5.5.56 and earlier, 5.6.36 and earlier and 5.7.18 and earlier. Difficult to exploit vulnerability allows low privileged attacker with network access via multiple protocols to compromise MySQL Server. Successful attacks of this vulnerability can result in unauthorized update, insert or delete access to some of MySQL Server accessible data. CVSS 3.0 Base Score 3.1 (Integrity impacts). CVSS Vector: (CVSS:3.0/AV:N/AC:H/PR:L/UI:N/S:U/C:N/I:L/A:N).\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2017-3653\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"5.5.57-0ubuntu0.14.04.1\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"python2.7\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.7.6-8ubuntu0.2\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2019-9636\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Python 2.7.x through 2.7.16 and 3.x through 3.7.2 is affected by: Improper Handling of Unicode Encoding (with an incorrect netloc) during NFKC normalization. The impact is: Information disclosure (credentials, cookies, etc. that are cached against a given hostname). The components are: urllib.parse.urlsplit, urllib.parse.urlparse. The attack vector is: A specially crafted URL could be incorrectly parsed to locate cookies or authentication data and send that information to a different host than when parsed correctly. This is fixed in: v2.7.17, v2.7.17rc1, v2.7.18, v2.7.18rc1; v3.5.10, v3.5.10rc1, v3.5.7, v3.5.8, v3.5.8rc1, v3.5.8rc2, v3.5.9; v3.6.10, v3.6.10rc1, v3.6.11, v3.6.11rc1, v3.6.12, v3.6.9, v3.6.9rc1; v3.7.3, v3.7.3rc1, v3.7.4, v3.7.4rc1, v3.7.4rc2, v3.7.5, v3.7.5rc1, v3.7.6, v3.7.6rc1, v3.7.7, v3.7.7rc1, v3.7.8, v3.7.8rc1, v3.7.9.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2019-9636\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2.7.6-8ubuntu0.6+esm2\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"mysql-5.5\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"5.5.47-0ubuntu0.14.04.1\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2017-10384\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Vulnerability in the MySQL Server component of Oracle MySQL (subcomponent: Server: DDL). Supported versions that are affected are 5.5.57 and earlier 5.6.37 and earlier 5.7.19 and earlier. Easily exploitable vulnerability allows low privileged attacker with network access via multiple protocols to compromise MySQL Server. Successful attacks of this vulnerability can result in unauthorized ability to cause a hang or frequently repeatable crash (complete DOS) of MySQL Server. CVSS 3.0 Base Score 6.5 (Availability impacts). CVSS Vector: (CVSS:3.0/AV:N/AC:L/PR:L/UI:N/S:U/C:N/I:N/A:H).\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2017-10384\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"5.5.58-0ubuntu0.14.04.1\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"mysql-5.5\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"5.5.47-0ubuntu0.14.04.1\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-0647\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Unspecified vulnerability in Oracle MySQL 5.5.48 and earlier, 5.6.29 and earlier, and 5.7.11 and earlier and MariaDB before 5.5.49, 10.0.x before 10.0.25, and 10.1.x before 10.1.14 allows local users to affect availability via vectors related to FTS.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-0647\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"5.5.49-0ubuntu0.14.04.1\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"python2.7\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.7.6-8ubuntu0.2\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2019-9948\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"urllib in Python 2.x through 2.7.16 supports the local_file: scheme, which makes it easier for remote attackers to bypass protection mechanisms that blacklist file: URIs, as demonstrated by triggering a urllib.urlopen('local_file:///etc/passwd') call.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2019-9948\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2.7.6-8ubuntu0.6+esm2\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"mysql-5.5\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"5.5.47-0ubuntu0.14.04.1\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-6663\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Race condition in Oracle MySQL before 5.5.52, 5.6.x before 5.6.33, 5.7.x before 5.7.15, and 8.x before 8.0.1; MariaDB before 5.5.52, 10.0.x before 10.0.28, and 10.1.x before 10.1.18; Percona Server before 5.5.51-38.2, 5.6.x before 5.6.32-78-1, and 5.7.x before 5.7.14-8; and Percona XtraDB Cluster before 5.5.41-37.0, 5.6.x before 5.6.32-25.17, and 5.7.x before 5.7.14-26.17 allows local users with certain permissions to gain privileges by leveraging use of my_copystat by REPAIR TABLE to repair a MyISAM table.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-6663\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"5.5.52-0ubuntu0.14.04.1\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"python2.7\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.7.6-8ubuntu0.2\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2019-9947\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"An issue was discovered in urllib2 in Python 2.x through 2.7.16 and urllib in Python 3.x through 3.7.3. CRLF injection is possible if the attacker controls a url parameter, as demonstrated by the first argument to urllib.request.urlopen with \\\\r\\\\n (specifically in the path component of a URL that lacks a ? character) followed by an HTTP header or a Redis command. This is similar to the CVE-2019-9740 query string issue. This is fixed in: v2.7.17, v2.7.17rc1, v2.7.18, v2.7.18rc1; v3.5.10, v3.5.10rc1, v3.5.8, v3.5.8rc1, v3.5.8rc2, v3.5.9; v3.6.10, v3.6.10rc1, v3.6.11, v3.6.11rc1, v3.6.12, v3.6.9, v3.6.9rc1; v3.7.4, v3.7.4rc1, v3.7.4rc2, v3.7.5, v3.7.5rc1, v3.7.6, v3.7.6rc1, v3.7.7, v3.7.7rc1, v3.7.8, v3.7.8rc1, v3.7.9.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2019-9947\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2.7.6-8ubuntu0.6+esm2\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"python2.7\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.7.6-8ubuntu0.2\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-5636\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Integer overflow in the get_data function in zipimport.c in CPython (aka Python) before 2.7.12, 3.x before 3.4.5, and 3.5.x before 3.5.2 allows remote attackers to have unspecified impact via a negative data size value, which triggers a heap-based buffer overflow.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-5636\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2.7.6-8ubuntu0.3\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"python2.7\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.7.6-8ubuntu0.2\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2018-1000802\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Python Software Foundation Python (CPython) version 2.7 contains a CWE-77: Improper Neutralization of Special Elements used in a Command ('Command Injection') vulnerability in shutil module (make_archive function) that can result in Denial of service, Information gain via injection of arbitrary files on the system or entire drive. This attack appear to be exploitable via Passage of unfiltered user input to the function. This vulnerability appears to have been fixed in after commit add531a1e55b0a739b0f42582f1c9747e5649ace.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2018-1000802\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2.7.6-8ubuntu0.5\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"python2.7\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.7.6-8ubuntu0.2\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2020-26116\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"http.client in Python 3.x before 3.5.10, 3.6.x before 3.6.12, 3.7.x before 3.7.9, and 3.8.x before 3.8.5 allows CRLF injection if the attacker controls the HTTP request method, as demonstrated by inserting CR and LF control characters in the first argument of HTTPConnection.request.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2020-26116\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2.7.6-8ubuntu0.6+esm7\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"mysql-5.5\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"5.5.47-0ubuntu0.14.04.1\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2018-2668\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Vulnerability in the MySQL Server component of Oracle MySQL (subcomponent: Server: Optimizer). Supported versions that are affected are 5.5.58 and prior, 5.6.38 and prior and 5.7.20 and prior. Easily exploitable vulnerability allows low privileged attacker with network access via multiple protocols to compromise MySQL Server. Successful attacks of this vulnerability can result in unauthorized ability to cause a hang or frequently repeatable crash (complete DOS) of MySQL Server. CVSS 3.0 Base Score 6.5 (Availability impacts). CVSS Vector: (CVSS:3.0/AV:N/AC:L/PR:L/UI:N/S:U/C:N/I:N/A:H).\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2018-2668\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"5.5.59-0ubuntu0.14.04.1\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"mysql-5.5\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"5.5.47-0ubuntu0.14.04.1\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2017-3312\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Vulnerability in the MySQL Server component of Oracle MySQL (subcomponent: Server: Packaging). Supported versions that are affected are 5.5.53 and earlier, 5.6.34 and earlier and 5.7.16 and earlier. Difficult to exploit vulnerability allows low privileged attacker with logon to the infrastructure where MySQL Server executes to compromise MySQL Server. Successful attacks require human interaction from a person other than the attacker. Successful attacks of this vulnerability can result in takeover of MySQL Server. CVSS v3.0 Base Score 6.7 (Confidentiality, Integrity and Availability impacts).\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2017-3312\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"5.5.54-0ubuntu0.14.04.1\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"python2.7\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.7.6-8ubuntu0.2\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-0772\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"The smtplib library in CPython (aka Python) before 2.7.12, 3.x before 3.4.5, and 3.5.x before 3.5.2 does not return an error when StartTLS fails, which might allow man-in-the-middle attackers to bypass the TLS protections by leveraging a network position between the client and the registry to block the StartTLS command, aka a \\\"StartTLS stripping attack.\\\"\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-0772\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2.7.6-8ubuntu0.3\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"python2.7\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.7.6-8ubuntu0.2\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2019-20907\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"In Lib/tarfile.py in Python through 3.8.3, an attacker is able to craft a TAR archive leading to an infinite loop when opened by tarfile.open, because _proc_pax lacks header validation.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2019-20907\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2.7.6-8ubuntu0.6+esm6\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"python2.7\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.7.6-8ubuntu0.2\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2017-1000158\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"CPython (aka Python) up to 2.7.13 is vulnerable to an integer overflow in the PyString_DecodeEscape function in stringobject.c, resulting in heap-based buffer overflow (and possible arbitrary code execution)\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2017-1000158\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2.7.6-8ubuntu0.4\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"python2.7\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.7.6-8ubuntu0.2\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2018-14647\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Python's elementtree C accelerator failed to initialise Expat's hash salt during initialization. This could make it easy to conduct denial of service attacks against Expat by constructing an XML document that would cause pathological hash collisions in Expat's internal data structures, consuming large amounts CPU and RAM. The vulnerability exists in Python versions 3.7.0, 3.6.0 through 3.6.6, 3.5.0 through 3.5.6, 3.4.0 through 3.4.9, 2.7.0 through 2.7.15.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2018-14647\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2.7.6-8ubuntu0.5\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"python2.7\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.7.6-8ubuntu0.2\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2019-10160\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"A security regression of CVE-2019-9636 was discovered in python since commit d537ab0ff9767ef024f26246899728f0116b1ec3 affecting versions 2.7, 3.5, 3.6, 3.7 and from v3.8.0a4 through v3.8.0b1, which still allows an attacker to exploit CVE-2019-9636 by abusing the user and password parts of a URL. When an application parses user-supplied URLs to store cookies, authentication credentials, or other kind of information, it is possible for an attacker to provide specially crafted URLs to make the application locate host-related information (e.g. cookies, authentication data) and send them to a different host than where it should, unlike if the URLs had been correctly parsed. The result of an attack may vary based on the application.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2019-10160\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2.7.6-8ubuntu0.6+esm2\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"mysql-5.5\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"5.5.47-0ubuntu0.14.04.1\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-3492\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Unspecified vulnerability in Oracle MySQL 5.5.51 and earlier, 5.6.32 and earlier, and 5.7.14 and earlier allows remote authenticated users to affect availability via vectors related to Server: Optimizer.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-3492\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"5.5.52-0ubuntu0.14.04.1\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"mysql-5.5\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"5.5.47-0ubuntu0.14.04.1\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2017-3313\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Vulnerability in the MySQL Server component of Oracle MySQL (subcomponent: Server: MyISAM). Supported versions that are affected are 5.5.53 and earlier, 5.6.34 and earlier and 5.7.16 and earlier. Difficult to exploit vulnerability allows low privileged attacker with logon to the infrastructure where MySQL Server executes to compromise MySQL Server. Successful attacks of this vulnerability can result in unauthorized access to critical data or complete access to all MySQL Server accessible data. CVSS v3.0 Base Score 4.7 (Confidentiality impacts).\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2017-3313\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"5.5.54-0ubuntu0.14.04.1\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"gnutls26\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.12.23-12ubuntu2.4\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2017-5337\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Multiple heap-based buffer overflows in the read_attribute function in GnuTLS before 3.3.26 and 3.5.x before 3.5.8 allow remote attackers to have unspecified impact via a crafted OpenPGP certificate.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2017-5337\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2.12.23-12ubuntu2.6\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"gnutls26\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.12.23-12ubuntu2.4\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2017-5335\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"The stream reading functions in lib/opencdk/read-packet.c in GnuTLS before 3.3.26 and 3.5.x before 3.5.8 allow remote attackers to cause a denial of service (out-of-memory error and crash) via a crafted OpenPGP certificate.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2017-5335\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2.12.23-12ubuntu2.6\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"mysql-5.5\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"5.5.47-0ubuntu0.14.04.1\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-0666\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Unspecified vulnerability in Oracle MySQL 5.5.48 and earlier, 5.6.29 and earlier, and 5.7.11 and earlier and MariaDB before 5.5.49, 10.0.x before 10.0.25, and 10.1.x before 10.1.14 allows local users to affect availability via vectors related to Security: Privileges.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-0666\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"5.5.49-0ubuntu0.14.04.1\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"gnutls26\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.12.23-12ubuntu2.4\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2017-5336\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Stack-based buffer overflow in the cdk_pk_get_keyid function in lib/opencdk/pubkey.c in GnuTLS before 3.3.26 and 3.5.x before 3.5.8 allows remote attackers to have unspecified impact via a crafted OpenPGP certificate.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2017-5336\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2.12.23-12ubuntu2.6\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"procps\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1:3.3.9-1ubuntu2.2\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2018-1126\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"procps-ng before version 3.3.15 is vulnerable to an incorrect integer size in proc/alloc.* leading to truncation/integer overflow issues. This flaw is related to CVE-2018-1124.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2018-1126\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"1:3.3.9-1ubuntu2.3\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"procps\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1:3.3.9-1ubuntu2.2\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2018-1122\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"procps-ng before version 3.3.15 is vulnerable to a local privilege escalation in top. If a user runs top with HOME unset in an attacker-controlled directory, the attacker could achieve privilege escalation by exploiting one of several vulnerabilities in the config_file() function.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2018-1122\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"1:3.3.9-1ubuntu2.3\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"procps\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1:3.3.9-1ubuntu2.2\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2018-1124\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"procps-ng before version 3.3.15 is vulnerable to multiple integer overflows leading to a heap corruption in file2strvec function. This allows a privilege escalation for a local attacker who can create entries in procfs by starting processes, which could result in crashes or arbitrary code execution in proc utilities run by other users.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2018-1124\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"1:3.3.9-1ubuntu2.3\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"procps\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1:3.3.9-1ubuntu2.2\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2018-1125\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"procps-ng before version 3.3.15 is vulnerable to a stack buffer overflow in pgrep. This vulnerability is mitigated by FORTIFY, as it involves strncat() to a stack-allocated string. When pgrep is compiled with FORTIFY (as on Red Hat Enterprise Linux and Fedora), the impact is limited to a crash.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2018-1125\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"1:3.3.9-1ubuntu2.3\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"procps\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1:3.3.9-1ubuntu2.2\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2018-1123\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"procps-ng before version 3.3.15 is vulnerable to a denial of service in ps via mmap buffer overflow. Inbuilt protection in ps maps a guard page at the end of the overflowed buffer, ensuring that the impact of this flaw is limited to a crash (temporary denial of service).\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2018-1123\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"1:3.3.9-1ubuntu2.3\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"libidn\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1.28-1ubuntu2\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2017-14062\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Integer overflow in the decode_digit function in puny_decode.c in Libidn2 before 2.0.4 allows remote attackers to cause a denial of service or possibly have unspecified other impact.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2017-14062\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"1.28-1ubuntu2.2\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"mysql-5.5\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"5.5.47-0ubuntu0.14.04.1\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2018-2761\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Vulnerability in the MySQL Server component of Oracle MySQL (subcomponent: Client programs). Supported versions that are affected are 5.5.59 and prior, 5.6.39 and prior and 5.7.21 and prior. Difficult to exploit vulnerability allows unauthenticated attacker with network access via multiple protocols to compromise MySQL Server. Successful attacks of this vulnerability can result in unauthorized ability to cause a hang or frequently repeatable crash (complete DOS) of MySQL Server. CVSS 3.0 Base Score 5.9 (Availability impacts). CVSS Vector: (CVSS:3.0/AV:N/AC:H/PR:N/UI:N/S:U/C:N/I:N/A:H).\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2018-2761\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"5.5.60-0ubuntu0.14.04.1\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"libidn\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1.28-1ubuntu2\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-6262\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"idn in libidn before 1.33 might allow remote attackers to obtain sensitive memory information by reading a zero byte as input, which triggers an out-of-bounds read, a different vulnerability than CVE-2015-8948.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-6262\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"1.28-1ubuntu2.1\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"libidn\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1.28-1ubuntu2\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-6263\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"The stringprep_utf8_nfkc_normalize function in lib/nfkc.c in libidn before 1.33 allows context-dependent attackers to cause a denial of service (out-of-bounds read and crash) via crafted UTF-8 data.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-6263\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"1.28-1ubuntu2.1\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"libidn\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1.28-1ubuntu2\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-6261\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"The idna_to_ascii_4i function in lib/idna.c in libidn before 1.33 allows context-dependent attackers to cause a denial of service (out-of-bounds read and crash) via 64 bytes of input.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-6261\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"1.28-1ubuntu2.1\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"mysql-5.5\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"5.5.47-0ubuntu0.14.04.1\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-0641\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Unspecified vulnerability in Oracle MySQL 5.5.47 and earlier, 5.6.28 and earlier, and 5.7.10 and earlier and MariaDB before 5.5.48, 10.0.x before 10.0.24, and 10.1.x before 10.1.12 allows local users to affect confidentiality and availability via vectors related to MyISAM.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-0641\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"5.5.49-0ubuntu0.14.04.1\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"apache2\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.4.7-1ubuntu4.9\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-8743\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Apache HTTP Server, in all releases prior to 2.2.32 and 2.4.25, was liberal in the whitespace accepted from requests and sent in response lines and headers. Accepting these different behaviors represented a security concern when httpd participates in any chain of proxies or interacts with back-end application servers, either through mod_proxy or using conventional CGI mechanisms, and may result in request smuggling, response splitting and cache pollution.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-8743\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2.4.7-1ubuntu4.14\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"mysql-5.5\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"5.5.47-0ubuntu0.14.04.1\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2017-3641\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Vulnerability in the MySQL Server component of Oracle MySQL (subcomponent: Server: DML). Supported versions that are affected are 5.5.56 and earlier, 5.6.36 and earlier and 5.7.18 and earlier. Easily exploitable vulnerability allows high privileged attacker with network access via multiple protocols to compromise MySQL Server. Successful attacks of this vulnerability can result in unauthorized ability to cause a hang or frequently repeatable crash (complete DOS) of MySQL Server. CVSS 3.0 Base Score 4.9 (Availability impacts). CVSS Vector: (CVSS:3.0/AV:N/AC:L/PR:H/UI:N/S:U/C:N/I:N/A:H).\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2017-3641\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"5.5.57-0ubuntu0.14.04.1\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"mysql-5.5\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"5.5.47-0ubuntu0.14.04.1\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2018-2817\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Vulnerability in the MySQL Server component of Oracle MySQL (subcomponent: Server: DDL). Supported versions that are affected are 5.5.59 and prior, 5.6.39 and prior and 5.7.21 and prior. Easily exploitable vulnerability allows low privileged attacker with network access via multiple protocols to compromise MySQL Server. Successful attacks of this vulnerability can result in unauthorized ability to cause a hang or frequently repeatable crash (complete DOS) of MySQL Server. CVSS 3.0 Base Score 6.5 (Availability impacts). CVSS Vector: (CVSS:3.0/AV:N/AC:L/PR:L/UI:N/S:U/C:N/I:N/A:H).\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2018-2817\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"5.5.60-0ubuntu0.14.04.1\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"mysql-5.5\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"5.5.47-0ubuntu0.14.04.1\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2017-10378\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Vulnerability in the MySQL Server component of Oracle MySQL (subcomponent: Server: Optimizer). Supported versions that are affected are 5.5.57 and earlier, 5.6.37 and earlier and 5.7.11 and earlier. Easily exploitable vulnerability allows low privileged attacker with network access via multiple protocols to compromise MySQL Server. Successful attacks of this vulnerability can result in unauthorized ability to cause a hang or frequently repeatable crash (complete DOS) of MySQL Server. CVSS 3.0 Base Score 6.5 (Availability impacts). CVSS Vector: (CVSS:3.0/AV:N/AC:L/PR:L/UI:N/S:U/C:N/I:N/A:H).\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2017-10378\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"5.5.58-0ubuntu0.14.04.1\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"mysql-5.5\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"5.5.47-0ubuntu0.14.04.1\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2017-10379\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Vulnerability in the MySQL Server component of Oracle MySQL (subcomponent: Client programs). Supported versions that are affected are 5.5.57 and earlier, 5.6.37 and earlier and 5.7.19 and earlier. Easily exploitable vulnerability allows low privileged attacker with network access via multiple protocols to compromise MySQL Server. Successful attacks of this vulnerability can result in unauthorized access to critical data or complete access to all MySQL Server accessible data. CVSS 3.0 Base Score 6.5 (Confidentiality impacts). CVSS Vector: (CVSS:3.0/AV:N/AC:L/PR:L/UI:N/S:U/C:H/I:N/A:N).\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2017-10379\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"5.5.58-0ubuntu0.14.04.1\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"mysql-5.5\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"5.5.47-0ubuntu0.14.04.1\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-5624\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Unspecified vulnerability in Oracle MySQL 5.5.51 and earlier allows remote authenticated users to affect availability via vectors related to DML.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-5624\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"5.5.52-0ubuntu0.14.04.1\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"mysql-5.5\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"5.5.47-0ubuntu0.14.04.1\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2018-2755\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Vulnerability in the MySQL Server component of Oracle MySQL (subcomponent: Server: Replication). Supported versions that are affected are 5.5.59 and prior, 5.6.39 and prior and 5.7.21 and prior. Difficult to exploit vulnerability allows unauthenticated attacker with logon to the infrastructure where MySQL Server executes to compromise MySQL Server. Successful attacks require human interaction from a person other than the attacker and while the vulnerability is in MySQL Server, attacks may significantly impact additional products. Successful attacks of this vulnerability can result in takeover of MySQL Server. CVSS 3.0 Base Score 7.7 (Confidentiality, Integrity and Availability impacts). CVSS Vector: (CVSS:3.0/AV:L/AC:H/PR:N/UI:R/S:C/C:H/I:H/A:H).\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2018-2755\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"5.5.60-0ubuntu0.14.04.1\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"apache2\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.4.7-1ubuntu4.9\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2017-9798\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Apache httpd allows remote attackers to read secret data from process memory if the Limit directive can be set in a user's .htaccess file, or if httpd.conf has certain misconfigurations, aka Optionsbleed. This affects the Apache HTTP Server through 2.2.34 and 2.4.x through 2.4.27. The attacker sends an unauthenticated OPTIONS HTTP request when attempting to read secret data. This is a use-after-free issue and thus secret data is not always sent, and the specific data depends on many factors including configuration. Exploitation with .htaccess can be blocked with a patch to the ap_limit_section function in server/core.c.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2017-9798\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2.4.7-1ubuntu4.18\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"mysql-5.5\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"5.5.47-0ubuntu0.14.04.1\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2017-3291\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Vulnerability in the MySQL Server component of Oracle MySQL (subcomponent: Server: Packaging). Supported versions that are affected are 5.5.53 and earlier, 5.6.34 and earlier and 5.7.16 and earlier. Difficult to exploit vulnerability allows high privileged attacker with logon to the infrastructure where MySQL Server executes to compromise MySQL Server. Successful attacks require human interaction from a person other than the attacker. Successful attacks of this vulnerability can result in takeover of MySQL Server. CVSS v3.0 Base Score 6.3 (Confidentiality, Integrity and Availability impacts).\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2017-3291\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"5.5.54-0ubuntu0.14.04.1\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"apache2\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.4.7-1ubuntu4.9\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2017-9788\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"In Apache httpd before 2.2.34 and 2.4.x before 2.4.27, the value placeholder in [Proxy-]Authorization headers of type 'Digest' was not initialized or reset before or between successive key=value assignments by mod_auth_digest. Providing an initial key with no '=' assignment could reflect the stale value of uninitialized pool memory used by the prior request, leading to leakage of potentially confidential information, and a segfault in other cases resulting in denial of service.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2017-9788\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2.4.7-1ubuntu4.17\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"mysql-5.5\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"5.5.47-0ubuntu0.14.04.1\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2018-2813\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Vulnerability in the MySQL Server component of Oracle MySQL (subcomponent: Server: DDL). Supported versions that are affected are 5.5.59 and prior, 5.6.39 and prior and 5.7.21 and prior. Easily exploitable vulnerability allows low privileged attacker with network access via multiple protocols to compromise MySQL Server. Successful attacks of this vulnerability can result in unauthorized read access to a subset of MySQL Server accessible data. CVSS 3.0 Base Score 4.3 (Confidentiality impacts). CVSS Vector: (CVSS:3.0/AV:N/AC:L/PR:L/UI:N/S:U/C:L/I:N/A:N).\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2018-2813\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"5.5.60-0ubuntu0.14.04.1\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"mysql-5.5\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"5.5.47-0ubuntu0.14.04.1\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-0648\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Unspecified vulnerability in Oracle MySQL 5.5.48 and earlier, 5.6.29 and earlier, and 5.7.11 and earlier and MariaDB before 5.5.49, 10.0.x before 10.0.25, and 10.1.x before 10.1.14 allows local users to affect availability via vectors related to PS.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-0648\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"5.5.49-0ubuntu0.14.04.1\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"mysql-5.5\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"5.5.47-0ubuntu0.14.04.1\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2017-3464\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Vulnerability in the MySQL Server component of Oracle MySQL (subcomponent: Server: DDL). Supported versions that are affected are 5.5.54 and earlier, 5.6.35 and earlier and 5.7.17 and earlier. Easily \\\"exploitable\\\" vulnerability allows low privileged attacker with network access via multiple protocols to compromise MySQL Server. Successful attacks of this vulnerability can result in unauthorized update, insert or delete access to some of MySQL Server accessible data. CVSS 3.0 Base Score 4.3 (Integrity impacts). CVSS Vector: (CVSS:3.0/AV:N/AC:L/PR:L/UI:N/S:U/C:N/I:L/A:N).\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2017-3464\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"5.5.55-0ubuntu0.14.04.1\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"apache2\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.4.7-1ubuntu4.9\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2017-3169\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"In Apache httpd 2.2.x before 2.2.33 and 2.4.x before 2.4.26, mod_ssl may dereference a NULL pointer when third-party modules call ap_hook_process_connection() during an HTTP request to an HTTPS port.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2017-3169\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2.4.7-1ubuntu4.16\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"apache2\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.4.7-1ubuntu4.9\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-5387\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"The Apache HTTP Server through 2.4.23 follows RFC 3875 section 4.1.18 and therefore does not protect applications from the presence of untrusted client data in the HTTP_PROXY environment variable, which might allow remote attackers to redirect an application's outbound HTTP traffic to an arbitrary proxy server via a crafted Proxy header in an HTTP request, aka an \\\"httpoxy\\\" issue.  NOTE: the vendor states \\\"This mitigation has been assigned the identifier CVE-2016-5387\\\"; in other words, this is not a CVE ID for a vulnerability.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-5387\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2.4.7-1ubuntu4.13\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"apache2\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.4.7-1ubuntu4.9\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2019-0217\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"In Apache HTTP Server 2.4 release 2.4.38 and prior, a race condition in mod_auth_digest when running in a threaded server could allow a user with valid credentials to authenticate using another username, bypassing configured access control restrictions.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2019-0217\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2.4.7-1ubuntu4.22\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"apache2\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.4.7-1ubuntu4.9\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2017-3167\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"In Apache httpd 2.2.x before 2.2.33 and 2.4.x before 2.4.26, use of the ap_get_basic_auth_pw() by third-party modules outside of the authentication phase may lead to authentication requirements being bypassed.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2017-3167\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2.4.7-1ubuntu4.16\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"mysql-5.5\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"5.5.47-0ubuntu0.14.04.1\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2018-2622\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Vulnerability in the MySQL Server component of Oracle MySQL (subcomponent: Server: DDL). Supported versions that are affected are 5.5.58 and prior, 5.6.38 and prior and 5.7.20 and prior. Easily exploitable vulnerability allows low privileged attacker with network access via multiple protocols to compromise MySQL Server. Successful attacks of this vulnerability can result in unauthorized ability to cause a hang or frequently repeatable crash (complete DOS) of MySQL Server. CVSS 3.0 Base Score 6.5 (Availability impacts). CVSS Vector: (CVSS:3.0/AV:N/AC:L/PR:L/UI:N/S:U/C:N/I:N/A:H)