 \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2018-3066\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Vulnerability in the MySQL Server component of Oracle MySQL (subcomponent: Server: Options). Supported versions that are affected are 5.5.60 and prior, 5.6.40 and prior and 5.7.22 and prior. Difficult to exploit vulnerability allows high privileged attacker with network access via multiple protocols to compromise MySQL Server. Successful attacks of this vulnerability can result in unauthorized update, insert or delete access to some of MySQL Server accessible data as well as unauthorized read access to a subset of MySQL Server accessible data. CVSS 3.0 Base Score 3.3 (Confidentiality and Integrity impacts). CVSS Vector: (CVSS:3.0/AV:N/AC:H/PR:H/UI:N/S:U/C:L/I:L/A:N).\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2018-3066\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"5.5.61-0ubuntu0.14.04.1\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"mysql-5.5\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"5.5.47-0ubuntu0.14.04.1\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2018-3081\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Vulnerability in the MySQL Client component of Oracle MySQL (subcomponent: Client programs). Supported versions that are affected are 5.5.60 and prior, 5.6.40 and prior, 5.7.22 and prior and 8.0.11 and prior. Difficult to exploit vulnerability allows high privileged attacker with network access via multiple protocols to compromise MySQL Client. Successful attacks of this vulnerability can result in unauthorized ability to cause a hang or frequently repeatable crash (complete DOS) of MySQL Client as well as unauthorized update, insert or delete access to some of MySQL Client accessible data. CVSS 3.0 Base Score 5.0 (Integrity and Availability impacts). CVSS Vector: (CVSS:3.0/AV:N/AC:H/PR:H/UI:N/S:U/C:N/I:L/A:H).\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2018-3081\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"5.5.61-0ubuntu0.14.04.1\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"rsync\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"3.1.0-2ubuntu0.2\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2018-5764\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"The parse_arguments function in options.c in rsyncd in rsync before 3.1.3 does not prevent multiple --protect-args uses, which allows remote attackers to bypass an argument-sanitization protection mechanism.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2018-5764\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"3.1.0-2ubuntu0.4\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"rsync\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"3.1.0-2ubuntu0.2\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2017-17434\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"The daemon in rsync 3.1.2, and 3.1.3-development before 2017-12-03, does not check for fnamecmp filenames in the daemon_filter_list data structure (in the recv_files function in receiver.c) and also does not apply the sanitize_paths protection mechanism to pathnames found in \\\"xname follows\\\" strings (in the read_ndx_and_attrs function in rsync.c), which allows remote attackers to bypass intended access restrictions.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2017-17434\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"3.1.0-2ubuntu0.3\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"rsync\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"3.1.0-2ubuntu0.2\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2017-17433\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"The recv_files function in receiver.c in the daemon in rsync 3.1.2, and 3.1.3-development before 2017-12-03, proceeds with certain file metadata updates before checking for a filename in the daemon_filter_list data structure, which allows remote attackers to bypass intended access restrictions.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2017-17433\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"3.1.0-2ubuntu0.3\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"mysql-5.5\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"5.5.47-0ubuntu0.14.04.1\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2017-3244\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Vulnerability in the MySQL Server component of Oracle MySQL (subcomponent: Server: DML). Supported versions that are affected are 5.5.53 and earlier, 5.6.34 and earlier and 5.7.16 and earlier. Easily exploitable vulnerability allows low privileged attacker with network access via multiple protocols to compromise MySQL Server. Successful attacks of this vulnerability can result in unauthorized ability to cause a hang or frequently repeatable crash (complete DOS) of MySQL Server. CVSS v3.0 Base Score 6.5 (Availability impacts).\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2017-3244\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"5.5.54-0ubuntu0.14.04.1\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"dbus\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1.6.18-0ubuntu4.3\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2015-0245\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"D-Bus 1.4.x through 1.6.x before 1.6.30, 1.8.x before 1.8.16, and 1.9.x before 1.9.10 does not validate the source of ActivationFailure signals, which allows local users to cause a denial of service (activation failure error returned) by leveraging a race condition involving sending an ActivationFailure signal before systemd responds.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2015-0245\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"1.6.18-0ubuntu4.4\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"dbus\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1.6.18-0ubuntu4.3\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2020-12049\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"An issue was discovered in dbus \\u003e= 1.3.0 before 1.12.18. The DBusServer in libdbus, as used in dbus-daemon, leaks file descriptors when a message exceeds the per-message file descriptor limit. A local attacker with access to the D-Bus system bus or another system service's private AF_UNIX socket could use this to make the system service reach its file descriptor limit, denying service to subsequent D-Bus clients.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2020-12049\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"1.6.18-0ubuntu4.5+esm2\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"dbus\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1.6.18-0ubuntu4.3\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2019-12749\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"dbus before 1.10.28, 1.12.x before 1.12.16, and 1.13.x before 1.13.12, as used in DBusServer in Canonical Upstart in Ubuntu 14.04 (and in some, less common, uses of dbus-daemon), allows cookie spoofing because of symlink mishandling in the reference implementation of DBUS_COOKIE_SHA1 in the libdbus library. (This only affects the DBUS_COOKIE_SHA1 authentication mechanism.) A malicious client with write access to its own home directory could manipulate a ~/.dbus-keyrings symlink to cause a DBusServer with a different uid to read and write in unintended locations. In the worst case, this could result in the DBusServer reusing a cookie that is known to the malicious client, and treating that cookie as evidence that a subsequent client connection came from an attacker-chosen uid, allowing authentication bypass.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2019-12749\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"1.6.18-0ubuntu4.5+esm1\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"mysql-5.5\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"5.5.47-0ubuntu0.14.04.1\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2017-3329\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Vulnerability in the MySQL Server component of Oracle MySQL (subcomponent: Server: Thread Pooling). Supported versions that are affected are 5.5.54 and earlier, 5.6.35 and earlier and 5.7.17 and earlier. Easily \\\"exploitable\\\" vulnerability allows unauthenticated attacker with network access via multiple protocols to compromise MySQL Server. Successful attacks of this vulnerability can result in unauthorized ability to cause a hang or frequently repeatable crash (complete DOS) of MySQL Server. CVSS 3.0 Base Score 7.5 (Availability impacts). CVSS Vector: (CVSS:3.0/AV:N/AC:L/PR:N/UI:N/S:U/C:N/I:N/A:H).\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2017-3329\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"5.5.55-0ubuntu0.14.04.1\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"perl\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"5.18.2-2ubuntu1\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-2381\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Perl might allow context-dependent attackers to bypass the taint protection mechanism in a child process via duplicate environment variables in envp.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-2381\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"5.18.2-2ubuntu1.1\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"mysql-5.5\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"5.5.47-0ubuntu0.14.04.1\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2017-330