-stmt-sqlstate.html. CVSS 3.0 Base Score 5.3 (Availability impacts). CVSS Vector: (CVSS:3.0/AV:N/AC:H/PR:L/UI:N/S:U/C:N/I:N/A:H).\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2017-3635\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"5.5.57-0ubuntu0.14.04.1\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"file\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1:5.14-2ubuntu3.3\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2019-18218\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"cdf_read_property_info in cdf.c in file through 5.37 does not restrict the number of CDF_VECTOR elements, which allows a heap-based buffer overflow (4-byte out-of-bounds write).\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2019-18218\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"1:5.14-2ubuntu3.4+esm1\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"mysql-5.5\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"5.5.47-0ubuntu0.14.04.1\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2017-3318\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Vulnerability in the MySQL Server component of Oracle MySQL (subcomponent: Server: Error Handling). Supported versions that are affected are 5.5.53 and earlier, 5.6.34 and earlier and 5.7.16 and earlier. Difficult to exploit vulnerability allows high privileged attacker with logon to the infrastructure where MySQL Server executes to compromise MySQL Server. Successful attacks require human interaction from a person other than the attacker. Successful attacks of this vulnerability can result in unauthorized access to critical data or complete access to all MySQL Server accessible data. CVSS v3.0 Base Score 4.0 (Confidentiality impacts).\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2017-3318\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"5.5.54-0ubuntu0.14.04.1\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"mysql-5.5\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"5.5.47-0ubuntu0.14.04.1\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2018-3133\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Vulnerability in the MySQL Server component of Oracle MySQL (subcomponent: Server: Parser). Supported versions that are affected are 5.5.61 and prior, 5.6.41 and prior, 5.7.23 and prior and 8.0.12 and prior. Easily exploitable vulnerability allows low privileged attacker with network access via multiple protocols to compromise MySQL Server. Successful attacks of this vulnerability can result in unauthorized ability to cause a hang or frequently repeatable crash (complete DOS) of MySQL Server. CVSS 3.0 Base Score 6.5 (Availability impacts). CVSS Vector: (CVSS:3.0/AV:N/AC:L/PR:L/UI:N/S:U/C:N/I:N/A:H).\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2018-3133\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"5.5.62-0ubuntu0.14.04.1\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"mysql-5.5\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"5.5.47-0ubuntu0.14.04.1\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2018-2781\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Vulnerability in the MySQL Server component of Oracle MySQL (subcomponent: Server: Optimizer). Supported versions that are affected are 5.5.59 and prior, 5.6.39 and prior and 5.7.21 and prior. Easily exploitable vulnerability allows high privileged attacker with network access via multiple protocols to compromise MySQL Server. Successful attacks of this vulnerability can result in unauthorized ability to cause a hang or frequently repeatable crash (complete DOS) of MySQL Server. CVSS 3.0 Base Score 4.9 (Availability impacts). CVSS Vector: (CVSS:3.0/AV:N/AC:L/PR:H/UI:N/S:U/C:N/I:N/A:H).\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2018-2781\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"5.5.60-0ubuntu0.14.04.1\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"libdbi-perl\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1.630-1\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2013-7490\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"An issue was discovered in the DBI module before 1.632 for Perl. Using many arguments to methods for Callbacks may lead to memory corruption.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2013-7490\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"1.630-1ubuntu0.1~esm4\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"libx11\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2:1.6.2-1ubuntu2\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2018-14598\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"An issue was discovered in XListExtensions in ListExt.c in libX11 through 1.6.5. A malicious server can send a reply in which the first string overflows, causing a variable to be set to NULL that will be freed later on, leading to DoS (segmentation fault).\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2018-14598\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2:1.6.2-1ubuntu2.1\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"libdbi-perl\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1.630-1\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2014-10402\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"An issue was discovered in the DBI module through 1.643 for Perl. DBD::File drivers can open files from folders other than those specifically passed via the f_dir attribute in the data source name (DSN). NOTE: this issue exists because of an incomplete fix for CVE-2014-10401.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2014-10402\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"libdbi-perl\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1.630-1\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2014-10401\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"An issue was discovered in the DBI module before 1.632 for Perl. DBD::File drivers can open files from folders other than those specifically passed via the f_dir attribute.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2014-10401\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"1.630-1ubuntu0.1~esm4\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"libdbi-perl\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1.630-1\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2019-20919\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"An issue was discovered in the DBI module before 1.643 for Perl. The hv_fetch() documentation requires checking for NULL and the code does that. But, shortly thereafter, it calls SvOK(profile), causing a NULL pointer dereference.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2019-20919\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"1.630-1ubuntu0.1~esm5\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"libdbi-perl\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1.630-1\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2020-14392\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"An untrusted pointer dereference flaw was found in Perl-DBI \\u003c 1.643. A local attacker who is able to manipulate calls to dbd_db_login6_sv() could cause memory corruption, affecting the service's availability.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2020-14392\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"1.630-1ubuntu0.1~esm1\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"wget\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1.15-1ubuntu1.14.04.2\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2017-13089\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"The http.c:skip_short_body() function is called in some circumstances, such as when processing redirects. When the response is sent chunked in wget before 1.19.2, the chunk parser uses strtol() to read each chunk's length, but doesn't check that the chunk length is a non-negative number. The code then tries to skip the chunk in pieces of 512 bytes by using the MIN() macro, but ends up passing the negative chunk length to connect.c:fd_read(). As fd_read() takes an int argument, the high 32 bits of the chunk length are discarded, leaving fd_read() with a completely attacker controlled length argument.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2017-13089\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"1.15-1ubuntu1.14.04.3\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"wget\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1.15-1ubuntu1.14.04.2\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2019-5953\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Buffer overflow in GNU Wget 1.20.1 and earlier allows remote attackers to cause a denial-of-service (DoS) or may execute an arbitrary code via unspecified vectors.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2019-5953\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"1.15-1ubuntu1.14.04.5\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"wget\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1.15-1ubuntu1.14.04.2\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2018-0494\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"GNU Wget before 1.19.5 is prone to a cookie injection vulnerability in the resp_new function in http.c via a \\\\r\\\\n sequence in a continuation line.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2018-0494\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"1.15-1ubuntu1.14.04.4\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"libx11\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2:1.6.2-1ubuntu2\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2020-14363\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"An integer overflow vulnerability leading to a double-free was found in libX11. This flaw allows a local privileged attacker to cause an application compiled with libX11 to crash, or in some cases, result in arbitrary code execution. The highest threat from this flaw is to confidentiality, integrity as well as system availability.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2020-14363\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2:1.6.2-1ubuntu2.1+esm1\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"wget\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1.15-1ubuntu1.14.04.2\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2017-13090\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"The retr.c:fd_read_body() function is called when processing OK responses. When the response is sent chunked in wget before 1.19.2, the chunk parser uses strtol() to read each chunk's length, but doesn't check that the chunk length is a non-negative number. The code then tries to read the chunk in pieces of 8192 bytes by using the MIN() macro, but ends up passing the negative chunk length to retr.c:fd_read(). As fd_read() takes an int argument, the high 32 bits of the chunk length are discarded, leaving fd_read() with a completely attacker controlled length argument. The attacker can corrupt malloc metadata after the allocated buffer.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2017-13090\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"1.15-1ubuntu1.14.04.3\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"libx11\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2:1.6.2-1ubuntu2\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2018-14600\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"An issue was discovered in libX11 through 1.6.5. The function XListExtensions in ListExt.c interprets a variable as signed instead of unsigned, resulting in an out-of-bounds write (of up to 128 bytes), leading to DoS or remote code execution.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2018-14600\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2:1.6.2-1ubuntu2.1\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"libx11\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2:1.6.2-1ubuntu2\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2018-14599\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"An issue was discovered in libX11 through 1.6.5. The function XListExtensions in ListExt.c is vulnerable to an off-by-one error caused by malicious server responses, leading to DoS or possibly unspecified other impact.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2018-14599\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2:1.6.2-1ubuntu2.1\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"libx11\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2:1.6.2-1ubuntu2\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2020-14344\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"An integer overflow leading to a heap-buffer overflow was found in The X Input Method (XIM) client was implemented in libX11 before version 1.6.10. As per upstream this is security relevant when setuid programs call XIM client functions while running with elevated privileges. No such programs are shipped with Red Hat Enterprise Linux.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2020-14344\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2:1.6.2-1ubuntu2.1+esm1\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"pcre3\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1:8.31-2ubuntu2.1\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-3191\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"The compile_branch function in pcre_compile.c in PCRE 8.x before 8.39 and pcre2_compile.c in PCRE2 before 10.22 mishandles patterns containing an (*ACCEPT) substring in conjunction with nested parentheses, which allows remote attackers to execute arbitrary code or cause a denial of service (stack-based buffer overflow) via a crafted regular expression, as demonstrated by a JavaScript RegExp object encountered by Konqueror, aka ZDI-CAN-3542.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-3191\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"1:8.31-2ubuntu2.2\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"sqlite3\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"3.8.2-1ubuntu2.1\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2019-13734\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Out of bounds write in SQLite in Google Chrome prior to 79.0.3945.79 allowed a remote attacker to potentially exploit heap corruption via a crafted HTML page.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2019-13734\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"3.8.2-1ubuntu2.2+esm2\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"sqlite3\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"3.8.2-1ubuntu2.1\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2020-9794\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"An out-of-bounds read was addressed with improved bounds checking. This issue is fixed in iOS 13.5 and iPadOS 13.5, macOS Catalina 10.15.5, tvOS 13.4.5, watchOS 6.2.5, iTunes 12.10.7 for Windows, iCloud for Windows 11.2, iCloud for Windows 7.19. A malicious application may cause a denial of service or potentially disclose memory contents.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2020-9794\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"curl\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"7.35.0-1ubuntu2.6\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2018-16839\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Curl versions 7.33.0 through 7.61.1 are vulnerable to a buffer overrun in the SASL authentication code that may lead to denial of service.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2018-16839\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"7.35.0-1ubuntu2.19\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"sqlite3\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"3.8.2-1ubuntu2.1\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2019-8457\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"SQLite3 from 3.6.0 to and including 3.27.2 is vulnerable to heap out-of-bound read in the rtreenode() function when handling invalid rtree tables.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2019-8457\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"3.8.2-1ubuntu2.2+esm1\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"curl\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"7.35.0-1ubuntu2.6\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-8615\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"A flaw was found in curl before version 7.51. If cookie state is written into a cookie jar file that is later read back and used for subsequent requests, a malicious HTTP server can inject new cookies for arbitrary domains into said cookie jar.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-8615\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"7.35.0-1ubuntu2.10\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"sqlite3\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"3.8.2-1ubuntu2.1\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2019-13752\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Out of bounds read in SQLite in Google Chrome prior to 79.0.3945.79 allowed a remote attacker to obtain potentially sensitive information from process memory via a crafted HTML page.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2019-13752\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"3.8.2-1ubuntu2.2+esm2\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"sqlite3\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"3.8.2-1ubuntu2.1\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2019-13750\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Insufficient data validation in SQLite in Google Chrome prior to 79.0.3945.79 allowed a remote attacker to bypass defense-in-depth measures via a crafted HTML page.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2019-13750\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"3.8.2-1ubuntu2.2+esm2\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"curl\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"7.35.0-1ubuntu2.6\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2017-1000257\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"An IMAP FETCH response line indicates the size of the returned data, in number of bytes. When that response says the data is zero bytes, libcurl would pass on that (non-existing) data with a pointer and the size (zero) to the deliver-data function. libcurl's deliver-data function treats zero as a magic number and invokes strlen() on the data to figure out the length. The strlen() is called on a heap based buffer that might not be zero terminated so libcurl might read beyond the end of it into whatever memory lies after (or just crash) and then deliver that to the application as if it was actually downloaded.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2017-1000257\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"7.35.0-1ubuntu2.12\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"sqlite3\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"3.8.2-1ubuntu2.1\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2019-13751\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Uninitialized data in SQLite in Google Chrome prior to 79.0.3945.79 allowed a remote attacker to obtain potentially sensitive information from process memory via a crafted HTML page.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2019-13751\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"3.8.2-1ubuntu2.2+esm2\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"sqlite3\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"3.8.2-1ubuntu2.1\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2019-19926\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"multiSelect in select.c in SQLite 3.30.1 mishandles certain errors during parsing, as demonstrated by errors from sqlite3WindowRewrite() calls. NOTE: this vulnerability exists because of an incomplete fix for CVE-2019-19880.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2019-19926\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"3.8.2-1ubuntu2.2+esm2\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"sqlite3\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"3.8.2-1ubuntu2.1\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2019-13753\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Out of bounds read in SQLite in Google Chrome prior to 79.0.3945.79 allowed a remote attacker to obtain potentially sensitive information from process memory via a crafted HTML page.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2019-13753\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"3.8.2-1ubuntu2.2+esm2\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"sqlite3\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"3.8.2-1ubuntu2.1\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2018-20346\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"SQLite before 3.25.3, when the FTS3 extension is enabled, encounters an integer overflow (and resultant buffer overflow) for FTS3 queries that occur after crafted changes to FTS3 shadow tables, allowing remote attackers to execute arbitrary code by leveraging the ability to run arbitrary SQL statements (such as in certain WebSQL use cases), aka Magellan.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2018-20346\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"3.8.2-1ubuntu2.2+esm1\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"curl\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"7.35.0-1ubuntu2.6\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2018-1000007\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"libcurl 7.1 through 7.57.0 might accidentally leak authentication data to third parties. When asked to send custom headers in its HTTP requests, libcurl will send that set of headers first to the host in the initial URL but also, if asked to follow redirects and a 30X HTTP response code is returned, to the host mentioned in URL in the `Location:` response header value. Sending the same set of headers to subsequent hosts is in particular a problem for applications that pass on custom `Authorization:` headers, as this header often contains privacy sensitive information or data that could allow others to impersonate the libcurl-using client's request.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2018-1000007\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"7.35.0-1ubuntu2.14\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"sqlite3\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"3.8.2-1ubuntu2.1\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2018-20506\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"SQLite before 3.25.3, when the FTS3 extension is enabled, encounters an integer overflow (and resultant buffer overflow) for FTS3 queries in a \\\"merge\\\" operation that occurs after crafted changes to FTS3 shadow tables, allowing remote attackers to execute arbitrary code by leveraging the ability to run arbitrary SQL statements (such as in certain WebSQL use cases). This is a different vulnerability than CVE-2018-20346.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2018-20506\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"3.8.2-1ubuntu2.2+esm1\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"krb5\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1.12+dfsg-2ubuntu5.2\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2015-8631\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Multiple memory leaks in kadmin/server/server_stubs.c in kadmind in MIT Kerberos 5 (aka krb5) before 1.13.4 and 1.14.x before 1.14.1 allow remote authenticated users to cause a denial of service (memory consumption) via a request specifying a NULL principal name.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2015-8631\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"1.12+dfsg-2ubuntu5.4\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"curl\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"7.35.0-1ubuntu2.6\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2017-8817\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"The FTP wildcard function in curl and libcurl before 7.57.0 allows remote attackers to cause a denial of service (out-of-bounds read and application crash) or possibly have unspecified other impact via a string that ends with an '[' character.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2017-8817\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"7.35.0-1ubuntu2.13\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"krb5\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1.12+dfsg-2ubuntu5.2\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2017-11368\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"In MIT Kerberos 5 (aka krb5) 1.7 and later, an authenticated attacker can cause a KDC assertion failure by sending invalid S4U2Self or S4U2Proxy requests.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2017-11368\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"1.12+dfsg-2ubuntu5.4\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"curl\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"7.35.0-1ubuntu2.6\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2020-8285\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"curl 7.21.0 to and including 7.73.0 is vulnerable to uncontrolled recursion due to a stack overflow issue in FTP wildcard match parsing.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2020-8285\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"7.35.0-1ubuntu2.20+esm6\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"krb5\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1.12+dfsg-2ubuntu5.2\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2020-28196\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"MIT Kerberos 5 (aka krb5) before 1.17.2 and 1.18.x before 1.18.3 allows unbounded recursion via an ASN.1-encoded Kerberos message because the lib/krb5/asn.1/asn1_encode.c support for BER indefinite lengths lacks a recursion limit.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2020-28196\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"1.12+dfsg-2ubuntu5.4+esm2\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"curl\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"7.35.0-1ubuntu2.6\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2018-1000121\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"A NULL pointer dereference exists in curl 7.21.0 to and including curl 7.58.0 in the LDAP code that allows an attacker to cause a denial of service\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2018-1000121\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"7.35.0-1ubuntu2.15\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"krb5\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1.12+dfsg-2ubuntu5.2\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-3119\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"The process_db_args function in plugins/kdb/ldap/libkdb_ldap/ldap_principal2.c in the LDAP KDB module in kadmind in MIT Kerberos 5 (aka krb5) through 1.13.4 and 1.14.x through 1.14.1 mishandles the DB argument, which allows remote authenticated users to cause a denial of service (NULL pointer dereference and daemon crash) via a crafted request to modify a principal.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-3119\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"1.12+dfsg-2ubuntu5.4\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"curl\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"7.35.0-1ubuntu2.6\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2020-8177\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"curl 7.20.0 through 7.70.0 is vulnerable to improper restriction of names for files and other resources that can lead too overwriting a local file when the -J flag is used.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2020-8177\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"7.35.0-1ubuntu2.20+esm4\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"curl\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"7.35.0-1ubuntu2.6\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2018-1000301\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"curl version curl 7.20.0 to and including curl 7.59.0 contains a CWE-126: Buffer Over-read vulnerability in denial of service that can result in curl can be tricked into reading data beyond the end of a heap based buffer used to store downloaded RTSP content.. This vulnerability appears to have been fixed in curl \\u003c 7.20.0 and curl \\u003e= 7.60.0.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2018-1000301\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"7.35.0-1ubuntu2.16\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"krb5\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1.12+dfsg-2ubuntu5.2\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2015-8629\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"The xdr_nullstring function in lib/kadm5/kadm_rpc_xdr.c in kadmind in MIT Kerberos 5 (aka krb5) before 1.13.4 and 1.14.x before 1.14.1 does not verify whether '\\\\0' characters exist as expected, which allows remote authenticated users to obtain sensitive information or cause a denial of service (out-of-bounds read) via a crafted string.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2015-8629\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"1.12+dfsg-2ubuntu5.4\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"krb5\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1.12+dfsg-2ubuntu5.2\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-3120\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"The validate_as_request function in kdc_util.c in the Key Distribution Center (KDC) in MIT Kerberos 5 (aka krb5) before 1.13.6 and 1.4.x before 1.14.3, when restrict_anonymous_to_tgt is enabled, uses an incorrect client data structure, which allows remote authenticated users to cause a denial of service (NULL pointer dereference and daemon crash) via an S4U2Self request.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-3120\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"1.12+dfsg-2ubuntu5.4\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"krb5\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1.12+dfsg-2ubuntu5.2\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2015-8630\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"The (1) kadm5_create_principal_3 and (2) kadm5_modify_principal functions in lib/kadm5/srv/svr_principal.c in kadmind in MIT Kerberos 5 (aka krb5) 1.12.x and 1.13.x before 1.13.4 and 1.14.x before 1.14.1 allow remote authenticated users to cause a denial of service (NULL pointer dereference and daemon crash) by specifying KADM5_POLICY with a NULL policy name.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2015-8630\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"1.12+dfsg-2ubuntu5.4\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"curl\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"7.35.0-1ubuntu2.6\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-8618\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"The libcurl API function called `curl_maprintf()` before version 7.51.0 can be tricked into doing a double-free due to an unsafe `size_t` multiplication, on systems using 32 bit `size_t` variables.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-8618\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"7.35.0-1ubuntu2.10\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"krb5\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1.12+dfsg-2ubuntu5.2\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2018-20217\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"A Reachable Assertion issue was discovered in the KDC in MIT Kerberos 5 (aka krb5) before 1.17. If an attacker can obtain a krbtgt ticket using an older encryption type (single-DES, triple-DES, or RC4), the attacker can crash the KDC by making an S4U2Self request.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2018-20217\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"libxml2\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.9.1+dfsg1-3ubuntu4.7\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-1834\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Heap-based buffer overflow in the xmlStrncat function in libxml2 before 2.9.4, as used in Apple iOS before 9.3.2, OS X before 10.11.5, tvOS before 9.2.1, and watchOS before 2.2.1, allows remote attackers to execute arbitrary code or cause a denial of service (memory corruption) via a crafted XML document.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-1834\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2.9.1+dfsg1-3ubuntu4.8\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"libxml2\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.9.1+dfsg1-3ubuntu4.7\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2018-14404\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"A NULL pointer dereference vulnerability exists in the xpath.c:xmlXPathCompOpEval() function of libxml2 through 2.9.8 when parsing an invalid XPath expression in the XPATH_OP_AND or XPATH_OP_OR case. Applications processing untrusted XSL format inputs with the use of the libxml2 library may be vulnerable to a denial of service attack due to a crash of the application.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2018-14404\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2.9.1+dfsg1-3ubuntu4.13\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"libxml2\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.9.1+dfsg1-3ubuntu4.7\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-1838\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"The xmlPArserPrintFileContextInternal function in libxml2 before 2.9.4, as used in Apple iOS before 9.3.2, OS X before 10.11.5, tvOS before 9.2.1, and watchOS before 2.2.1, allows remote attackers to cause a denial of service (heap-based buffer over-read) via a crafted XML document.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-1838\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2.9.1+dfsg1-3ubuntu4.8\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"curl\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"7.35.0-1ubuntu2.6\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2017-1000254\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"libcurl may read outside of a heap allocated buffer when doing FTP. When libcurl connects to an FTP server and successfully logs in (anonymous or not), it asks the server for the current directory with the `PWD` command. The server then responds with a 257 response containing the path, inside double quotes. The returned path name is then kept by libcurl for subsequent uses. Due to a flaw in the string parser for this directory name, a directory name passed like this but without a closing double quote would lead to libcurl not adding a trailing NUL byte to the buffer holding the name. When libcurl would then later access the string, it could read beyond the allocated heap buffer and crash or wrongly access data beyond the buffer, thinking it was part of the path. A malicious server could abuse this fact and effectively prevent libcurl-based clients to work with it - the PWD command is always issued on new FTP connections and the mistake has a high chance of causing a segfault. The simple fact that this has issue remained undiscovered for this long could suggest that malformed PWD responses are rare in benign servers. We are not aware of any exploit of this flaw. This bug was introduced in commit [415d2e7cb7](https://github.com/curl/curl/commit/415d2e7cb7), March 2005. In libcurl version 7.56.0, the parser always zero terminates the string but also rejects it if not terminated properly with a final double quote.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2017-1000254\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"7.35.0-1ubuntu2.11\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"curl\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"7.35.0-1ubuntu2.6\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2018-1000122\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"A buffer over-read exists in curl 7.20.0 to and including curl 7.58.0 in the RTSP+RTP handling code that allows an attacker to cause a denial of service or information leakage\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2018-1000122\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"7.35.0-1ubuntu2.15\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"libxml2\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.9.1+dfsg1-3ubuntu4.7\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-1762\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"The xmlNextChar function in libxml2 before 2.9.4 allows remote attackers to cause a denial of service (heap-based buffer over-read) via a crafted XML document.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-1762\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2.9.1+dfsg1-3ubuntu4.8\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"libxml2\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.9.1+dfsg1-3ubuntu4.7\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2017-9048\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"libxml2 20904-GITv2.9.4-16-g0741801 is vulnerable to a stack-based buffer overflow. The function xmlSnprintfElementContent in valid.c is supposed to recursively dump the element content definition into a char buffer 'buf' of size 'size'. At the end of the routine, the function may strcat two more characters without checking whether the current strlen(buf) + 2 \\u003c size. This vulnerability causes programs that use libxml2, such as PHP, to crash.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2017-9048\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2.9.1+dfsg1-3ubuntu4.10\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"curl\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"7.35.0-1ubuntu2.6\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2019-5436\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"A heap buffer overflow in the TFTP receiving code allows for DoS or arbitrary code execution in libcurl versions 7.19.4 through 7.64.1.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2019-5436\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"7.35.0-1ubuntu2.20+esm2\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"libxml2\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.9.1+dfsg1-3ubuntu4.7\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-4658\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"xpointer.c in libxml2 before 2.9.5 (as used in Apple iOS before 10, OS X before 10.12, tvOS before 10, and watchOS before 3, and other products) does not forbid namespace nodes in XPointer ranges, which allows remote attackers to execute arbitrary code or cause a denial of service (use-after-free and memory corruption) via a crafted XML document.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-4658\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2.9.1+dfsg1-3ubuntu4.9\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"libxml2\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.9.1+dfsg1-3ubuntu4.7\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-1839\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"The xmlDictAddString function in libxml2 before 2.9.4, as used in Apple iOS before 9.3.2, OS X before 10.11.5, tvOS before 9.2.1, and watchOS before 2.2.1, allows remote attackers to cause a denial of service (heap-based buffer over-read) via a crafted XML document.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-1839\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2.9.1+dfsg1-3ubuntu4.8\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"libxml2\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.9.1+dfsg1-3ubuntu4.7\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2017-9049\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"libxml2 20904-GITv2.9.4-16-g0741801 is vulnerable to a heap-based buffer over-read in the xmlDictComputeFastKey function in dict.c. This vulnerability causes programs that use libxml2, such as PHP, to crash. This vulnerability exists because of an incomplete fix for libxml2 Bug 759398.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2017-9049\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2.9.1+dfsg1-3ubuntu4.10\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"curl\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"7.35.0-1ubuntu2.6\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-5419\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"curl and libcurl before 7.50.1 do not prevent TLS session resumption when the client certificate has changed, which allows remote attackers to bypass intended restrictions by resuming a session.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-5419\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"7.35.0-1ubuntu2.8\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"libxml2\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.9.1+dfsg1-3ubuntu4.7\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2017-0663\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"A remote code execution vulnerability in libxml2 could enable an attacker using a specially crafted file to execute arbitrary code within the context of an unprivileged process. This issue is rated as High due to the possibility of remote code execution in an application that uses this library. Product: Android. Versions: 4.4.4, 5.0.2, 5.1.1, 6.0, 6.0.1, 7.0, 7.1.1, 7.1.2. Android ID: A-37104170.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2017-0663\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2.9.1+dfsg1-3ubuntu4.10\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"curl\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"7.35.0-1ubuntu2.6\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-8619\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"The function `read_data()` in security.c in curl before version 7.51.0 is vulnerable to memory double free.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-8619\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"7.35.0-1ubuntu2.10\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"libxml2\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.9.1+dfsg1-3ubuntu4.7\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-1833\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"The htmlCurrentChar function in libxml2 before 2.9.4, as used in Apple iOS before 9.3.2, OS X before 10.11.5, tvOS before 9.2.1, and watchOS before 2.2.1, allows remote attackers to cause a denial of service (heap-based buffer over-read) via a crafted XML document.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-1833\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2.9.1+dfsg1-3ubuntu4.8\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"curl\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"7.35.0-1ubuntu2.6\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-8624\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"curl before version 7.51.0 doesn't parse the authority component of the URL correctly when the host name part ends with a '#' character, and could instead be tricked into connecting to a different host. This may have security implications if you for example use an URL parser that follows the RFC to check for allowed domains before using curl to request them.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-8624\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"7.35.0-1ubuntu2.10\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"curl\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"7.35.0-1ubuntu2.6\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-8617\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"The base64 encode function in curl before version 7.51.0 is prone to a buffer being under allocated in 32bit systems if it receives at least 1Gb as input via `CURLOPT_USERNAME`.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-8617\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"7.35.0-1ubuntu2.10\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"curl\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"7.35.0-1ubuntu2.6\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2018-16842\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Curl versions 7.14.1 through 7.61.1 are vulnerable to a heap-based buffer over-read in the tool_msgs.c:voutf() function that may result in information exposure and denial of service.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2018-16842\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"7.35.0-1ubuntu2.19\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"libxml2\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.9.1+dfsg1-3ubuntu4.7\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2017-7375\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"A flaw in libxml2 allows remote XML entity inclusion with default parser flags (i.e., when the caller did not request entity substitution, DTD validation, external DTD subset loading, or default DTD attributes). Depending on the context, this may expose a higher-risk attack surface in libxml2 not usually reachable with default parser flags, and expose content from local files, HTTP, or FTP servers (which might be otherwise unreachable).\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2017-7375\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2.9.1+dfsg1-3ubuntu4.10\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"curl\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"7.35.0-1ubuntu2.6\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-5420\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"curl and libcurl before 7.50.1 do not check the client certificate when choosing the TLS connection to reuse, which might allow remote attackers to hijack the authentication of the connection by leveraging a previously created connection with a different client certificate.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-5420\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"7.35.0-1ubuntu2.8\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"libxml2\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.9.1+dfsg1-3ubuntu4.7\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2017-9050\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"libxml2 20904-GITv2.9.4-16-g0741801 is vulnerable to a heap-based buffer over-read in the xmlDictAddString function in dict.c. This vulnerability causes programs that use libxml2, such as PHP, to crash. This vulnerability exists because of an incomplete fix for CVE-2016-1839.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2017-9050\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2.9.1+dfsg1-3ubuntu4.10\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"libxml2\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.9.1+dfsg1-3ubuntu4.7\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-5131\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Use-after-free vulnerability in libxml2 through 2.9.4, as used in Google Chrome before 52.0.2743.82, allows remote attackers to cause a denial of service or possibly have unspecified other impact via vectors related to the XPointer range-to function.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-5131\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2.9.1+dfsg1-3ubuntu4.9\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"curl\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"7.35.0-1ubuntu2.6\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-8620\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"The 'globbing' feature in curl before version 7.51.0 has a flaw that leads to integer overflow and out-of-bounds read via user controlled input.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-8620\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"7.35.0-1ubuntu2.10\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"libxml2\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.9.1+dfsg1-3ubuntu4.7\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2017-15412\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Use after free in libxml2 before 2.9.5, as used in Google Chrome prior to 63.0.3239.84 and other products, allowed a remote attacker to potentially exploit heap corruption via a crafted HTML page.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2017-15412\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2.9.1+dfsg1-3ubuntu4.12\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"libxml2\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.9.1+dfsg1-3ubuntu4.7\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-1835\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Use-after-free vulnerability in the xmlSAX2AttributeNs function in libxml2 before 2.9.4, as used in Apple iOS before 9.3.2 and OS X before 10.11.5, allows remote attackers to cause a denial of service via a crafted XML document.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-1835\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2.9.1+dfsg1-3ubuntu4.8\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"curl\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"7.35.0-1ubuntu2.6\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-8622\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"The URL percent-encoding decode function in libcurl before 7.51.0 is called `curl_easy_unescape`. Internally, even if this function would be made to allocate a unscape destination buffer larger than 2GB, it would return that new length in a signed 32 bit integer variable, thus the length would get either just truncated or both truncated and turned negative. That could then lead to libcurl writing outside of its heap based buffer.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-8622\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"7.35.0-1ubuntu2.10\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"libxml2\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.9.1+dfsg1-3ubuntu4.7\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2018-14567\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"libxml2 2.9.8, if --with-lzma is used, allows remote attackers to cause a denial of service (infinite loop) via a crafted XML file that triggers LZMA_MEMLIMIT_ERROR, as demonstrated by xmllint, a different vulnerability than CVE-2015-8035 and CVE-2018-9251.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2018-14567\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2.9.1+dfsg1-3ubuntu4.13\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"libxml2\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.9.1+dfsg1-3ubuntu4.7\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-1837\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Multiple use-after-free vulnerabilities in the (1) htmlPArsePubidLiteral and (2) htmlParseSystemiteral functions in libxml2 before 2.9.4, as used in Apple iOS before 9.3.2, OS X before 10.11.5, tvOS before 9.2.1, and watchOS before 2.2.1, allow remote attackers to cause a denial of service via a crafted XML document.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-1837\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2.9.1+dfsg1-3ubuntu4.8\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"libxml2\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.9.1+dfsg1-3ubuntu4.7\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-1840\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Heap-based buffer overflow in the xmlFAParsePosCharGroup function in libxml2 before 2.9.4, as used in Apple iOS before 9.3.2, OS X before 10.11.5, tvOS before 9.2.1, and watchOS before 2.2.1, allows remote attackers to execute arbitrary code or cause a denial of service (memory corruption) via a crafted XML document.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-1840\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2.9.1+dfsg1-3ubuntu4.8\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"libxml2\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.9.1+dfsg1-3ubuntu4.7\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2017-7376\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Buffer overflow in libxml2 allows remote attackers to execute arbitrary code by leveraging an incorrect limit for port values when handling redirects.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2017-7376\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2.9.1+dfsg1-3ubuntu4.10\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"curl\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"7.35.0-1ubuntu2.6\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2018-1000120\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"A buffer overflow exists in curl 7.12.3 to and including curl 7.58.0 in the FTP URL handling that allows an attacker to cause a denial of service or worse.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2018-1000120\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"7.35.0-1ubuntu2.15\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"curl\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"7.35.0-1ubuntu2.6\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2019-5482\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Heap buffer overflow in the TFTP protocol handler in cURL 7.19.4 to 7.65.3.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2019-5482\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"7.35.0-1ubuntu2.20+esm3\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"curl\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"7.35.0-1ubuntu2.6\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-8623\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"A flaw was found in curl before version 7.51.0. The way curl handles cookies permits other threads to trigger a use-after-free leading to information disclosure.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-8623\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"7.35.0-1ubuntu2.10\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"libxml2\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.9.1+dfsg1-3ubuntu4.7\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-1836\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Use-after-free vulnerability in the xmlDictComputeFastKey function in libxml2 before 2.9.4, as used in Apple iOS before 9.3.2, OS X before 10.11.5, tvOS before 9.2.1, and watchOS before 2.2.1, allows remote attackers to cause a denial of service via a crafted XML document.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-1836\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2.9.1+dfsg1-3ubuntu4.8\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"libxml2\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.9.1+dfsg1-3ubuntu4.7\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2017-9047\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"A buffer overflow was discovered in libxml2 20904-GITv2.9.4-16-g0741801. The function xmlSnprintfElementContent in valid.c is supposed to recursively dump the element content definition into a char buffer 'buf' of size 'size'. The variable len is assigned strlen(buf). If the content-\\u003etype is XML_ELEMENT_CONTENT_ELEMENT, then (i) the content-\\u003eprefix is appended to buf (if it actually fits) whereupon (ii) content-\\u003ename is written to the buffer. However, the check for whether the content-\\u003ename actually fits also uses 'len' rather than the updated buffer length strlen(buf). This allows us to write about \\\"size\\\" many bytes beyond the allocated memory. This vulnerability causes programs that use libxml2, such as PHP, to crash.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2017-9047\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2.9.1+dfsg1-3ubuntu4.10\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"curl\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"7.35.0-1ubuntu2.6\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2018-14618\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"curl before version 7.61.1 is vulnerable to a buffer overrun in the NTLM authentication code. The internal function Curl_ntlm_core_mk_nt_hash multiplies the length of the password by two (SUM) to figure out how large temporary storage area to allocate from the heap. The length value is then subsequently used to iterate over the password and generate output into the allocated storage buffer. On systems with a 32 bit size_t, the math to calculate SUM triggers an integer overflow when the password length exceeds 2GB (2^31 bytes). This integer overflow usually causes a very small buffer to actually get allocated instead of the intended very huge one, making the use of that buffer end up in a heap buffer overflow. (This bug is almost identical to CVE-2017-8816.)\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2018-14618\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"7.35.0-1ubuntu2.17\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"curl\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"7.35.0-1ubuntu2.6\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-5421\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Use-after-free vulnerability in libcurl before 7.50.1 allows attackers to control which connection is used or possibly have unspecified other impact via unknown vectors.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-5421\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"7.35.0-1ubuntu2.8\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"rtmpdump\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.4+20121230.gitdf6c518-1\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2015-8272\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"RTMPDump 2.4 allows remote attackers to trigger a denial of service (NULL pointer dereference and process crash).\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2015-8272\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2.4+20121230.gitdf6c518-1ubuntu0.1\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"rtmpdump\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.4+20121230.gitdf6c518-1\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2015-8271\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"The AMF3CD_AddProp function in amf.c in RTMPDump 2.4 allows remote RTMP Media servers to execute arbitrary code.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2015-8271\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2.4+20121230.gitdf6c518-1ubuntu0.1\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"rtmpdump\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.4+20121230.gitdf6c518-1\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2015-8270\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"The AMF3ReadString function in amf.c in RTMPDump 2.4 allows remote RTMP Media servers to cause a denial of service (invalid pointer dereference and process crash).\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2015-8270\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2.4+20121230.gitdf6c518-1ubuntu0.1\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"cpio\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.11+dfsg-1ubuntu1.1\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-2037\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"The cpio_safer_name_suffix function in util.c in cpio 2.11 allows remote attackers to cause a denial of service (out-of-bounds write) via a crafted cpio file.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-2037\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2.11+dfsg-1ubuntu1.2\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"cpio\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.11+dfsg-1ubuntu1.1\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2019-14866\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"In all versions of cpio before 2.13 does not properly validate input files when generating TAR archives. When cpio is used to create TAR archives from paths an attacker can write to, the resulting archive may contain files with permissions the attacker did not have or in paths he did not have access to. Extracting those archives from a high-privilege user without carefully reviewing them may lead to the compromise of the system.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2019-14866\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2.11+dfsg-1ubuntu1.2+esm1\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"busybox\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1:1.21.0-1ubuntu1\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2017-16544\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"In the add_match function in libbb/lineedit.c in BusyBox through 1.27.2, the tab autocomplete feature of the shell, used to get a list of filenames in a directory, does not sanitize filenames and results in executing any escape sequence in the terminal. This could potentially result in code execution, arbitrary file writes, or other attacks.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2017-16544\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"1:1.21.0-1ubuntu1.4\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"busybox\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1:1.21.0-1ubuntu1\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2019-5747\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"An issue was discovered in BusyBox through 1.30.0. An out of bounds read in udhcp components (consumed by the DHCP server, client, and/or relay) might allow a remote attacker to leak sensitive information from the stack by sending a crafted DHCP message. This is related to assurance of a 4-byte length when decoding DHCP_SUBNET. NOTE: this issue exists because of an incomplete fix for CVE-2018-20679.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2019-5747\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"1:1.21.0-1ubuntu1.4\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"busybox\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1:1.21.0-1ubuntu1\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2018-1000517\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"BusyBox project BusyBox wget version prior to commit 8e2174e9bd836e53c8b9c6e00d1bc6e2a718686e contains a Buffer Overflow vulnerability in Busybox wget that can result in heap buffer overflow. This attack appear to be exploitable via network connectivity. This vulnerability appears to have been fixed in after commit 8e2174e9bd836e53c8b9c6e00d1bc6e2a718686e.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2018-1000517\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"1:1.21.0-1ubuntu1.4\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"busybox\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1:1.21.0-1ubuntu1\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2015-9261\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"huft_build in archival/libarchive/decompress_gunzip.c in BusyBox before 1.27.2 misuses a pointer, causing segfaults and an application crash during an unzip operation on a specially crafted ZIP file.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2015-9261\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"1:1.21.0-1ubuntu1.4\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"tiff\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"4.0.3-7ubuntu0.4\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-3990\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Heap-based buffer overflow in the horizontalDifference8 function in tif_pixarlog.c in LibTIFF 4.0.6 and earlier allows remote attackers to cause a denial of service (crash) or execute arbitrary code via a crafted TIFF image to tiffcp.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-3990\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"4.0.3-7ubuntu0.6\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"tiff\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"4.0.3-7ubuntu0.4\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-9453\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"The t2p_readwrite_pdf_image_tile function in LibTIFF allows remote attackers to cause a denial of service (out-of-bounds write and crash) or possibly execute arbitrary code via a JPEG file with a TIFFTAG_JPEGTABLES of length one.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-9453\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"4.0.3-7ubuntu0.6\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"tiff\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"4.0.3-7ubuntu0.4\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2017-7597\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"tif_dirread.c in LibTIFF 4.0.7 has an \\\"outside the range of representable values of type float\\\" undefined behavior issue, which might allow remote attackers to cause a denial of service (application crash) or possibly have unspecified other impact via a crafted image.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2017-7597\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"4.0.3-7ubuntu0.8\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"tiff\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"4.0.3-7ubuntu0.4\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-5314\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Buffer overflow in the PixarLogDecode function in tif_pixarlog.c in LibTIFF 4.0.6 and earlier allows remote attackers to cause a denial of service (application crash) or possibly have unspecified other impact via a crafted TIFF image, as demonstrated by overwriting the vgetparent function pointer with rgb2ycbcr.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-5314\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"4.0.3-7ubuntu0.6\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"tiff\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"4.0.3-7ubuntu0.4\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2017-7601\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"LibTIFF 4.0.7 has a \\\"shift exponent too large for 64-bit type long\\\" undefined behavior issue, which might allow remote attackers to cause a denial of service (application crash) or possibly have unspecified other impact via a crafted image.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2017-7601\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"4.0.3-7ubuntu0.8\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"p11-kit\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"0.20.2-2ubuntu2\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2020-29362\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"An issue was discovered in p11-kit 0.21.1 through 0.23.21. A heap-based buffer over-read has been discovered in the RPC protocol used by thep11-kit server/remote commands and the client library. When the remote entity supplies a byte array through a serialized PKCS#11 function call, the receiving entity may allow the reading of up to 4 bytes of memory past the heap allocation.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2020-29362\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"p11-kit\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"0.20.2-2ubuntu2\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2020-29361\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"An issue was discovered in p11-kit 0.21.1 through 0.23.21. Multiple integer overflows have been discovered in the array allocations in the p11-kit library and the p11-kit list command, where overflow checks are missing before calling realloc or calloc.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2020-29361\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"0.20.2-2ubuntu2+esm1\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"tiff\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"4.0.3-7ubuntu0.4\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2018-17101\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"An issue was discovered in LibTIFF 4.0.9. There are two out-of-bounds writes in cpTags in tools/tiff2bw.c and tools/pal2rgb.c, which can cause a denial of service (application crash) or possibly have unspecified other impact via a crafted image file.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2018-17101\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"4.0.3-7ubuntu0.10\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"libdbd-mysql-perl\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"4.025-1\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2015-8949\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Use-after-free vulnerability in the my_login function in DBD::mysql before 4.033_01 allows attackers to have unspecified impact by leveraging a call to mysql_errno after a failure of my_login.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2015-8949\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"4.025-1ubuntu0.1\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"php5\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"5.5.9+dfsg-1ubuntu4.20\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2019-11042\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"When PHP EXIF extension is parsing EXIF information from an image, e.g. via exif_read_data() function, in PHP versions 7.1.x below 7.1.31, 7.2.x below 7.2.21 and 7.3.x below 7.3.8 it is possible to supply it with data what will cause it to read past the allocated buffer. This may lead to information disclosure or crash.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2019-11042\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"5.5.9+dfsg-1ubuntu4.29+esm5\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"libdbd-mysql-perl\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"4.025-1\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-1246\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Buffer overflow in the DBD::mysql module before 4.037 for Perl allows context-dependent attackers to cause a denial of service (crash) via vectors related to an