libffi is used by a number of other libraries. It was previously stated that this affects libffi version 3.2.1 but this appears to be incorrect. libffi prior to version 3.1 on 32 bit x86 systems was vulnerable, and upstream is believed to have fixed this issue in version 3.1.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2017-1000376\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"3.1~rc1+r3.0.13-12ubuntu0.2\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"tiff\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"4.0.3-7ubuntu0.4\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2017-9935\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"In LibTIFF 4.0.8, there is a heap-based buffer overflow in the t2p_write_pdf function in tools/tiff2pdf.c. This heap overflow could lead to different damages. For example, a crafted TIFF document can lead to an out-of-bounds read in TIFFCleanup, an invalid free in TIFFClose or t2p_free, memory corruption in t2p_readwrite_pdf_image, or a double free in t2p_free. Given these possibilities, it probably could cause arbitrary code execution.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2017-9935\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"4.0.3-7ubuntu0.9\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"tiff\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"4.0.3-7ubuntu0.4\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2018-16335\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"newoffsets handling in ChopUpSingleUncompressedStrip in tif_dirread.c in LibTIFF 4.0.9 allows remote attackers to cause a denial of service (heap-based buffer overflow and application crash) or possibly have unspecified other impact via a crafted TIFF file, as demonstrated by tiff2pdf. This is a different vulnerability than CVE-2018-15209.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2018-16335\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"4.0.3-7ubuntu0.9\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"tiff\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"4.0.3-7ubuntu0.4\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-3632\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"The _TIFFVGetField function in tif_dirinfo.c in LibTIFF 4.0.6 and earlier allows remote attackers to cause a denial of service (out-of-bounds write) or execute arbitrary code via a crafted TIFF image.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-3632\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"4.0.3-7ubuntu0.6\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"vim\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2:7.4.052-1ubuntu3\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-1248\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"vim before patch 8.0.0056 does not properly validate values for the 'filetype', 'syntax' and 'keymap' options, which may result in the execution of arbitrary code if a file with a specially crafted modeline is opened.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-1248\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2:7.4.052-1ubuntu3.1\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"tiff\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"4.0.3-7ubuntu0.4\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2018-18557\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"LibTIFF 3.9.3, 3.9.4, 3.9.5, 3.9.6, 3.9.7, 4.0.0alpha4, 4.0.0alpha5, 4.0.0alpha6, 4.0.0beta7, 4.0.0, 4.0.1, 4.0.2, 4.0.3, 4.0.4, 4.0.4beta, 4.0.5, 4.0.6, 4.0.7, 4.0.8 and 4.0.9 (with JBIG enabled) decodes arbitrarily-sized JBIG into a buffer, ignoring the buffer size, which leads to a tif_jbig.c JBIGDecode out-of-bounds write.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2018-18557\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"4.0.3-7ubuntu0.10\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"tiff\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"4.0.3-7ubuntu0.4\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2017-9936\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"In LibTIFF 4.0.8, there is a memory leak in tif_jbig.c. A crafted TIFF document can lead to a memory leak resulting in a remote denial of service attack.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2017-9936\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"4.0.3-7ubuntu0.8\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"tiff\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"4.0.3-7ubuntu0.4\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-10271\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"tools/tiffcrop.c in LibTIFF 4.0.7 allows remote attackers to cause a denial of service (heap-based buffer over-read and buffer overflow) or possibly have unspecified other impact via a crafted TIFF image, related to \\\"READ of size 1\\\" and libtiff/tif_fax3.c:413:13.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-10271\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"4.0.3-7ubuntu0.6\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"tiff\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"4.0.3-7ubuntu0.4\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-3624\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"The cvtClump function in the rgb2ycbcr tool in LibTIFF 4.0.6 and earlier allows remote attackers to cause a denial of service (out-of-bounds write) by setting the \\\"-v\\\" option to -1.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-3624\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"4.0.3-7ubuntu0.6\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"tiff\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"4.0.3-7ubuntu0.4\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2017-7595\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"The JPEGSetupEncode function in tiff_jpeg.c in LibTIFF 4.0.7 allows remote attackers to cause a denial of service (divide-by-zero error and application crash) via a crafted image.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2017-7595\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"4.0.3-7ubuntu0.8\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"tiff\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"4.0.3-7ubuntu0.4\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-10094\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Off-by-one error in the t2p_readwrite_pdf_image_tile function in tools/tiff2pdf.c in LibTIFF 4.0.7 allows remote attackers to have unspecified impact via a crafted image.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-10094\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"4.0.3-7ubuntu0.6\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"openldap\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.4.31-1+nmu2ubuntu8.2\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2020-36224\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"A flaw was discovered in OpenLDAP before 2.4.57 leading to an invalid pointer free and slapd crash in the saslAuthzTo processing, resulting in denial of service.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2020-36224\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"openldap\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.4.31-1+nmu2ubuntu8.2\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2020-25692\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"A NULL pointer dereference was found in OpenLDAP server and was fixed in openldap 2.4.55, during a request for renaming RDNs. An unauthenticated attacker could remotely crash the slapd process by sending a specially crafted request, causing a Denial of Service.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2020-25692\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2.4.31-1+nmu2ubuntu8.5+esm3\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"openldap\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.4.31-1+nmu2ubuntu8.2\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2020-25710\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"assertion failure in CSN normalization with invalid input\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2020-25710\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2.4.31-1+nmu2ubuntu8.5+esm4\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"openldap\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.4.31-1+nmu2ubuntu8.2\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2020-36229\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"A flaw was discovered in ldap_X509dn2bv in OpenLDAP before 2.4.57 leading to a slapd crash in the X.509 DN parsing in ad_keystring, resulting in denial of service.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2020-36229\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"openldap\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.4.31-1+nmu2ubuntu8.2\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2020-36226\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"A flaw was discovered in OpenLDAP before 2.4.57 leading to a memch-\\u003ebv_len miscalculation and slapd crash in the saslAuthzTo processing, resulting in denial of service.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2020-36226\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"openldap\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.4.31-1+nmu2ubuntu8.2\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2019-13565\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"An issue was discovered in OpenLDAP 2.x before 2.4.48. When using SASL authentication and session encryption, and relying on the SASL security layers in slapd access controls, it is possible to obtain access that would otherwise be denied via a simple bind for any identity covered in those ACLs. After the first SASL bind is completed, the sasl_ssf value is retained for all new non-SASL connections. Depending on the ACL configuration, this can affect different types of operations (searches, modifications, etc.). In other words, a successful authorization step completed by one user affects the authorization requirement for a different user.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2019-13565\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2.4.31-1+nmu2ubuntu8.5+esm1\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"openldap\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.4.31-1+nmu2ubuntu8.2\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2020-25709\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"assertion failure in Certificate List syntax validation\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2020-25709\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2.4.31-1+nmu2ubuntu8.5+esm4\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"openldap\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.4.31-1+nmu2ubuntu8.2\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2021-27212\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"In OpenLDAP through 2.4.57 and 2.5.x through 2.5.1alpha, an assertion failure in slapd can occur in the issuerAndThisUpdateCheck function via a crafted packet, resulting in a denial of service (daemon exit) via a short timestamp. This is related to schema_init.c and checkTime.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2021-27212\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"openldap\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.4.31-1+nmu2ubuntu8.2\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2017-9287\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"servers/slapd/back-mdb/search.c in OpenLDAP through 2.4.44 is prone to a double free vulnerability. A user with access to search the directory can crash slapd by issuing a search including the Paged Results control with a page size of 0.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2017-9287\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2.4.31-1+nmu2ubuntu8.4\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"openldap\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.4.31-1+nmu2ubuntu8.2\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2020-36228\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"An integer underflow was discovered in OpenLDAP before 2.4.57 leading to a slapd crash in the Certificate List Exact Assertion processing, resulting in denial of service.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2020-36228\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"openldap\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.4.31-1+nmu2ubuntu8.2\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2020-36225\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"A flaw was discovered in OpenLDAP before 2.4.57 leading to a double free and slapd crash in the saslAuthzTo processing, resulting in denial of service.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2020-36225\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"openldap\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.4.31-1+nmu2ubuntu8.2\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2020-36230\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"A flaw was discovered in OpenLDAP before 2.4.57 leading in an assertion failure in slapd in the X.509 DN parsing in decode.c ber_next_element, resulting in denial of service.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2020-36230\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"openldap\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.4.31-1+nmu2ubuntu8.2\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2020-36227\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"A flaw was discovered in OpenLDAP before 2.4.57 leading to an infinite loop in slapd with the cancel_extop Cancel operation, resulting in denial of service.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2020-36227\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"openldap\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.4.31-1+nmu2ubuntu8.2\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2020-36221\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"An integer underflow was discovered in OpenLDAP before 2.4.57 leading to slapd crashes in the Certificate Exact Assertion processing, resulting in denial of service (schema_init.c serialNumberAndIssuerCheck).\",\n            \"link\": \"http:/