\"description\": \"An issue was discovered in the EXIF component in PHP before 7.1.27, 7.2.x before 7.2.16, and 7.3.x before 7.3.3. There is an Invalid Read in exif_process_SOFn.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2019-9640\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"5.5.9+dfsg-1ubuntu4.29\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"tiff\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"4.0.3-7ubuntu0.4\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2018-17100\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"An issue was discovered in LibTIFF 4.0.9. There is a int32 overflow in multiply_ms in tools/ppm2tiff.c, which can cause a denial of service (crash) or possibly have unspecified other impact via a crafted image file.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2018-17100\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"4.0.3-7ubuntu0.10\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"tiff\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"4.0.3-7ubuntu0.4\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-5322\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"The setByteArray function in tif_dir.c in libtiff 4.0.6 and earlier allows remote attackers to cause a denial of service (out-of-bounds read) via a crafted tiff image.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-5322\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"4.0.3-7ubuntu0.6\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"tiff\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"4.0.3-7ubuntu0.4\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-3945\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Multiple integer overflows in the (1) cvt_by_strip and (2) cvt_by_tile functions in the tiff2rgba tool in LibTIFF 4.0.6 and earlier, when -b mode is enabled