scovered in the EXIF component in PHP before 7.1.27, 7.2.x before 7.2.16, and 7.3.x before 7.3.3. There is an uninitialized read in exif_process_IFD_in_MAKERNOTE because of mishandling the data_len variable.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2019-9639\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"5.5.9+dfsg-1ubuntu4.29\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"php5\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"5.5.9+dfsg-1ubuntu4.20\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2019-11048\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"In PHP versions 7.2.x below 7.2.31, 7.3.x below 7.3.18 and 7.4.x below 7.4.6, when HTTP file uploads are allowed, supplying overly long filenames or field names could lead PHP engine to try to allocate oversized memory storage, hit the memory limit and stop processing the request, without cleaning up temporary files created by upload request. This potentially could lead to accumulation of uncleaned temporary files exhausting the disk space on the target server.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2019-11048\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"5.5.9+dfsg-1ubuntu4.29+esm12\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"php5\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"5.5.9+dfsg-1ubuntu4.20\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2017-9226\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"An issue was discovered in Oniguruma 6.2.0, as used in Oniguruma-mod in Ruby through 2.4.1 and mbstring in PHP through 7.1.5. A heap out-of-bounds write or read occurs in next_state_val() during regular expression compilation. Octal numbers larger than 0xff are not handled correctly in fetch_token() and fetch_token_in_cc(). A malformed regular expression containing an octal number in the form of '\\\\700' would produce an invalid code point value larger than 0xff in next_state_val(), resulting in an out-of-bounds write memory corruption.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2017-9226\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"5.5.9+dfsg-1ubuntu4.22\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"php5\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"5.5.9+dfsg-1ubuntu4.20\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2018-10545\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"An issue was discovered in PHP before 5.6.35, 7.0.x before 7.0.29, 7.1.x before 7.1.16, and 7.2.x before 7.2.4. Dumpable FPM child processes allow bypassing opcache access controls because fpm_unix.c makes a PR_SET_DUMPABLE prctl call, allowing one user (in a multiuser environment) to obtain sensitive information from the process memory of a second user's PHP applications by running gcore on the PID of the PHP-FPM worker process.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2018-10545\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"5.5.9+dfsg-1ubuntu4.25\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"php5\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"5.5.9+dfsg-1ubuntu4.20\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-9934\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"ext/wddx/wddx.c in PHP before 5.6.28 and 7.x before 7.0.13 allows remote attackers to cause a denial of service (NULL pointer dereference) via crafted serialized data in a wddxPacket XML document, as demonstrated by a PDORow string.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-9934\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"5.5.9+dfsg-1ubuntu4.21\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"php5\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"5.5.9+dfsg-1ubuntu4.20\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2017-11144\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"In PHP before 5.6.31, 7.x before 7.0.21, and 7.1.x before 7.1.7, the openssl extension PEM sealing code did not check the return value of the OpenSSL sealing function, which could lead to a crash of the PHP interpreter, related to an interpretation conflict for a negative number in ext/openssl/openssl.c, and an OpenSSL documentation omission.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2017-11144\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"5.5.9+dfsg-1ubuntu4.22\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"tiff\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"4.0.3-7ubuntu0.4\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-5316\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Out-of-bounds read in the PixarLogCleanup function in tif_pixarlog.c in libtiff 4.0.6 and earlier allows remote attackers to crash the application by sending a crafted TIFF image to the rgb2ycbcr tool.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-5316\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"4.0.3-7ubuntu0.6\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"tiff\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"4.0.3-7ubuntu0.4\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2015-7554\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"The _TIFFVGetField function in tif_dir.c in libtiff 4.0.6 allows attackers to cause a denial of service (invalid memory write and crash) or possibly have unspecified other impact via crafted field data in an extension tag in a TIFF image.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2015-7554\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"4.0.3-7ubuntu0.6\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"tiff\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"4.0.3-7ubuntu0.4\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-3186\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Buffer overflow in the readextension function in gif2tiff.c in LibTIFF 4.0.6 allows remote attackers to cause a denial of service (application crash) via a crafted GIF file.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-3186\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"4.0.3-7ubuntu0.9\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"php5\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"5.5.9+dfsg-1ubuntu4.20\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2018-10547\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"An issue was discovered in ext/phar/phar_object.c in PHP before 5.6.36, 7.0.x before 7.0.30, 7.1.x before 7.1.17, and 7.2.x before 7.2.5. There is Reflected XSS on the PHAR 403 and 404 error pages via request data of a request for a .phar file. NOTE: this vulnerability exists because of an incomplete fix for CVE-2018-5712.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2018-10547\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"5.5.9+dfsg-1ubuntu4.25\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"php5\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"5.5.9+dfsg-1ubuntu4.20\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2019-11040\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"When PHP EXIF extension is parsing EXIF information from an image, e.g. via exif_read_data() function, in PHP versions 7.1.x below 7.1.30, 7.2.x below 7.2.19 and 7.3.x below 7.3.6 it is possible to supply it with data what will cause it to read past the allocated buffer. This may lead to information disclosure or crash.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2019-11040\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"5.5.9+dfsg-1ubuntu4.29+esm3\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"tiff\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"4.0.3-7ubuntu0.4\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2017-7602\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"LibTIFF 4.0.7 has a signed integer overflow, which might allow remote attackers to cause a denial of service (application crash) or possibly have unspecified other impact via a crafted image.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2017-7602\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"4.0.3-7ubuntu0.8\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"php5\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"5.5.9+dfsg-1ubuntu4.20\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2017-11143\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"In PHP before 5.6.31, an invalid free in the WDDX deserialization of boolean parameters could be used by attackers able to inject XML for deserialization to crash the PHP interpreter, related to an invalid free for an empty boolean element in ext/wddx/wddx.c.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2017-11143\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"5.5.9+dfsg-1ubuntu4.22\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"php5\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"5.5.9+dfsg-1ubuntu4.20\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2019-11041\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"When PHP EXIF extension is parsing EXIF information from an image, e.g. via exif_read_data() function, in PHP versions 7.1.x below 7.1.31, 7.2.x below 7.2.21 and 7.3.x below 7.3.8 it is possible to supply it with data what will cause it to read past the allocated buffer. This may lead to information disclosure or crash.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2019-11041\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"5.5.9+dfsg-1ubuntu4.29+esm5\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"tiff\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"4.0.3-7ubuntu0.4\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2017-7593\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"tif_read.c in LibTIFF 4.0.7 does not ensure that tif_rawdata is properly initialized, which might allow remote attackers to obtain sensitive information from process memory via a crafted image.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2017-7593\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"4.0.3-7ubuntu0.8\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"php5\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"5.5.9+dfsg-1ubuntu4.20\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2019-11035\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"When processing certain files, PHP EXIF extension in versions 7.1.x below 7.1.28, 7.2.x below 7.2.17 and 7.3.x below 7.3.4 can be caused to read past allocated buffer in exif_iif_add_value function. This may lead to information disclosure or crash.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2019-11035\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"5.5.9+dfsg-1ubuntu4.29+esm1\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"php5\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"5.5.9+dfsg-1ubuntu4.20\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2018-14883\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"An issue was discovered in PHP before 5.6.37, 7.0.x before 7.0.31, 7.1.x before 7.1.20, and 7.2.x before 7.2.8. An Integer Overflow leads to a heap-based buffer over-read in exif_thumbnail_extract of exif.c.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2018-14883\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"5.5.9+dfsg-1ubuntu4.26\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"php5\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"5.5.9+dfsg-1ubuntu4.20\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2019-11039\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Function iconv_mime_decode_headers() in PHP versions 7.1.x below 7.1.30, 7.2.x below 7.2.19 and 7.3.x below 7.3.6 may perform out-of-buffer read due to integer overflow when parsing MIME headers. This may lead to information disclosure or crash.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2019-11039\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"5.5.9+dfsg-1ubuntu4.29+esm3\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"php5\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"5.5.9+dfsg-1ubuntu4.20\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2019-9020\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"An issue was discovered in PHP before 5.6.40, 7.x before 7.1.26, 7.2.x before 7.2.14, and 7.3.x before 7.3.1. Invalid input to the function xmlrpc_decode() can lead to an invalid memory access (heap out of bounds read or read after free). This is related to xml_elem_parse_buf in ext/xmlrpc/libxmlrpc/xml_element.c.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2019-9020\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"5.5.9+dfsg-1ubuntu4.27\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"php5\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"5.5.9+dfsg-1ubuntu4.20\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2017-9228\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"An issue was discovered in Oniguruma 6.2.0, as used in Oniguruma-mod in Ruby through 2.4.1 and mbstring in PHP through 7.1.5. A heap out-of-bounds write occurs in bitset_set_range() during regular expression compilation due to an uninitialized variable from an incorrect state transition. An incorrect state transition in parse_char_class() could create an execution path that leaves a critical local variable uninitialized until it's used as an index, resulting in an out-of-bounds write memory corruption.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2017-9228\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"5.5.9+dfsg-1ubuntu4.22\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"php5\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"5.5.9+dfsg-1ubuntu4.20\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2020-7066\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"In PHP versions 7.2.x below 7.2.29, 7.3.x below 7.3.16 and 7.4.x below 7.4.4, while using get_headers() with user-supplied URL, if the URL contains zero (\\\\0) character, the URL will be silently truncated at it. This may cause some software to make incorrect assumptions about the target of the get_headers() and possibly send some information to a wrong server.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2020-7066\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"5.5.9+dfsg-1ubuntu4.29+esm11\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"tiff\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"4.0.3-7ubuntu0.4\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-5315\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"The setByteArray function in tif_dir.c in libtiff 4.0.6 and earlier allows remote attackers to cause a denial of service (out-of-bounds read) via a crafted tiff image.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-5315\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"4.0.3-7ubuntu0.6\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"tiff\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"4.0.3-7ubuntu0.4\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-9535\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"tif_predict.h and tif_predict.c in libtiff 4.0.6 have assertions that can lead to assertion failures in debug mode, or buffer overflows in release mode, when dealing with unusual tile size like YCbCr with subsampling. Reported as MSVR 35105, aka \\\"Predictor heap-buffer-overflow.\\\"\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-9535\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"4.0.3-7ubuntu0.6\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"php5\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"5.5.9+dfsg-1ubuntu4.20\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-10160\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Off-by-one error in the phar_parse_pharfile function in ext/phar/phar.c in PHP before 5.6.30 and 7.0.x before 7.0.15 allows remote attackers to cause a denial of service (memory corruption) or possibly execute arbitrary code via a crafted PHAR archive with an alias mismatch.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-10160\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"5.5.9+dfsg-1ubuntu4.21\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"tiff\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"4.0.3-7ubuntu0.4\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2017-7596\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"LibTIFF 4.0.7 has an \\\"outside the range of representable values of type float\\\" undefined behavior issue, which might allow remote attackers to cause a denial of service (application crash) or possibly have unspecified other impact via a crafted image.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2017-7596\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"4.0.3-7ubuntu0.8\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"php5\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"5.5.9+dfsg-1ubuntu4.20\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2017-9118\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"PHP 7.1.5 has an Out of bounds access in php_pcre_replace_impl via a crafted preg_replace call.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2017-9118\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"tiff\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"4.0.3-7ubuntu0.4\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-10092\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Heap-based buffer overflow in the readContigStripsIntoBuffer function in tif_unix.c in LibTIFF 4.0.7, 3.9.3, 3.9.4, 3.9.5, 3.9.6, 3.9.7, 4.0.0alpha4, 4.0.0alpha5, 4.0.0alpha6, 4.0.0beta7, 4.0.0, 4.0.1, 4.0.2, 4.0.3, 4.0.4, 4.0.4beta, 4.0.5 and 4.0.6 allows remote attackers to have unspecified impact via a crafted image.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-10092\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"4.0.3-7ubuntu0.6\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"php5\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"5.5.9+dfsg-1ubuntu4.20\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2020-7064\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"In PHP versions 7.2.x below 7.2.9, 7.3.x below 7.3.16 and 7.4.x below 7.4.4, while parsing EXIF data with exif_read_data() function, it is possible for malicious data to cause PHP to read one byte of uninitialized memory. This could potentially lead to information disclosure or crash.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2020-7064\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"5.5.9+dfsg-1ubuntu4.29+esm11\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"php5\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"5.5.9+dfsg-1ubuntu4.20\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2019-9024\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"An issue was discovered in PHP before 5.6.40, 7.x before 7.1.26, 7.2.x before 7.2.14, and 7.3.x before 7.3.1. xmlrpc_decode() can allow a hostile XMLRPC server to cause PHP to read memory outside of allocated areas in base64_decode_xmlrpc in ext/xmlrpc/libxmlrpc/base64.c.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2019-9024\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"5.5.9+dfsg-1ubuntu4.27\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"php5\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"5.5.9+dfsg-1ubuntu4.20\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2018-17082\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"The Apache2 component in PHP before 5.6.38, 7.0.x before 7.0.32, 7.1.x before 7.1.22, and 7.2.x before 7.2.10 allows XSS via the body of a \\\"Transfer-Encoding: chunked\\\" request, because the bucket brigade is mishandled in the php_handler function in sapi/apache2handler/sapi_apache2.c.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2018-17082\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"5.5.9+dfsg-1ubuntu4.26\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"tiff\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"4.0.3-7ubuntu0.4\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2019-7663\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"An Invalid Address dereference was discovered in TIFFWriteDirectoryTagTransferfunction in libtiff/tif_dirwrite.c in LibTIFF 4.0.10, affecting the cpSeparateBufToContigBuf function in tiffcp.c. Remote attackers could leverage this vulnerability to cause a denial-of-service via a crafted tiff file. This is different from CVE-2018-12900.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2019-7663\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"4.0.3-7ubuntu0.11\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"php5\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"5.5.9+dfsg-1ubuntu4.20\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2019-9022\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"An issue was discovered in PHP 7.x before 7.1.26, 7.2.x before 7.2.14, and 7.3.x before 7.3.2. dns_get_record misparses a DNS response, which can allow a hostile DNS server to cause PHP to misuse memcpy, leading to read operations going past the buffer allocated for DNS data. This affects php_parserr in ext/standard/dns.c for DNS_CAA and DNS_ANY queries.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2019-9022\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"5.5.9+dfsg-1ubuntu4.29\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"php5\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"5.5.9+dfsg-1ubuntu4.20\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2017-9229\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"An issue was discovered in Oniguruma 6.2.0, as used in Oniguruma-mod in Ruby through 2.4.1 and mbstring in PHP through 7.1.5. A SIGSEGV occurs in left_adjust_char_head() during regular expression compilation. Invalid handling of reg-\\u003edmax in forward_search_range() could result in an invalid pointer dereference, normally as an immediate denial-of-service condition.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2017-9229\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"5.5.9+dfsg-1ubuntu4.22\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"php5\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"5.5.9+dfsg-1ubuntu4.20\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-9935\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"The php_wddx_push_element function in ext/wddx/wddx.c in PHP before 5.6.29 and 7.x before 7.0.14 allows remote attackers to cause a denial of service (out-of-bounds read and memory corruption) or possibly have unspecified other impact via an empty boolean element in a wddxPacket XML document.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-9935\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"5.5.9+dfsg-1ubuntu4.21\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"php5\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"5.5.9+dfsg-1ubuntu4.20\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2020-7070\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"In PHP versions 7.2.x below 7.2.34, 7.3.x below 7.3.23 and 7.4.x below 7.4.11, when PHP is processing incoming HTTP cookie values, the cookie names are url-decoded. This may lead to cookies with prefixes like __Host confused with cookies that decode to such prefix, thus leading to an attacker being able to forge cookie which is supposed to be secure. See also CVE-2020-8184 for more information.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2020-7070\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"5.5.9+dfsg-1ubuntu4.29+esm13\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"php5\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"5.5.9+dfsg-1ubuntu4.20\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2019-11043\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"In PHP versions 7.1.x below 7.1.33, 7.2.x below 7.2.24 and 7.3.x below 7.3.11 in certain configurations of FPM setup it is possible to cause FPM module to write past allocated buffers into the space reserved for FCGI protocol data, thus opening the possibility of remote code execution.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2019-11043\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"5.5.9+dfsg-1ubuntu4.29+esm6\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"php5\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"5.5.9+dfsg-1ubuntu4.20\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2017-9224\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"An issue was discovered in Oniguruma 6.2.0, as used in Oniguruma-mod in Ruby through 2.4.1 and mbstring in PHP through 7.1.5. A stack out-of-bounds read occurs in match_at() during regular expression searching. A logical error involving order of validation and access in match_at() could result in an out-of-bounds read from a stack buffer.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2017-9224\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"5.5.9+dfsg-1ubuntu4.22\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"php5\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"5.5.9+dfsg-1ubuntu4.20\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2018-5712\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"An issue was discovered in PHP before 5.6.33, 7.0.x before 7.0.27, 7.1.x before 7.1.13, and 7.2.x before 7.2.1. There is Reflected XSS on the PHAR 404 error page via the URI of a request for a .phar file.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2018-5712\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"5.5.9+dfsg-1ubuntu4.23\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"php5\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"5.5.9+dfsg-1ubuntu4.20\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2019-13224\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"A use-after-free in onig_new_deluxe() in regext.c in Oniguruma 6.9.2 allows attackers to potentially cause information disclosure, denial of service, or possibly code execution by providing a crafted regular expression. The attacker provides a pair of a regex pattern and a string, with a multi-byte encoding that gets handled by onig_new_deluxe(). Oniguruma issues often affect Ruby, as well as common optional libraries for PHP and Rust.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2019-13224\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"5.5.9+dfsg-1ubuntu4.29+esm4\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"tiff\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"4.0.3-7ubuntu0.4\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2017-7600\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"LibTIFF 4.0.7 has an \\\"outside the range of representable values of type unsigned char\\\" undefined behavior issue, which might allow remote attackers to cause a denial of service (application crash) or possibly have unspecified other impact via a crafted image.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2017-7600\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"4.0.3-7ubuntu0.8\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"php5\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"5.5.9+dfsg-1ubuntu4.20\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-7478\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Zend/zend_exceptions.c in PHP, possibly 5.x before 5.6.28 and 7.x before 7.0.13, allows remote attackers to cause a denial of service (infinite loop) via a crafted Exception object in serialized data, a related issue to CVE-2015-8876.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-7478\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"5.5.9+dfsg-1ubuntu4.21\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"php5\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"5.5.9+dfsg-1ubuntu4.20\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2017-11147\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"In PHP before 5.6.30 and 7.x before 7.0.15, the PHAR archive handler could be used by attackers supplying malicious archive files to crash the PHP interpreter or potentially disclose information due to a buffer over-read in the phar_parse_pharfile function in ext/phar/phar.c.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2017-11147\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"5.5.9+dfsg-1ubuntu4.22\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"php5\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"5.5.9+dfsg-1ubuntu4.20\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2020-7059\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"When using fgetss() function to read data with stripping tags, in PHP versions 7.2.x below 7.2.27, 7.3.x below 7.3.14 and 7.4.x below 7.4.2 it is possible to supply data that will cause this function to read past the allocated buffer. This may lead to information disclosure or crash.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2020-7059\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"5.5.9+dfsg-1ubuntu4.29+esm10\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"tiff\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"4.0.3-7ubuntu0.4\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-5317\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Buffer overflow in the PixarLogDecode function in libtiff.so in the PixarLogDecode function in libtiff 4.0.6 and earlier, as used in GNOME nautilus, allows attackers to cause a denial of service attack (crash) via a crafted TIFF file.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-5317\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"4.0.3-7ubuntu0.6\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"tiff\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"4.0.3-7ubuntu0.4\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2017-7594\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"The OJPEGReadHeaderInfoSecTablesDcTable function in tif_ojpeg.c in LibTIFF 4.0.7 allows remote attackers to cause a denial of service (memory leak) via a crafted image.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2017-7594\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"4.0.3-7ubuntu0.8\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"php5\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"5.5.9+dfsg-1ubuntu4.20\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2017-9120\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"PHP 7.x through 7.1.5 allows remote attackers to cause a denial of service (buffer overflow and application crash) or possibly have unspecified other impact via a long string because of an Integer overflow in mysqli_real_escape_string.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2017-9120\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"tiff\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"4.0.3-7ubuntu0.4\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-10093\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Integer overflow in tools/tiffcp.c in LibTIFF 4.0.7, 3.9.3, 3.9.4, 3.9.5, 3.9.6, 3.9.7, 4.0.0alpha4, 4.0.0alpha5, 4.0.0alpha6, 4.0.0beta7, 4.0.0, 4.0.1, 4.0.2, 4.0.3, 4.0.4, 4.0.4beta, 4.0.5 and 4.0.6 allows remote attackers to have unspecified impact via a crafted image, which triggers a heap-based buffer overflow.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-10093\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"4.0.3-7ubuntu0.6\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"php5\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"5.5.9+dfsg-1ubuntu4.20\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2020-7069\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"In PHP versions 7.2.x below 7.2.34, 7.3.x below 7.3.23 and 7.4.x below 7.4.11, when AES-CCM mode is used with openssl_encrypt() function with 12 bytes IV, only first 7 bytes of the IV is actually used. This can lead to both decreased security and incorrect encryption data.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2020-7069\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"5.5.9+dfsg-1ubuntu4.29+esm13\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"gcc-4.8\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"4.8.4-2ubuntu1~14.04\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2020-13844\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Arm Armv8-A core implementations utilizing speculative execution past unconditional changes in control flow may allow unauthorized disclosure of information to an attacker with local user access via a side-channel analysis, aka \\\"straight-line speculation.\\\"\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2020-13844\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"php5\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"5.5.9+dfsg-1ubuntu4.20\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-7479\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"In all versions of PHP 7, during the unserialization process, resizing the 'properties' hash table of a serialized object may lead to use-after-free. A remote attacker may exploit this bug to gain arbitrary code execution.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-7479\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"5.5.9+dfsg-1ubuntu4.21\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"perl\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"5.18.2-2ubuntu1\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2018-18311\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Perl before 5.26.3 and 5.28.x before 5.28.1 has a buffer overflow via a crafted regular expression that triggers invalid write operations.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2018-18311\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"5.18.2-2ubuntu1.7\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"expat\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.1.0-4ubuntu1.1\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-5300\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"The XML parser in Expat does not use sufficient entropy for hash initialization, which allows context-dependent attackers to cause a denial of service (CPU consumption) via crafted identifiers in an XML document. NOTE: this vulnerability exists because of an incomplete fix for CVE-2012-0876.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-5300\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2.1.0-4ubuntu1.3\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"sudo\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1.8.9p5-1ubuntu1.2\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-7076\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"sudo before version 1.8.18p1 is vulnerable to a bypass in the sudo noexec restriction if application run via sudo executed wordexp() C library function with a user supplied argument. A local user permitted to run such application via sudo with noexec restriction could possibly use this flaw to execute arbitrary commands with elevated privileges.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-7076\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"1.8.9p5-1ubuntu1.5+esm5\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"sudo\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1.8.9p5-1ubuntu1.2\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2019-14287\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"In Sudo before 1.8.28, an attacker with access to a Runas ALL sudoer account can bypass certain policy blacklists and session PAM modules, and can cause incorrect logging, by invoking sudo with a crafted user ID. For example, this allows bypass of !root configuration, and USER= logging, for a \\\"sudo -u \\\\#$((0xffffffff))\\\" command.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2019-14287\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"1.8.9p5-1ubuntu1.5+esm2\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"expat\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.1.0-4ubuntu1.1\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2017-9233\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"XML External Entity vulnerability in libexpat 2.2.0 and earlier (Expat XML Parser Library) allows attackers to put the parser in an infinite loop using a malformed external entity definition from an external DTD.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2017-9233\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2.1.0-4ubuntu1.4\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"php5\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"5.5.9+dfsg-1ubuntu4.20\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2019-9638\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"An issue was discovered in the EXIF component in PHP before 7.1.27, 7.2.x before 7.2.16, and 7.3.x before 7.3.3. There is an uninitialized read in exif_process_IFD_in_MAKERNOTE because of mishandling the maker_note-\\u003eoffset relationship to value_len.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2019-9638\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"5.5.9+dfsg-1ubuntu4.29\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"sudo\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1.8.9p5-1ubuntu1.2\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2017-1000368\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Todd Miller's sudo version 1.8.20p1 and earlier is vulnerable to an input validation (embedded newlines) in the get_process_ttyname() function resulting in information disclosure and command execution.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2017-1000368\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"1.8.9p5-1ubuntu1.5+esm1\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"libgd2\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.1.0-3ubuntu0.5\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2018-15879\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"** REJECT ** DO NOT USE THIS CANDIDATE NUMBER. ConsultIDs: CVE-2019-6978. Reason: This candidate is a reservation duplicate of CVE-2019-6978. Notes: All CVE users should reference CVE-2019-6978 instead of this candidate. All references and descriptions in this candidate have been removed to prevent accidental usage.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2018-15879\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2.1.0-3ubuntu0.10\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"libgd2\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.1.0-3ubuntu0.5\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2017-6362\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Double free vulnerability in the gdImagePngPtr function in libgd2 before 2.2.5 allows remote attackers to cause a denial of service via vectors related to a palette with no colors.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2017-6362\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2.1.0-3ubuntu0.8\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"php5\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"5.5.9+dfsg-1ubuntu4.20\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2017-11628\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"In PHP before 5.6.31, 7.x before 7.0.21, and 7.1.x before 7.1.7, a stack-based buffer overflow in the zend_ini_do_op() function in Zend/zend_ini_parser.c could cause a denial of service or potentially allow executing code. NOTE: this is only relevant for PHP applications that accept untrusted input (instead of the system's php.ini file) for the parse_ini_string or parse_ini_file function, e.g., a web application for syntax validation of php.ini directives.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2017-11628\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"5.5.9+dfsg-1ubuntu4.22\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"php5\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"5.5.9+dfsg-1ubuntu4.20\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2019-9021\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"An issue was discovered in PHP before 5.6.40, 7.x before 7.1.26, 7.2.x before 7.2.14, and 7.3.x before 7.3.1. A heap-based buffer over-read in PHAR reading functions in the PHAR extension may allow an attacker to read allocated or unallocated memory past the actual data when trying to parse the file name, a different vulnerability than CVE-2018-20783. This is related to phar_detect_phar_fname_ext in ext/phar/phar.c.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2019-9021\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"5.5.9+dfsg-1ubuntu4.27\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"php5\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"5.5.9+dfsg-1ubuntu4.20\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2017-9227\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"An issue was discovered in Oniguruma 6.2.0, as used in Oniguruma-mod in Ruby through 2.4.1 and mbstring in PHP through 7.1.5. A stack out-of-bounds read occurs in mbc_enc_len() during regular expression searching. Invalid handling of reg-\\u003edmin in forward_search_range() could result in an invalid pointer dereference, as an out-of-bounds read from a stack buffer.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2017-9227\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"5.5.9+dfsg-1ubuntu4.22\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"libgd2\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.1.0-3ubuntu0.5\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-10168\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Integer overflow in gd_io.c in the GD Graphics Library (aka libgd) before 2.2.4 allows remote attackers to have unspecified impact via vectors involving the number of horizontal and vertical chunks in an image.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-10168\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2.1.0-3ubuntu0.6\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"php5\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"5.5.9+dfsg-1ubuntu4.20\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2017-11145\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"In PHP before 5.6.31, 7.x before 7.0.21, and 7.1.x before 7.1.7, an error in the date extension's timelib_meridian parsing code could be used by attackers able to supply date strings to leak information from the interpreter, related to ext/date/lib/parse_date.c out-of-bounds reads affecting the php_parse_date function. NOTE: the correct fix is in the e8b7698f5ee757ce2c8bd10a192a491a498f891c commit, not the bd77ac90d3bdf31ce2a5251ad92e9e75 gist.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2017-11145\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"5.5.9+dfsg-1ubuntu4.22\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"php5\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"5.5.9+dfsg-1ubuntu4.20\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2019-11034\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"When processing certain files, PHP EXIF extension in versions 7.1.x below 7.1.28, 7.2.x below 7.2.17 and 7.3.x below 7.3.4 can be caused to read past allocated buffer in exif_process_IFD_TAG function. This may lead to information disclosure or crash.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2019-11034\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"5.5.9+dfsg-1ubuntu4.29+esm1\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"php5\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"5.5.9+dfsg-1ubuntu4.20\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2018-7584\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"In PHP through 5.6.33, 7.0.x before 7.0.28, 7.1.x through 7.1.14, and 7.2.x through 7.2.2, there is a stack-based buffer under-read while parsing an HTTP response in the php_stream_url_wrap_http_ex function in ext/standard/http_fopen_wrapper.c. This subsequently results in copying a large string.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2018-7584\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"5.5.9+dfsg-1ubuntu4.24\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"libgd2\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.1.0-3ubuntu0.5\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2018-15878\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"** REJECT ** DO NOT USE THIS CANDIDATE NUMBER. ConsultIDs: CVE-2019-6978. Reason: This candidate is a reservation duplicate of CVE-2019-6978. Notes: All CVE users should reference CVE-2019-6978 instead of this candidate. All references and descriptions in this candidate have been removed to prevent accidental usage.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2018-15878\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2.1.0-3ubuntu0.10\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"libgd2\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.1.0-3ubuntu0.5\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2018-1000222\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Libgd version 2.2.5 contains a Double Free Vulnerability vulnerability in gdImageBmpPtr Function that can result in Remote Code Execution . This attack appear to be exploitable via Specially Crafted Jpeg Image can trigger double free. This vulnerability appears to have been fixed in after commit ac16bdf2d41724b5a65255d4c28fb0ec46bc42f5.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2018-1000222\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2.1.0-3ubuntu0.10\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"libgd2\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.1.0-3ubuntu0.5\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-10166\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Integer underflow in the _gdContributionsAlloc function in gd_interpolation.c in the GD Graphics Library (aka libgd) before 2.2.4 allows remote attackers to have unspecified impact via vectors related to decrementing the u variable.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-10166\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2.1.0-3ubuntu0.6\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"libgd2\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.1.0-3ubuntu0.5\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2019-6977\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"gdImageColorMatch in gd_color_match.c in the GD Graphics Library (aka LibGD) 2.2.5, as used in the imagecolormatch function in PHP before 5.6.40, 7.x before 7.1.26, 7.2.x before 7.2.14, and 7.3.x before 7.3.1, has a heap-based buffer overflow. This can be exploited by an attacker who is able to trigger imagecolormatch calls with crafted image data.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2019-6977\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2.1.0-3ubuntu0.11\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"bash\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"4.3-7ubuntu1.5\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-7543\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Bash before 4.4 allows local users to execute arbitrary commands with root privileges via crafted SHELLOPTS and PS4 environment variables.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-7543\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"4.3-7ubuntu1.7\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"libtasn1-6\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"3.4-3ubuntu0.3\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-4008\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"The _asn1_extract_der_octet function in lib/decoding.c in GNU Libtasn1 before 4.8, when used without the ASN1_DECODE_FLAG_STRICT_DER flag, allows remote attackers to cause a denial of service (infinite recursion) via a crafted certificate.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-4008\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"3.4-3ubuntu0.4\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"libgd2\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.1.0-3ubuntu0.5\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2017-7890\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"The GIF decoding function gdImageCreateFromGifCtx in gd_gif_in.c in the GD Graphics Library (aka libgd), as used in PHP before 5.6.31 and 7.x before 7.1.7, does not zero colorMap arrays before use. A specially crafted GIF image could use the uninitialized tables to read ~700 bytes from the top of the stack, potentially disclosing sensitive information.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2017-7890\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2.1.0-3ubuntu0.7\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"libtasn1-6\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"3.4-3ubuntu0.3\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2017-6891\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Two errors in the \\\"asn1_find_node()\\\" function (lib/parser_aux.c) within GnuTLS libtasn1 version 4.10 can be exploited to cause a stacked-based buffer overflow by tricking a user into processing a specially crafted assignments file via the e.g. asn1Coding utility.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2017-6891\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"3.4-3ubuntu0.5\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"libgd2\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.1.0-3ubuntu0.5\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-10167\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"The gdImageCreateFromGd2Ctx function in gd_gd2.c in the GD Graphics Library (aka libgd) before 2.2.4 allows remote attackers to cause a denial of service (application crash) via a crafted image file.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-10167\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2.1.0-3ubuntu0.6\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"git\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1:1.9.1-1ubuntu0.2\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2017-1000117\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"A malicious third-party can give a crafted \\\"ssh://...\\\" URL to an unsuspecting victim, and an attempt to visit the URL can result in any program that exists on the victim's machine being executed. Such a URL could be placed in the .gitmodules file of a malicious project, and an unsuspecting victim could be tricked into running \\\"git clone --recurse-submodules\\\" to trigger the vulnerability.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2017-1000117\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"1:1.9.1-1ubuntu0.6\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"git\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1:1.9.1-1ubuntu0.2\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-2324\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Integer overflow in Git before 2.7.4 allows remote attackers to execute arbitrary code via a (1) long filename or (2) many nested trees, which triggers a heap-based buffer overflow.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-2324\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"1:1.9.1-1ubuntu0.3\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"libgd2\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.1.0-3ubuntu0.5\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-6912\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Double free vulnerability in the gdImageWebPtr function in the GD Graphics Library (aka libgd) before 2.2.4 allows remote attackers to have unspecified impact via large width and height values.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-6912\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2.1.0-3ubuntu0.6\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"cyrus-sasl2\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.1.25.dfsg1-17build1\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2019-19906\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"cyrus-sasl (aka Cyrus SASL) 2.1.27 has an out-of-bounds write leading to unauthenticated remote denial-of-service in OpenLDAP via a malformed LDAP packet. The OpenLDAP crash is ultimately caused by an off-by-one error in _sasl_add_string in common.c in cyrus-sasl.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2019-19906\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2.1.25.dfsg1-17ubuntu0.1~esm1\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"git\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1:1.9.1-1ubuntu0.2\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2018-17456\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Git before 2.14.5, 2.15.x before 2.15.3, 2.16.x before 2.16.5, 2.17.x before 2.17.2, 2.18.x before 2.18.1, and 2.19.x before 2.19.1 allows remote code execution during processing of a recursive \\\"git clone\\\" of a superproject if a .gitmodules file has a URL field beginning with a '-' character.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2018-17456\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"1:1.9.1-1ubuntu0.9\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"expat\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.1.0-4ubuntu1.1\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-0718\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Expat allows context-dependent attackers to cause a denial of service (crash) or possibly execute arbitrary code via a malformed input document, which triggers a buffer overflow.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-0718\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2.1.0-4ubuntu1.2\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"git\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1:1.9.1-1ubuntu0.2\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2017-14867\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Git before 2.10.5, 2.11.x before 2.11.4, 2.12.x before 2.12.5, 2.13.x before 2.13.6, and 2.14.x before 2.14.2 uses unsafe Perl scripts to support subcommands such as cvsserver, which allows attackers to execute arbitrary OS commands via shell metacharacters in a module name. The vulnerable code is reachable via git-shell even without CVS support.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2017-14867\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"1:1.9.1-1ubuntu0.7\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"git\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1:1.9.1-1ubuntu0.2\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2014-9938\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"contrib/completion/git-prompt.sh in Git before 1.9.3 does not sanitize branch names in the PS1 variable, allowing a malicious repository to cause code execution.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2014-9938\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"1:1.9.1-1ubuntu0.4\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"git\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1:1.9.1-1ubuntu0.2\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2017-8386\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"git-shell in git before 2.4.12, 2.5.x before 2.5.6, 2.6.x before 2.6.7, 2.7.x before 2.7.5, 2.8.x before 2.8.5, 2.9.x before 2.9.4, 2.10.x before 2.10.3, 2.11.x before 2.11.2, and 2.12.x before 2.12.3 might allow remote authenticated users to gain privileges via a repository name that starts with a - (dash) character.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2017-8386\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"1:1.9.1-1ubuntu0.5\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"expat\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.1.0-4ubuntu1.1\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2019-15903\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"In libexpat before 2.2.8, crafted XML input could fool the parser into changing from DTD parsing to document parsing too early; a consecutive call to XML_GetCurrentLineNumber (or XML_GetCurrentColumnNumber) then resulted in a heap-based buffer over-read.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2019-15903\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2.1.0-4ubuntu1.4+esm2\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"libgcrypt11\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1.5.3-2ubuntu4.2\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2017-7526\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"libgcrypt before version 1.7.8 is vulnerable to a cache side-channel attack resulting into a complete break of RSA-1024 while using the left-to-right method for computing the sliding-window expansion. The same attack is believed to work on RSA-2048 with moderately more computation. This side-channel requires that attacker can run arbitrary software on the hardware where the private RSA key is used.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2017-7526\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"1.5.3-2ubuntu4.5\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"bzip2\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1.0.6-5\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2019-12900\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"BZ2_decompress in decompress.c in bzip2 through 1.0.6 has an out-of-bounds write when there are many selectors.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2019-12900\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"1.0.6-5ubuntu0.1~esm2\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"e2fsprogs\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1.42.9-3ubuntu1.3\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2019-5094\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"An exploitable code execution vulnerability exists in the quota file functionality of E2fsprogs 1.45.3. A specially crafted ext4 partition can cause an out-of-bounds write on the heap, resulting in code execution. An attacker can corrupt a partition to trigger this vulnerability.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2019-5094\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"1.42.9-3ubuntu1.3+esm1\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"e2fsprogs\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1.42.9-3ubuntu1.3\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2019-5188\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"A code execution vulnerability exists in the directory rehashing functionality of E2fsprogs e2fsck 1.45.4. A specially crafted ext4 directory can cause an out-of-bounds write on the stack, resulting in code execution. An attacker can corrupt a partition to trigger this vulnerability.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2019-5188\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"1.42.9-3ubuntu1.3+esm2\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"apt\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1.0.1ubuntu2.10\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2020-3810\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Missing input validation in the ar/tar implementations of APT before version 2.1.2 could result in denial of service when processing specially crafted deb files.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2020-3810\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"1.0.1ubuntu2.24+esm1\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"expat\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.1.0-4ubuntu1.1\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2012-6702\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Expat, when used in a parser that has not called XML_SetHashSalt or passed it a seed of 0, makes it easier for context-dependent attackers to defeat cryptographic protection mechanisms via vectors involving use of the srand function.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2012-6702\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2.1.0-4ubuntu1.3\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"freetype\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.5.2-1ubuntu2.5\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2017-8287\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"FreeType 2 before 2017-03-26 has an out-of-bounds write caused by a heap-based buffer overflow related to the t1_builder_close_contour function in psaux/psobjs.c.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2017-8287\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2.5.2-1ubuntu2.8\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"apt\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1.0.1ubuntu2.10\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2020-27350\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"APT had several integer overflows and underflows while parsing .deb packages, aka GHSL-2020-168 GHSL-2020-169, in files apt-pkg/contrib/extracttar.cc, apt-pkg/deb/debfile.cc, and apt-pkg/contrib/arfile.cc. This issue affects: apt 1.2.32ubuntu0 versions prior to 1.2.32ubuntu0.2; 1.6.12ubuntu0 versions prior to 1.6.12ubuntu0.2; 2.0.2ubuntu0 versions prior to 2.0.2ubuntu0.2; 2.1.10ubuntu0 versions prior to 2.1.10ubuntu0.1;\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2020-27350\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"1.0.1ubuntu2.24+esm3\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"libgcrypt11\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1.5.3-2ubuntu4.2\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2015-7511\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Libgcrypt before 1.6.5 does not properly perform elliptic-point curve multiplication during decryption, which makes it easier for physically proximate attackers to extract ECDH keys by measuring electromagnetic emanations.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2015-7511\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"1.5.3-2ubuntu4.3\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"heimdal\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1.6~git20131207+dfsg-1ubuntu1.1\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2017-11103\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Heimdal before 7.4 allows remote attackers to impersonate services with Orpheus' Lyre attacks because it obtains service-principal names in a way that violates the Kerberos 5 protocol specification. In _krb5_extract_ticket() the KDC-REP service name must be obtained from the encrypted version stored in 'enc_part' instead of the unencrypted version stored in 'ticket'. Use of the unencrypted version provides an opportunity for successful server impersonation and other attacks. NOTE: this CVE is only for Heimdal and other products that embed Heimdal code; it does not apply to other instances in which this part of the Kerberos 5 protocol specification is violated.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2017-11103\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"1.6~git20131207+dfsg-1ubuntu1.2\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"libgcrypt11\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1.5.3-2ubuntu4.2\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2019-13627\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"It was discovered that there was a ECDSA timing attack in the libgcrypt20 cryptographic library. Version affected: 1.8.4-5, 1.7.6-2+deb9u3, and 1.6.3-2+deb8u4. Versions fixed: 1.8.5-2 and 1.6.3-2+deb8u7.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2019-13627\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"1.5.3-2ubuntu4.6+esm1\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"freetype\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.5.2-1ubuntu2.5\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-10244\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"The parse_charstrings function in type1/t1load.c in FreeType 2 before 2.7 does not ensure that a font contains a glyph name, which allows remote attackers to cause a denial of service (heap-based buffer over-read) or possibly have unspecified other impact via a crafted file.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-10244\",\n            \"severity\": \"Medium\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2.5.2-1ubuntu2.6\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"libgcrypt11\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1.5.3-2ubuntu4.2\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2018-0495\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Libgcrypt before 1.7.10 and 1.8.x before 1.8.3 allows a memory-cache side-channel attack on ECDSA signatures that can be mitigated through the use of blinding during the signing process in the _gcry_ecc_ecdsa_sign function in cipher/ecc-ecdsa.c, aka the Return Of the Hidden Number Problem or ROHNP. To discover an ECDSA key, the attacker needs access to either the local machine or a different virtual machine on the same physical host.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2018-0495\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"1.5.3-2ubuntu4.6\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"heimdal\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1.6~git20131207+dfsg-1ubuntu1.1\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2017-6594\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"The transit path validation code in Heimdal before 7.3 might allow attackers to bypass the capath policy protection mechanism by leveraging failure to add the previous hop realm to the transit path of issued tickets.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2017-6594\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"heimdal\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1.6~git20131207+dfsg-1ubuntu1.1\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2019-12098\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"In the client side of Heimdal before 7.6.0, failure to verify anonymous PKINIT PA-PKINIT-KX key exchange permits a man-in-the-middle attack. This issue is in krb5_init_creds_step in lib/krb5/init_creds_pw.c.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2019-12098\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"bzip2\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1.0.6-5\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-3189\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Use-after-free vulnerability in bzip2recover in bzip2 1.0.6 allows remote attackers to cause a denial of service (crash) via a crafted bzip2 file, related to block ends set to before the start of the block.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-3189\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"1.0.6-5ubuntu0.1~esm1\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"git\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1:1.9.1-1ubuntu0.2\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2018-11233\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"In Git before 2.13.7, 2.14.x before 2.14.4, 2.15.x before 2.15.2, 2.16.x before 2.16.4, and 2.17.x before 2.17.1, code to sanity-check pathnames on NTFS can result in reading out-of-bounds memory.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2018-11233\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"1:1.9.1-1ubuntu0.8\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"libgd2\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.1.0-3ubuntu0.5\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-9933\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Stack consumption vulnerability in the gdImageFillToBorder function in gd.c in the GD Graphics Library (aka libgd) before 2.2.2, as used in PHP before 5.6.28 and 7.x before 7.0.13, allows remote attackers to cause a denial of service (segmentation violation) via a crafted imagefilltoborder call that triggers use of a negative color value.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-9933\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2.1.0-3ubuntu0.6\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"git\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1:1.9.1-1ubuntu0.2\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2017-15298\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Git through 2.14.2 mishandles layers of tree objects, which allows remote attackers to cause a denial of service (memory consumption) via a crafted repository, aka a Git bomb. This can also have an impact of disk consumption; however, an affected process typically would not survive its attempt to build the data structure in memory before writing to disk.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2017-15298\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"1:1.9.1-1ubuntu0.10\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"libgd2\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.1.0-3ubuntu0.5\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-9317\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"The gdImageCreate function in the GD Graphics Library (aka libgd) before 2.2.4 allows remote attackers to cause a denial of service (system hang) via an oversized image.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-9317\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2.1.0-3ubuntu0.6\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"freetype\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.5.2-1ubuntu2.5\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2015-9381\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"FreeType before 2.6.1 has a heap-based buffer over-read in T1_Get_Private_Dict in type1/t1parse.c.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2015-9381\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2.5.2-1ubuntu2.8+esm1\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"libgd2\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.1.0-3ubuntu0.5\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2019-6978\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"The GD Graphics Library (aka LibGD) 2.2.5 has a double free in the gdImage*Ptr() functions in gd_gif_out.c, gd_jpeg.c, and gd_wbmp.c. NOTE: PHP is unaffected.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2019-6978\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2.1.0-3ubuntu0.11\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"libtasn1-6\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"3.4-3ubuntu0.3\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2017-10790\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"The _asn1_check_identifier function in GNU Libtasn1 through 4.12 causes a NULL pointer dereference and crash when reading crafted input that triggers assignment of a NULL value within an asn1_node structure. It may lead to a remote denial of service attack.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2017-10790\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"3.4-3ubuntu0.6\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"bash\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"4.3-7ubuntu1.5\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-0634\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"The expansion of '\\\\h' in the prompt string in bash 4.3 allows remote authenticated users to execute arbitrary code via shell metacharacters placed in 'hostname' of a machine.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-0634\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"4.3-7ubuntu1.7\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"bash\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"4.3-7ubuntu1.5\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2019-9924\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"rbash in Bash before 4.4-beta2 did not prevent the shell user from modifying BASH_CMDS, thus allowing the user to execute any command with the permissions of the shell.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2019-9924\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"4.3-7ubuntu1.8+esm1\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"expat\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.1.0-4ubuntu1.1\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2018-20843\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"In libexpat in Expat before 2.2.7, XML input including XML names that contain a large number of colons could make the XML parser consume a high amount of RAM and CPU resources while processing (enough to be usable for denial-of-service attacks).\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2018-20843\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2.1.0-4ubuntu1.4+esm1\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"libgd2\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.1.0-3ubuntu0.5\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2018-5711\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"gd_gif_in.c in the GD Graphics Library (aka libgd), as used in PHP before 5.6.33, 7.0.x before 7.0.27, 7.1.x before 7.1.13, and 7.2.x before 7.2.1, has an integer signedness error that leads to an infinite loop via a crafted GIF file, as demonstrated by a call to the imagecreatefromgif or imagecreatefromstring PHP function. This is related to GetCode_ and gdImageCreateFromGifCtx.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2018-5711\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2.1.0-3ubuntu0.10\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"libgd2\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.1.0-3ubuntu0.5\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2019-11038\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"When using the gdImageCreateFromXbm() function in the GD Graphics Library (aka LibGD) 2.2.5, as used in the PHP GD extension in PHP versions 7.1.x below 7.1.30, 7.2.x below 7.2.19 and 7.3.x below 7.3.6, it is possible to supply data that will cause the function to use the value of uninitialized variable. This may lead to disclosing contents of the stack that has been left there by previous code.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2019-11038\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2.1.0-3ubuntu0.11+esm1\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"bash\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"4.3-7ubuntu1.5\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2019-18276\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"An issue was discovered in disable_priv_mode in shell.c in GNU Bash through 5.0 patch 11. By default, if Bash is run with its effective UID not equal to its real UID, it will drop privileges by setting its effective UID to its real UID. However, it does so incorrectly. On Linux and other systems that support \\\"saved UID\\\" functionality, the saved UID is not dropped. An attacker with command execution in the shell can use \\\"enable -f\\\" for runtime loading of a new builtin, which can be a shared object that calls setuid() and therefore regains privileges. However, binaries running with an effective UID of 0 are unaffected.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2019-18276\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"openssh\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1:6.6p1-2ubuntu2.6\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-10012\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"The shared memory manager (associated with pre-authentication compression) in sshd in OpenSSH before 7.4 does not ensure that a bounds check is enforced by all compilers, which might allows local users to gain privileges by leveraging access to a sandboxed privilege-separation process, related to the m_zback and m_zlib data structures.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-10012\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"1:6.6p1-2ubuntu2.10\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"php5\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"5.5.9+dfsg-1ubuntu4.20\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2017-9119\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"The i_zval_ptr_dtor function in Zend/zend_variables.h in PHP 7.1.5 allows attackers to cause a denial of service (memory consumption and application crash) or possibly have unspecified other impact by triggering crafted operations on array data structures.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2017-9119\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"php5\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"5.5.9+dfsg-1ubuntu4.20\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2020-7062\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"In PHP versions 7.2.x below 7.2.28, 7.3.x below 7.3.15 and 7.4.x below 7.4.3, when using file upload functionality, if upload progress tracking is enabled, but session.upload_progress.cleanup is set to 0 (disabled), and the file upload fails, the upload procedure would try to clean up data that does not exist and encounter null pointer dereference, which would likely lead to a crash.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2020-7062\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"5.5.9+dfsg-1ubuntu4.29+esm11\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"libgd2\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.1.0-3ubuntu0.5\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-6906\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"The read_image_tga function in gd_tga.c in the GD Graphics Library (aka libgd) before 2.2.4 allows remote attackers to cause a denial of service (out-of-bounds read) via a crafted TGA file, related to the decompression buffer.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-6906\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2.1.0-3ubuntu0.6\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"libgd2\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.1.0-3ubuntu0.5\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2018-14553\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"gdImageClone in gd.c in libgd 2.1.0-rc2 through 2.2.5 has a NULL pointer dereference allowing attackers to crash an application via a specific function call sequence. Only affects PHP when linked with an external libgd (not bundled).\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2018-14553\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2.1.0-3ubuntu0.11+esm1\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"php5\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"5.5.9+dfsg-1ubuntu4.20\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2017-8923\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"The zend_string_extend function in Zend/zend_string.h in PHP through 7.1.5 does not prevent changes to string objects that result in a negative length, which allows remote attackers to cause a denial of service (application crash) or possibly have unspecified other impact by leveraging a script's use of .= with a long string.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2017-8923\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"sudo\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1.8.9p5-1ubuntu1.2\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2019-18634\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"In Sudo before 1.8.26, if pwfeedback is enabled in /etc/sudoers, users can trigger a stack-based buffer overflow in the privileged sudo process. (pwfeedback is a default setting in Linux Mint and elementary OS; however, it is NOT the default for upstream and many other packages, and would exist only if enabled by an administrator.) The attacker needs to deliver a long string to the stdin of getln() in tgetpass.c.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2019-18634\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"1.8.9p5-1ubuntu1.5+esm3\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"openssh\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1:6.6p1-2ubuntu2.6\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-10011\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"authfile.c in sshd in OpenSSH before 7.4 does not properly consider the effects of realloc on buffer contents, which might allow local users to obtain sensitive private-key information by leveraging access to a privilege-separated child process.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-10011\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"1:6.6p1-2ubuntu2.10\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"php5\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"5.5.9+dfsg-1ubuntu4.20\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2020-7063\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"In PHP versions 7.2.x below 7.2.28, 7.3.x below 7.3.15 and 7.4.x below 7.4.3, when creating PHAR archive using PharData::buildFromIterator() function, the files are added with default permissions (0666, or all access) even if the original files on the filesystem were with more restrictive permissions. This may result in files having more lax permissions than intended when such archive is extracted.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2020-7063\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"5.5.9+dfsg-1ubuntu4.29+esm11\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"sudo\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1.8.9p5-1ubuntu1.2\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2015-8239\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"The SHA-2 digest support in the sudoers plugin in sudo after 1.8.7 allows local users with write permissions to parts of the called command to replace them before it is executed.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2015-8239\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"php5\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"5.5.9+dfsg-1ubuntu4.20\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2017-7189\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"main/streams/xp_socket.c in PHP 7.x before 2017-03-07 misparses fsockopen calls, such as by interpreting fsockopen('127.0.0.1:80', 443) as if the address/port were 127.0.0.1:80:443, which is later truncated to 127.0.0.1:80. This behavior has a security risk if the explicitly provided port number (i.e., 443 in this example) is hardcoded into an application as a security policy, but the hostname argument (i.e., 127.0.0.1:80 in this example) is obtained from untrusted input.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2017-7189\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"openssh\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1:6.6p1-2ubuntu2.6\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-6210\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"sshd in OpenSSH before 7.3, when SHA256 or SHA512 are used for user password hashing, uses BLOWFISH hashing on a static password when the username does not exist, which allows remote attackers to enumerate users by leveraging the timing difference between responses when a large password is provided.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-6210\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"1:6.6p1-2ubuntu2.8\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"php5\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"5.5.9+dfsg-1ubuntu4.20\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2018-14851\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"exif_process_IFD_in_MAKERNOTE in ext/exif/exif.c in PHP before 5.6.37, 7.0.x before 7.0.31, 7.1.x before 7.1.20, and 7.2.x before 7.2.8 allows remote attackers to cause a denial of service (out-of-bounds read and application crash) via a crafted JPEG file.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2018-14851\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"5.5.9+dfsg-1ubuntu4.26\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"php5\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"5.5.9+dfsg-1ubuntu4.20\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2019-11046\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"In PHP versions 7.2.x below 7.2.26, 7.3.x below 7.3.13 and 7.4.0, PHP bcmath extension functions on some systems, including Windows, can be tricked into reading beyond the allocated space by supplying it with string containing characters that are identified as numeric by the OS but aren't ASCII numbers. This can read to disclosure of the content of some memory locations.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2019-11046\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"5.5.9+dfsg-1ubuntu4.29+esm8\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"gcc-4.8\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"4.8.4-2ubuntu1~14.04\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2015-5276\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"The std::random_device class in libstdc++ in the GNU Compiler Collection (aka GCC) before 4.9.4 does not properly handle short reads from blocking sources, which makes it easier for context-dependent attackers to predict the random values via unspecified vectors.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2015-5276\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"php5\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"5.5.9+dfsg-1ubuntu4.20\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-10712\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"In PHP before 5.5.32, 5.6.x before 5.6.18, and 7.x before 7.0.3, all of the return values of stream_get_meta_data can be controlled if the input can be controlled (e.g., during file uploads). For example, a \\\"$uri = stream_get_meta_data(fopen($file, \\\"r\\\"))['uri']\\\" call mishandles the case where $file is data:text/plain;uri=eviluri, -- in other words, metadata can be set by an attacker.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-10712\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"5.5.9+dfsg-1ubuntu4.24\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"php5\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"5.5.9+dfsg-1ubuntu4.20\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-9138\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"PHP through 5.6.27 and 7.x through 7.0.12 mishandles property modification during __wakeup processing, which allows remote attackers to cause a denial of service or possibly have unspecified other impact via crafted serialized data, as demonstrated by Exception::__toString with DateInterval::__wakeup.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-9138\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"tiff\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"4.0.3-7ubuntu0.4\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2019-14973\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"_TIFFCheckMalloc and _TIFFCheckRealloc in tif_aux.c in LibTIFF through 4.0.10 mishandle Integer Overflow checks because they rely on compiler behavior that is undefined by the applicable C standards. This can, for example, lead to an application crash.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2019-14973\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"tiff\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"4.0.3-7ubuntu0.4\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2018-10779\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"TIFFWriteScanline in tif_write.c in LibTIFF 3.8.2 has a heap-based buffer over-read, as demonstrated by bmp2tiff.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2018-10779\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"4.0.3-7ubuntu0.11\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"tiff\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"4.0.3-7ubuntu0.4\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2018-12900\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Heap-based buffer overflow in the cpSeparateBufToContigBuf function in tiffcp.c in LibTIFF 3.9.3, 3.9.4, 3.9.5, 3.9.6, 3.9.7, 4.0.0beta7, 4.0.0alpha4, 4.0.0alpha5, 4.0.0alpha6, 4.0.0, 4.0.1, 4.0.2, 4.0.3, 4.0.4, 4.0.4beta, 4.0.5, 4.0.6, 4.0.7, 4.0.8 and 4.0.9 allows remote attackers to cause a denial of service (crash) or possibly have unspecified other impact via a crafted TIFF file.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2018-12900\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"4.0.3-7ubuntu0.11\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"tiff\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"4.0.3-7ubuntu0.4\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2019-6128\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"The TIFFFdOpen function in tif_unix.c in LibTIFF 4.0.10 has a memory leak, as demonstrated by pal2rgb.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2019-6128\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"4.0.3-7ubuntu0.11\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"tiff\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"4.0.3-7ubuntu0.4\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2017-13727\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"There is a reachable assertion abort in the function TIFFWriteDirectoryTagSubifd() in LibTIFF 4.0.8, related to tif_dirwrite.c and a SubIFD tag. A crafted input will lead to a remote denial of service attack.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2017-13727\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"4.0.3-7ubuntu0.8\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"tiff\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"4.0.3-7ubuntu0.4\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2017-9403\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"In LibTIFF 4.0.7, a memory leak vulnerability was found in the function TIFFReadDirEntryLong8Array in tif_dirread.c, which allows attackers to cause a denial of service via a crafted file.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2017-9403\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"4.0.3-7ubuntu0.8\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"php5\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"5.5.9+dfsg-1ubuntu4.20\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2020-7068\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"In PHP versions 7.2.x below 7.2.33, 7.3.x below 7.3.21 and 7.4.x below 7.4.9, while processing PHAR files using phar extension, phar_parse_zipfile could be tricked into accessing freed memory, which could lead to a crash or information disclosure.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2020-7068\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"tiff\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"4.0.3-7ubuntu0.4\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2017-12944\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"The TIFFReadDirEntryArray function in tif_read.c in LibTIFF 4.0.8 mishandles memory allocation for short files, which allows remote attackers to cause a denial of service (allocation failure and application crash) in the TIFFFetchStripThing function in tif_dirread.c during a tiff2pdf invocation.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2017-12944\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"4.0.3-7ubuntu0.8\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"php5\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"5.5.9+dfsg-1ubuntu4.20\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-9137\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Use-after-free vulnerability in the CURLFile implementation in ext/curl/curl_file.c in PHP before 5.6.27 and 7.x before 7.0.12 allows remote attackers to cause a denial of service or possibly have unspecified other impact via crafted serialized data that is mishandled during __wakeup processing.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-9137\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"5.5.9+dfsg-1ubuntu4.21\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"tiff\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"4.0.3-7ubuntu0.4\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-9538\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"tools/tiffcrop.c in libtiff 4.0.6 reads an undefined buffer in readContigStripsIntoBuffer() because of a uint16 integer overflow. Reported as MSVR 35100.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-9538\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"4.0.3-7ubuntu0.6\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"openssh\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1:6.6p1-2ubuntu2.6\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2018-15473\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"OpenSSH through 7.7 is prone to a user enumeration vulnerability due to not delaying bailout for an invalid authenticating user until after the packet containing the request has been fully parsed, related to auth2-gss.c, auth2-hostbased.c, and auth2-pubkey.c.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2018-15473\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"1:6.6p1-2ubuntu2.11\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"php5\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"5.5.9+dfsg-1ubuntu4.20\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2019-11047\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"When PHP EXIF extension is parsing EXIF information from an image, e.g. via exif_read_data() function, in PHP versions 7.2.x below 7.2.26, 7.3.x below 7.3.13 and 7.4.0 it is possible to supply it with data what will cause it to read past the allocated buffer. This may lead to information disclosure or crash.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2019-11047\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"5.5.9+dfsg-1ubuntu4.29+esm8\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"openssh\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1:6.6p1-2ubuntu2.6\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2015-8325\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"The do_setup_env function in session.c in sshd in OpenSSH through 7.2p2, when the UseLogin feature is enabled and PAM is configured to read .pam_environment files in user home directories, allows local users to gain privileges by triggering a crafted environment for the /bin/login program, as demonstrated by an LD_PRELOAD environment variable.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2015-8325\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"1:6.6p1-2ubuntu2.7\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"php5\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"5.5.9+dfsg-1ubuntu4.20\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2018-20783\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"In PHP before 5.6.39, 7.x before 7.0.33, 7.1.x before 7.1.25, and 7.2.x before 7.2.13, a buffer over-read in PHAR reading functions may allow an attacker to read allocated or unallocated memory past the actual data when trying to parse a .phar file. This is related to phar_parse_pharfile in ext/phar/phar.c.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2018-20783\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"5.5.9+dfsg-1ubuntu4.29+esm2\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"php5\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"5.5.9+dfsg-1ubuntu4.20\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2014-9912\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"The get_icu_disp_value_src_php function in ext/intl/locale/locale_methods.c in PHP before 5.3.29, 5.4.x before 5.4.30, and 5.5.x before 5.5.14 does not properly restrict calls to the ICU uresbund.cpp component, which allows remote attackers to cause a denial of service (buffer overflow) or possibly have unspecified other impact via a locale_get_display_name call with a long first argument.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2014-9912\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"5.5.9+dfsg-1ubuntu4.21\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"php5\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"5.5.9+dfsg-1ubuntu4.20\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2019-9675\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"** DISPUTED ** An issue was discovered in PHP 7.x before 7.1.27 and 7.3.x before 7.3.3. phar_tar_writeheaders_int in ext/phar/tar.c has a buffer overflow via a long link value. NOTE: The vendor indicates that the link value is used only when an archive contains a symlink, which currently cannot happen: \\\"This issue allows theoretical compromise of security, but a practical attack is usually impossible.\\\"\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2019-9675\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"5.5.9+dfsg-1ubuntu4.29\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"php5\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"5.5.9+dfsg-1ubuntu4.20\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-10158\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"The exif_convert_any_to_int function in ext/exif/exif.c in PHP before 5.6.30, 7.0.x before 7.0.15, and 7.1.x before 7.1.1 allows remote attackers to cause a denial of service (application crash) via crafted EXIF data that triggers an attempt to divide the minimum representable negative integer by -1.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-10158\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"5.5.9+dfsg-1ubuntu4.21\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"pam\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1.1.8-1ubuntu2\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2014-2583\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Multiple directory traversal vulnerabilities in pam_timestamp.c in the pam_timestamp module for Linux-PAM (aka pam) 1.1.8 allow local users to create arbitrary files or possibly bypass authentication via a .. (dot dot) in the (1) PAM_RUSER value to the get_ruser function or (2) PAM_TTY value to the check_tty function, which is used by the format_timestamp_name function.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2014-2583\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"1.1.8-1ubuntu2.1\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"php5\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"5.5.9+dfsg-1ubuntu4.20\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2015-9253\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"An issue was discovered in PHP 7.3.x before 7.3.0alpha3, 7.2.x before 7.2.8, and before 7.1.20. The php-fpm master process restarts a child process in an endless loop when using program execution functions (e.g., passthru, exec, shell_exec, or system) with a non-blocking STDIN stream, causing this master process to consume 100% of the CPU, and consume disk space with a large volume of error logs, as demonstrated by an attack by a customer of a shared-hosting facility.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2015-9253\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"5.5.9+dfsg-1ubuntu4.29+esm10\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"php5\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"5.5.9+dfsg-1ubuntu4.20\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-10159\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Integer overflow in the phar_parse_pharfile function in ext/phar/phar.c in PHP before 5.6.30 and 7.0.x before 7.0.15 allows remote attackers to cause a denial of service (memory consumption or application crash) via a truncated manifest entry in a PHAR archive.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-10159\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"5.5.9+dfsg-1ubuntu4.21\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"tiff\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"4.0.3-7ubuntu0.4\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-3623\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"The rgb2ycbcr tool in LibTIFF 4.0.6 and earlier allows remote attackers to cause a denial of service (divide-by-zero) by setting the (1) v or (2) h parameter to 0.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-3623\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"4.0.3-7ubuntu0.6\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"php5\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"5.5.9+dfsg-1ubuntu4.20\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2015-8994\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"An issue was discovered in PHP 5.x and 7.x, when the configuration uses apache2handler/mod_php or php-fpm with OpCache enabled. With 5.x after 5.6.28 or 7.x after 7.0.13, the issue is resolved in a non-default configuration with the opcache.validate_permission=1 setting. The vulnerability details are as follows. In PHP SAPIs where PHP interpreters share a common parent process, Zend OpCache creates a shared memory object owned by the common parent during initialization. Child PHP processes inherit the SHM descriptor, using it to cache and retrieve compiled script bytecode (\\\"opcode\\\" in PHP jargon). Cache keys vary depending on configuration, but filename is a central key component, and compiled opcode can generally be run if a script's filename is known or can be guessed. Many common shared-hosting configurations change EUID in child processes to enforce privilege separation among hosted users (for example using mod_ruid2 for the Apache HTTP Server, or php-fpm user settings). In these scenarios, the default Zend OpCache behavior defeats script file permissions by sharing a single SHM cache among all child PHP processes. PHP scripts often contain sensitive information: Think of CMS configurations where reading or running another user's script usually means gaining privileges to the CMS database.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2015-8994\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"5.5.9+dfsg-1ubuntu4.22\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"tiff\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"4.0.3-7ubuntu0.4\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2017-9117\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"In LibTIFF 4.0.7, the program processes BMP images without verifying that biWidth and biHeight in the bitmap-information header match the actual input, leading to a heap-based buffer over-read in bmp2tiff.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2017-9117\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"4.0.3-7ubuntu0.9\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"php5\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"5.5.9+dfsg-1ubuntu4.20\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2019-11050\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"When PHP EXIF extension is parsing EXIF information from an image, e.g. via exif_read_data() function, in PHP versions 7.2.x below 7.2.26, 7.3.x below 7.3.13 and 7.4.0 it is possible to supply it with data what will cause it to read past the allocated buffer. This may lead to information disclosure or crash.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2019-11050\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"5.5.9+dfsg-1ubuntu4.29+esm8\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"tiff\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"4.0.3-7ubuntu0.4\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-9537\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"tools/tiffcrop.c in libtiff 4.0.6 has out-of-bounds write vulnerabilities in buffers. Reported as MSVR 35093, MSVR 35096, and MSVR 35097.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-9537\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"4.0.3-7ubuntu0.6\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"php5\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"5.5.9+dfsg-1ubuntu4.20\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2019-11036\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"When processing certain files, PHP EXIF extension in versions 7.1.x below 7.1.29, 7.2.x below 7.2.18 and 7.3.x below 7.3.5 can be caused to read past allocated buffer in exif_process_IFD_TAG function. This may lead to information disclosure or crash.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2019-11036\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"5.5.9+dfsg-1ubuntu4.29+esm2\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"tiff\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"4.0.3-7ubuntu0.4\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2018-18661\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"An issue was discovered in LibTIFF 4.0.9. There is a NULL pointer dereference in the function LZWDecode in the file tif_lzw.c.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2018-18661\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"4.0.3-7ubuntu0.10\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"tiff\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"4.0.3-7ubuntu0.4\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2017-9815\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"In LibTIFF 4.0.7, the TIFFReadDirEntryLong8Array function in libtiff/tif_dirread.c mishandles a malloc operation, which allows attackers to cause a denial of service (memory lea