of-bounds read) via crafted TIFF_SETGET_C16ASCII or TIFF_SETGET_C32_ASCII tag values.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-9297\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"4.0.3-7ubuntu0.6\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"libvpx\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1.3.0-2\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2019-9232\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"In libvpx, there is a possible out of bounds read due to a missing bounds check. This could lead to remote information disclosure with no additional execution privileges needed. User interaction is not needed for exploitation. Product: AndroidVersions: Android-10Android ID: A-122675483\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2019-9232\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"1.3.0-2ubuntu0.1~esm1\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"tiff\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"4.0.3-7ubuntu0.4\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-5102\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Buffer overflow in the readgifimage function in gif2tiff.c in the gif2tiff tool in LibTIFF 4.0.6 allows remote attackers to cause a denial of service (segmentation fault) via a crafted gif file.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-5102\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"4.0.3-7ubuntu0.9\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"pam\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1.1.8-1ubuntu2\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2013-7041\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"The pam_userdb module for Pam uses a case-insensitive method to compare hashed passwords, which makes it easier for attackers to guess the password via a brute force attack.\