016-10371\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"The TIFFWriteDirectoryTagCheckedRational function in tif_dirwrite.c in LibTIFF 4.0.6 allows remote attackers to cause a denial of service (assertion failure and application exit) via a crafted TIFF file.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-10371\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"4.0.3-7ubuntu0.8\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"tiff\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"4.0.3-7ubuntu0.4\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-3658\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"The TIFFWriteDirectoryTagLongLong8Array function in tif_dirwrite.c in the tiffset tool in LibTIFF 4.0.6 and earlier allows remote attackers to cause a denial of service (out-of-bounds read) via vectors involving the ma variable.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-3658\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"4.0.3-7ubuntu0.6\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"util-linux\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.20.1-5.1ubuntu20.7\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2013-0157\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"(a) mount and (b) umount in util-linux 2.14.1, 2.17.2, and probably other versions allow local users to determine the existence of restricted directories by (1) using the --guess-fstype command-line option or (2) attempting to mount a non-existent device, which generates different error messages depending on whether the directory exists.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2013-0157\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"tiff\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"4.0.3-7ubuntu0.4\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2015-8668\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Heap-based buffer overflow in the PackBitsPreEncode function in tif_packbits.c in bmp2tiff in libtiff 4.0.6 and earlier allows remote attackers to execute arbitrary code or cause a denial of service via a large width field in a BMP image.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2015-8668\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"4.0.3-7ubuntu0.6\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"tiff\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"4.0.3-7ubuntu0.4\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2017-11613\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"In LibTIFF 4.0.8, there is a denial of service vulnerability in the TIFFOpen function. A crafted input will lead to a denial of service attack. During the TIFFOpen process, td_imagelength is not checked. The value of td_imagelength can be directly controlled by an input file. In the ChopUpSingleUncompressedStrip function, the _TIFFCheckMalloc function is called based on td_imagelength. If we set the value of td_imagelength close to the amount of system memory, it will hang the system or trigger the OOM killer.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2017-11613\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"4.0.3-7ubuntu0.9\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"openssh\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1:6.6p1-2ubuntu2.6\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2019-6111\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"An issue was discovered in OpenSSH 7.9. Due to the scp implementation being derived from 1983 rcp, the server chooses which files/directories are sent to the client. However, the scp client only performs cursory validation of the object name returned (only directory traversal attacks are prevented). A malicious scp server (or Man-in-The-Middle attacker) can overwrite arbitrary files in the scp client target directory. If recursive operation (-r) is performed, the server can manipulate subdirectories as well (for example, to overwrite the .ssh/authorized_keys file).\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2019-6111\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"1:6.6p1-2ubuntu2.13\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"tiff\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"4.0.3-7ubuntu0.4\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2018-5784\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"In LibTIFF 4.0.9, there is an uncontrolled resource consumption in the TIFFSetDirectory function of tif_dir.c. Remote attackers could leverage this vulnerability to cause a denial of service via a crafted tif file. This occurs because the declared number of directory entries is not validated against the actual number of directory entries.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2018-5784\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"4.0.3-7ubuntu0.8\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"tiff\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"4.0.3-7ubuntu0.4\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-5323\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"The _TIFFFax3fillruns function in libtiff before 4.0.6 allows remote attackers to cause a denial of service (divide-by-zero error and application crash) via a crafted Tiff image.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-5323\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"4.0.3-7ubuntu0.6\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"util-linux\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.20.1-5.1ubuntu20.7\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2014-9114\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Blkid in util-linux before 2.26rc-1 allows local users to execute arbitrary code.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2014-9114\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"tiff\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"4.0.3-7ubuntu0.4\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2017-11335\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"There is a heap based buffer overflow in tools/tiff2pdf.c of LibTIFF 4.0.8 via a PlanarConfig=Contig image, which causes a more than one hundred bytes out-of-bounds write (related to the ZIPDecode function in tif_zip.c). A crafted input may lead to a remote denial of service attack or an arbitrary code execution attack.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2017-11335\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"4.0.3-7ubuntu0.8\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"libdbd-mysql-perl\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"4.025-1\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2017-10788\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"The DBD::mysql module through 4.043 for Perl allows remote attackers to cause a denial of service (use-after-free and application crash) or possibly have unspecified other impact by triggering (1) certain error responses from a MySQL server or (2) a loss of a network connection to a MySQL server. The use-after-free defect was introduced by relying on incorrect Oracle mysql_stmt_close documentation and code examples.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2017-10788\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"tiff\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"4.0.3-7ubuntu0.4\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2017-10688\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"In LibTIFF 4.0.8, there is a assertion abort in the TIFFWriteDirectoryTagCheckedLong8Array function in tif_dirwrite.c. A crafted input will lead to a remote denial of service attack.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2017-10688\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"4.0.3-7ubuntu0.8\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"libdbd-mysql-perl\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"4.025-1\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2017-10789\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"The DBD::mysql module through 4.043 for Perl uses the mysql_ssl=1 setting to mean that SSL is optional (even though this setting's documentation has a \\\"your communication with the server will be encrypted\\\" statement), which allows man-in-the-middle attackers to spoof servers via a cleartext-downgrade attack, a related issue to CVE-2015-3152.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2017-10789\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"ntp\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1:4.2.6.p5+dfsg-3ubuntu2.14.04.6\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-9311\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"ntpd in NTP before 4.2.8p9, when the trap service is enabled, allows remote attackers to cause a denial of service (NULL pointer dereference and crash) via a crafted packet.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-9311\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"1:4.2.6.p5+dfsg-3ubuntu2.14.04.11\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"tiff\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"4.0.3-7ubuntu0.4\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2018-8905\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"In LibTIFF 4.0.9, a heap-based buffer overflow occurs in the function LZWDecodeCompat in tif_lzw.c via a crafted TIFF file, as demonstrated by tiff2ps.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2018-8905\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"4.0.3-7ubuntu0.10\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"openssh\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1:6.6p1-2ubuntu2.6\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2020-14145\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"The client side in OpenSSH 5.7 through 8.4 has an Observable Discrepancy leading to an information leak in the algorithm negotiation. This allows man-in-the-middle attackers to target initial connection attempts (where no host key for the server has been cached by the client).\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2020-14145\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"ntp\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1:4.2.6.p5+dfsg-3ubuntu2.14.04.6\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2017-6463\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"NTP before 4.2.8p10 and 4.3.x before 4.3.94 allows remote authenticated users to cause a denial of service (daemon crash) via an invalid setting in a :config directive, related to the unpeer option.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2017-6463\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"1:4.2.6.p5+dfsg-3ubuntu2.14.04.11\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"ntp\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1:4.2.6.p5+dfsg-3ubuntu2.14.04.6\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2015-8158\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"The getresponse function in ntpq in NTP versions before 4.2.8p9 and 4.3.x before 4.3.90 allows remote attackers to cause a denial of service (infinite loop) via crafted packets with incorrect values.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2015-8158\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"1:4.2.6.p5+dfsg-3ubuntu2.14.04.10\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"tiff\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"4.0.3-7ubuntu0.4\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2017-17942\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"In LibTIFF 4.0.9, there is a heap-based buffer over-read in the function PackBitsEncode in tif_packbits.c.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2017-17942\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"tiff\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"4.0.3-7ubuntu0.4\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-6223\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"The TIFFReadRawStrip1 and TIFFReadRawTile1 functions in tif_read.c in libtiff before 4.0.7 allows remote attackers to cause a denial of service (crash) or possibly obtain sensitive information via a negative index in a file-content buffer.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-6223\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"4.0.3-7ubuntu0.6\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"tiff\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"4.0.3-7ubuntu0.4\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-5652\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"An exploitable heap-based buffer overflow exists in the handling of TIFF images in LibTIFF's TIFF2PDF tool. A crafted TIFF document can lead to a heap-based buffer overflow resulting in remote code execution. Vulnerability can be triggered via a saved TIFF file delivered by other means.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-5652\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"4.0.3-7ubuntu0.6\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"ntp\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1:4.2.6.p5+dfsg-3ubuntu2.14.04.6\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-7427\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"The broadcast mode replay prevention functionality in ntpd in NTP before 4.2.8p9 allows remote attackers to cause a denial of service (reject broadcast mode packets) via a crafted broadcast mode packet.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-7427\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"1:4.2.6.p5+dfsg-3ubuntu2.14.04.11\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"ntp\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1:4.2.6.p5+dfsg-3ubuntu2.14.04.6\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2018-7185\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"The protocol engine in ntp 4.2.6 before 4.2.8p11 allows a remote attackers to cause a denial of service (disruption) by continually sending a packet with a zero-origin timestamp and source IP address of the \\\"other side\\\" of an interleaved association causing the victim ntpd to reset its association.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2018-7185\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"1:4.2.6.p5+dfsg-3ubuntu2.14.04.13\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"ntp\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1:4.2.6.p5+dfsg-3ubuntu2.14.04.6\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-7426\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"NTP before 4.2.8p9 rate limits responses received from the configured sources when rate limiting for all associations is enabled, which allows remote attackers to cause a denial of service (prevent responses from the sources) by sending responses with a spoofed source address.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-7426\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"1:4.2.6.p5+dfsg-3ubuntu2.14.04.11\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"tiff\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"4.0.3-7ubuntu0.4\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2018-15209\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"ChopUpSingleUncompressedStrip in tif_dirread.c in LibTIFF 4.0.9 allows remote attackers to cause a denial of service (heap-based buffer overflow and application crash) or possibly have unspecified other impact via a crafted TIFF file, as demonstrated by tiff2pdf.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2018-15209\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"4.0.3-7ubuntu0.9\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"tiff\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"4.0.3-7ubuntu0.4\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-3622\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"The fpAcc function in tif_predict.c in the tiff2rgba tool in LibTIFF 4.0.6 and earlier allows remote attackers to cause a denial of service (divide-by-zero error) via a crafted TIFF image.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-3622\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"4.0.3-7ubuntu0.6\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"tiff\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"4.0.3-7ubuntu0.4\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2017-9404\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"In LibTIFF 4.0.7, a memory leak vulnerability was found in the function OJPEGReadHeaderInfoSecTablesQTable in tif_ojpeg.c, which allows attackers to cause a denial of service via a crafted file.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2017-9404\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"4.0.3-7ubuntu0.8\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"tiff\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"4.0.3-7ubuntu0.4\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-9448\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"The TIFFFetchNormalTag function in LibTiff 4.0.6 allows remote attackers to cause a denial of service (NULL pointer dereference and crash) by setting the tags TIFF_SETGET_C16ASCII or TIFF_SETGET_C32_ASCII to values that access 0-byte arrays.  NOTE: this vulnerability exists because of an incomplete fix for CVE-2016-9297.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-9448\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"4.0.3-7ubuntu0.6\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"busybox\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1:1.21.0-1ubuntu1\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-2147\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Integer overflow in the DHCP client (udhcpc) in BusyBox before 1.25.0 allows remote attackers to cause a denial of service (crash) via a malformed RFC1035-encoded domain name, which triggers an out-of-bounds heap write.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-2147\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"1:1.21.0-1ubuntu1.4\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"openssh\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1:6.6p1-2ubuntu2.6\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2017-15906\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"The process_open function in sftp-server.c in OpenSSH before 7.6 does not properly prevent write operations in readonly mode, which allows attackers to create zero-length files.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2017-15906\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"1:6.6p1-2ubuntu2.10\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"busybox\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1:1.21.0-1ubuntu1\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2011-5325\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Directory traversal vulnerability in the BusyBox implementation of tar before 1.22.0 v5 allows remote attackers to point to files outside the current working directory via a symlink.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2011-5325\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"1:1.21.0-1ubuntu1.4\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"busybox\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1:1.21.0-1ubuntu1\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-2148\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Heap-based buffer overflow in the DHCP client (udhcpc) in BusyBox before 1.25.0 allows remote attackers to have unspecified impact via vectors involving OPTION_6RD parsing.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-2148\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"1:1.21.0-1ubuntu1.4\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"busybox\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1:1.21.0-1ubuntu1\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2014-9645\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"The add_probe function in modutils/modprobe.c in BusyBox before 1.23.0 allows local users to bypass intended restrictions on loading kernel modules via a / (slash) character in a module name, as demonstrated by an \\\"ifconfig /usbserial up\\\" command or a \\\"mount -t /snd_pcm none /\\\" command.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2014-9645\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"1:1.21.0-1ubuntu1.4\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"openssh\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1:6.6p1-2ubuntu2.6\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-1908\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"The client in OpenSSH before 7.2 mishandles failed cookie generation for untrusted X11 forwarding and relies on the local X11 server for access-control decisions, which allows remote X11 clients to trigger a fallback and obtain trusted X11 forwarding privileges by leveraging configuration issues on this X11 server, as demonstrated by lack of the SECURITY extension on this X11 server.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-1908\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"1:6.6p1-2ubuntu2.7\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"busybox\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1:1.21.0-1ubuntu1\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2018-20679\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"An issue was discovered in BusyBox before 1.30.0. An out of bounds read in udhcp components (consumed by the DHCP server, client, and relay) allows a remote attacker to leak sensitive information from the stack by sending a crafted DHCP message. This is related to verification in udhcp_get_option() in networking/udhcp/common.c that 4-byte options are indeed 4 bytes.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2018-20679\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"1:1.21.0-1ubuntu1.4\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"ntp\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1:4.2.6.p5+dfsg-3ubuntu2.14.04.6\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-2518\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"The MATCH_ASSOC function in NTP before version 4.2.8p9 and 4.3.x before 4.3.92 allows remote attackers to cause an out-of-bounds reference via an addpeer request with a large hmode value.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-2518\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"1:4.2.6.p5+dfsg-3ubuntu2.14.04.10\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"busybox\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1:1.21.0-1ubuntu1\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2017-15873\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"The get_next_block function in archival/libarchive/decompress_bunzip2.c in BusyBox 1.27.2 has an Integer Overflow that may lead to a write access violation.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2017-15873\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"1:1.21.0-1ubuntu1.4\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"openssh\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1:6.6p1-2ubuntu2.6\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-10708\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"sshd in OpenSSH before 7.4 allows remote attackers to cause a denial of service (NULL pointer dereference and daemon crash) via an out-of-sequence NEWKEYS message, as demonstrated by Honggfuzz, related to kex.c and packet.c.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-10708\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"1:6.6p1-2ubuntu2.11\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"coreutils\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"8.21-1ubuntu5.3\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-2781\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"chroot in GNU coreutils, when used with --userspec, allows local users to escape to the parent session via a crafted TIOCSTI ioctl call, which pushes characters to the terminal's input buffer.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-2781\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"cpio\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.11+dfsg-1ubuntu1.1\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2015-1197\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"cpio 2.11, when using the --no-absolute-filenames option, allows local users to write to arbitrary files via a symlink attack on a file in an archive.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2015-1197\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2.11+dfsg-1ubuntu1.2\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"ntp\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1:4.2.6.p5+dfsg-3ubuntu2.14.04.6\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-9310\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"The control mode (mode 6) functionality in ntpd in NTP before 4.2.8p9 allows remote attackers to set or unset traps via a crafted control mode packet.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-9310\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"1:4.2.6.p5+dfsg-3ubuntu2.14.04.11\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"pcre3\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1:8.31-2ubuntu2.1\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2015-8390\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"PCRE before 8.38 mishandles the [: and \\\\\\\\ substrings in character classes, which allows remote attackers to cause a denial of service (uninitialized memory read) or possibly have unspecified other impact via a crafted regular expression, as demonstrated by a JavaScript RegExp object encountered by Konqueror.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2015-8390\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"1:8.31-2ubuntu2.2\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"ntp\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1:4.2.6.p5+dfsg-3ubuntu2.14.04.6\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2015-7974\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"NTP 4.x before 4.2.8p6 and 4.3.x before 4.3.90 do not verify peer associations of symmetric keys when authenticating packets, which might allow remote attackers to conduct impersonation attacks via an arbitrary trusted key, aka a \\\"skeleton key.\\\"\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2015-7974\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"1:4.2.6.p5+dfsg-3ubuntu2.14.04.10\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"ntp\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1:4.2.6.p5+dfsg-3ubuntu2.14.04.6\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-7429\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"NTP before 4.2.8p9 changes the peer structure to the interface it receives the response from a source, which allows remote attackers to cause a denial of service (prevent communication with a source) by sending a response for a source to an interface the source does not use.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-7429\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"1:4.2.6.p5+dfsg-3ubuntu2.14.04.11\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"ntp\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1:4.2.6.p5+dfsg-3ubuntu2.14.04.6\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2015-7979\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"NTP before 4.2.8p6 and 4.3.x before 4.3.90 allows remote attackers to cause a denial of service (client-server association tear down) by sending broadcast packets with invalid authentication to a broadcast client.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2015-7979\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"1:4.2.6.p5+dfsg-3ubuntu2.14.04.10\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"ntp\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1:4.2.6.p5+dfsg-3ubuntu2.14.04.6\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-0727\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"The crontab script in the ntp package before 1:4.2.6.p3+dfsg-1ubuntu3.11 on Ubuntu 12.04 LTS, before 1:4.2.6.p5+dfsg-3ubuntu2.14.04.10 on Ubuntu 14.04 LTS, on Ubuntu Wily, and before 1:4.2.8p4+dfsg-3ubuntu5.3 on Ubuntu 16.04 LTS allows local users with access to the ntp account to write to arbitrary files and consequently gain privileges via vectors involving statistics directory cleanup.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-0727\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"1:4.2.6.p5+dfsg-3ubuntu2.14.04.10\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"dpkg\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1.17.5ubuntu5.5\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2014-8625\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Multiple format string vulnerabilities in the parse_error_msg function in parsehelp.c in dpkg before 1.17.22 allow remote attackers to cause a denial of service (crash) and possibly execute arbitrary code via format string specifiers in the (1) package or (2) architecture name.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2014-8625\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"libxml2\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.9.1+dfsg1-3ubuntu4.7\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2017-16932\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"parser.c in libxml2 before 2.9.5 does not prevent infinite recursion in parameter entities.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2017-16932\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2.9.1+dfsg1-3ubuntu4.11\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"libxml2\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.9.1+dfsg1-3ubuntu4.7\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2015-8806\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"dict.c in libxml2 allows remote attackers to cause a denial of service (heap-based buffer over-read and application crash) via an unexpected character immediately after the \\\"\\u003c!DOCTYPE html\\\" substring in a crafted HTML document.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2015-8806\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2.9.1+dfsg1-3ubuntu4.8\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"curl\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"7.35.0-1ubuntu2.6\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-8616\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"A flaw was found in curl before version 7.51.0 When re-using a connection, curl was doing case insensitive comparisons of user name and password with the existing connections. This means that if an unused connection with proper credentials exists for a protocol that has connection-scoped credentials, an attacker can cause that connection to be reused if s/he knows the case-insensitive version of the correct password.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-8616\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"7.35.0-1ubuntu2.10\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"libxml2\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.9.1+dfsg1-3ubuntu4.7\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-9318\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"libxml2 2.9.4 and earlier, as used in XMLSec 1.2.23 and earlier and other products, does not offer a flag directly indicating that the current document may be read but other files may not be opened, which makes it easier for remote attackers to conduct XML External Entity (XXE) attacks via a crafted document.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-9318\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2.9.1+dfsg1-3ubuntu4.13\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"libxml2\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.9.1+dfsg1-3ubuntu4.7\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-4448\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Format string vulnerability in libxml2 before 2.9.4 allows attackers to have unspecified impact via format string specifiers in unknown vectors.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-4448\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2.9.1+dfsg1-3ubuntu4.9\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"libxml2\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.9.1+dfsg1-3ubuntu4.7\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2019-19956\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"xmlParseBalancedChunkMemoryRecover in parser.c in libxml2 before 2.9.10 has a memory leak related to newDoc-\\u003eoldNs.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2019-19956\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2.9.1+dfsg1-3ubuntu4.13+esm1\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"libxml2\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.9.1+dfsg1-3ubuntu4.7\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-4483\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"The xmlBufAttrSerializeTxtContent function in xmlsave.c in libxml2 allows context-dependent attackers to cause a denial of service (out-of-bounds read and application crash) via a non-UTF-8 attribute value, related to serialization.  NOTE: this vulnerability may be a duplicate of CVE-2016-3627.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-4483\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2.9.1+dfsg1-3ubuntu4.8\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"libxml2\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.9.1+dfsg1-3ubuntu4.7\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-3627\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"The xmlStringGetNodeList function in tree.c in libxml2 2.9.3 and earlier, when used in recovery mode, allows context-dependent attackers to cause a denial of service (infinite recursion, stack consumption, and application crash) via a crafted XML document.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-3627\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2.9.1+dfsg1-3ubuntu4.8\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"libxml2\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.9.1+dfsg1-3ubuntu4.7\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2020-7595\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"xmlStringLenDecodeEntities in parser.c in libxml2 2.9.10 has an infinite loop in a certain end-of-file situation.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2020-7595\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2.9.1+dfsg1-3ubuntu4.13+esm1\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"libxml2\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.9.1+dfsg1-3ubuntu4.7\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-3705\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"The (1) xmlParserEntityCheck and (2) xmlParseAttValueComplex functions in parser.c in libxml2 2.9.3 do not properly keep track of the recursion depth, which allows context-dependent attackers to cause a denial of service (stack consumption and application crash) via a crafted XML document containing a large number of nested entity references.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-3705\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2.9.1+dfsg1-3ubuntu4.8\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"libxml2\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.9.1+dfsg1-3ubuntu4.7\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-4449\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"XML external entity (XXE) vulnerability in the xmlStringLenDecodeEntities function in parser.c in libxml2 before 2.9.4, when not in validating mode, allows context-dependent attackers to read arbitrary files or cause a denial of service (resource consumption) via unspecified vectors.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-4449\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2.9.1+dfsg1-3ubuntu4.8\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"curl\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"7.35.0-1ubuntu2.6\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-7167\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Multiple integer overflows in the (1) curl_escape, (2) curl_easy_escape, (3) curl_unescape, and (4) curl_easy_unescape functions in libcurl before 7.50.3 allow attackers to have unspecified impact via a string of length 0xffffffff, which triggers a heap-based buffer overflow.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-7167\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"7.35.0-1ubuntu2.10\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"curl\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"7.35.0-1ubuntu2.6\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2019-3823\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"libcurl versions from 7.34.0 to before 7.64.0 are vulnerable to a heap out-of-bounds read in the code handling the end-of-response for SMTP. If the buffer passed to `smtp_endofresp()` isn't NUL terminated and contains no character ending the parsed number, and `len` is set to 5, then the `strtol()` call reads beyond the allocated buffer. The read contents will not be returned to the caller.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2019-3823\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"7.35.0-1ubuntu2.20\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"curl\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"7.35.0-1ubuntu2.6\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2017-1000100\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"When doing a TFTP transfer and curl/libcurl is given a URL that contains a very long file name (longer than about 515 bytes), the file name is truncated to fit within the buffer boundaries, but the buffer size is still wrongly updated to use the untruncated length. This too large value is then used in the sendto() call, making curl attempt to send more data than what is actually put into the buffer. The endto() function will then read beyond the end of the heap based buffer. A malicious HTTP(S) server could redirect a vulnerable libcurl-using client to a crafted TFTP URL (if the client hasn't restricted which protocols it allows redirects to) and trick it to send private memory contents to a remote server over UDP. Limit curl's redirect protocols with --proto-redir and libcurl's with CURLOPT_REDIR_PROTOCOLS.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2017-1000100\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"7.35.0-1ubuntu2.11\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"libxml2\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.9.1+dfsg1-3ubuntu4.7\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2017-8872\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"The htmlParseTryOrFinish function in HTMLparser.c in libxml2 2.9.4 allows attackers to cause a denial of service (buffer over-read) or information disclosure.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2017-8872\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"curl\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"7.35.0-1ubuntu2.6\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-7141\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"curl and libcurl before 7.50.2, when built with NSS and the libnsspem.so library is available at runtime, allow remote attackers to hijack the authentication of a TLS connection by leveraging reuse of a previously loaded client certificate from file for a connection for which no certificate has been set, a different vulnerability than CVE-2016-5420.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-7141\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"7.35.0-1ubuntu2.10\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"libxml2\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.9.1+dfsg1-3ubuntu4.7\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2017-18258\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"The xz_head function in xzlib.c in libxml2 before 2.9.6 allows remote attackers to cause a denial of service (memory consumption) via a crafted LZMA file, because the decoder functionality does not restrict memory usage to what is required for a legitimate file.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2017-18258\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2.9.1+dfsg1-3ubuntu4.13\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"libxml2\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.9.1+dfsg1-3ubuntu4.7\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-4447\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"The xmlParseElementDecl function in parser.c in libxml2 before 2.9.4 allows context-dependent attackers to cause a denial of service (heap-based buffer underread and application crash) via a crafted file, involving xmlParseName.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-4447\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2.9.1+dfsg1-3ubuntu4.8\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"libxml2\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.9.1+dfsg1-3ubuntu4.7\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-2073\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"The htmlParseNameComplex function in HTMLparser.c in libxml2 allows attackers to cause a denial of service (out-of-bounds read) via a crafted XML document.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-2073\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2.9.1+dfsg1-3ubuntu4.8\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"curl\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"7.35.0-1ubuntu2.6\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2017-1000101\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"curl supports \\\"globbing\\\" of URLs, in which a user can pass a numerical range to have the tool iterate over those numbers to do a sequence of transfers. In the globbing function that parses the numerical range, there was an omission that made curl read a byte beyond the end of the URL if given a carefully crafted, or just wrongly written, URL. The URL is stored in a heap based buffer, so it could then be made to wrongly read something else instead of crashing. An example of a URL that triggers the flaw would be `http://ur%20[0-60000000000000000000`.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2017-1000101\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"7.35.0-1ubuntu2.11\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"krb5\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1.12+dfsg-2ubuntu5.2\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2018-5710\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"An issue was discovered in MIT Kerberos 5 (aka krb5) through 1.16. The pre-defined function \\\"strlen\\\" is getting a \\\"NULL\\\" string as a parameter value in plugins/kdb/ldap/libkdb_ldap/ldap_principal2.c in the Key Distribution Center (KDC), which allows remote authenticated users to cause a denial of service (NULL pointer dereference) via a modified kadmin client.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2018-5710\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"ntp\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1:4.2.6.p5+dfsg-3ubuntu2.14.04.6\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2017-6464\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"NTP before 4.2.8p10 and 4.3.x before 4.3.94 allows remote attackers to cause a denial of service (ntpd crash) via a malformed mode configuration directive.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2017-6464\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"1:4.2.6.p5+dfsg-3ubuntu2.14.04.11\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"krb5\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1.12+dfsg-2ubuntu5.2\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2018-5729\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"MIT krb5 1.6 or later allows an authenticated kadmin with permission to add principals to an LDAP Kerberos database to cause a denial of service (NULL pointer dereference) or bypass a DN container check by supplying tagged data that is internal to the database module.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2018-5729\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"1.12+dfsg-2ubuntu5.4\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"curl\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"7.35.0-1ubuntu2.6\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2020-8284\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"A malicious server can use the FTP PASV response to trick curl 7.73.0 and earlier into connecting back to a given IP address and port, and this way potentially make curl extract information about services that are otherwise private and not disclosed, for example doing port scanning and service banner extractions.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2020-8284\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"7.35.0-1ubuntu2.20+esm6\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"curl\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"7.35.0-1ubuntu2.6\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-8621\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"The `curl_getdate` function in curl before version 7.51.0 is vulnerable to an out of bounds read if it receives an input with one digit short.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-8621\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"7.35.0-1ubuntu2.10\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"krb5\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1.12+dfsg-2ubuntu5.2\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2017-11462\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Double free vulnerability in MIT Kerberos 5 (aka krb5) allows attackers to have unspecified impact via vectors involving automatic deletion of security contexts on error.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2017-11462\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"1.12+dfsg-2ubuntu5.4\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"openssh\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1:6.6p1-2ubuntu2.6\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-3115\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Multiple CRLF injection vulnerabilities in session.c in sshd in OpenSSH before 7.2p2 allow remote authenticated users to bypass intended shell-command restrictions via crafted X11 forwarding data, related to the (1) do_authenticated1 and (2) session_x11_req functions.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-3115\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"1:6.6p1-2ubuntu2.7\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"curl\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"7.35.0-1ubuntu2.6\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2020-8231\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Due to use of a dangling pointer, libcurl 7.29.0 through 7.71.1 can use the wrong connection when sending data.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2020-8231\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"7.35.0-1ubuntu2.20+esm5\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"ntp\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1:4.2.6.p5+dfsg-3ubuntu2.14.04.6\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-4956\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"ntpd in NTP 4.x before 4.2.8p8 allows remote attackers to cause a denial of service (interleaved-mode transition and time change) via a spoofed broadcast packet.  NOTE: this vulnerability exists because of an incomplete fix for CVE-2016-1548.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-4956\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"1:4.2.6.p5+dfsg-3ubuntu2.14.04.10\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"krb5\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1.12+dfsg-2ubuntu5.2\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2018-5730\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"MIT krb5 1.6 or later allows an authenticated kadmin with permission to add principals to an LDAP Kerberos database to circumvent a DN containership check by supplying both a \\\"linkdn\\\" and \\\"containerdn\\\" database argument, or by supplying a DN string which is a left extension of a container DN string but is not hierarchically within the container DN.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2018-5730\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"1.12+dfsg-2ubuntu5.4\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"sqlite3\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"3.8.2-1ubuntu2.1\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2017-2518\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"An issue was discovered in certain Apple products. iOS before 10.3.2 is affected. macOS before 10.12.5 is affected. tvOS before 10.2.1 is affected. watchOS before 3.2.2 is affected. The issue involves the \\\"SQLite\\\" component. It allows remote attackers to execute arbitrary code or cause a denial of service (buffer overflow and application crash) via a crafted SQL statement.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2017-2518\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"3.8.2-1ubuntu2.2+esm1\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"curl\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"7.35.0-1ubuntu2.6\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-9586\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"curl before version 7.52.0 is vulnerable to a buffer overflow when doing a large floating point output in libcurl's implementation of the printf() functions. If there are any application that accepts a format string from the outside without necessary input filtering, it could allow remote attacks.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-9586\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"7.35.0-1ubuntu2.11\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"ntp\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1:4.2.6.p5+dfsg-3ubuntu2.14.04.6\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-4954\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"The process_packet function in ntp_proto.c in ntpd in NTP 4.x before 4.2.8p8 allows remote attackers to cause a denial of service (peer-variable modification) by sending spoofed packets from many source IP addresses in a certain scenario, as demonstrated by triggering an incorrect leap indication.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-4954\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"1:4.2.6.p5+dfsg-3ubuntu2.14.04.10\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"sqlite3\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"3.8.2-1ubuntu2.1\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2020-9849\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"An information disclosure issue was addressed with improved state management. This issue is fixed in macOS Big Sur 11.0.1, watchOS 7.0, iOS 14.0 and iPadOS 14.0, iTunes for Windows 12.10.9, iCloud for Windows 11.5, tvOS 14.0. A remote attacker may be able to leak memory.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2020-9849\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"ntp\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1:4.2.6.p5+dfsg-3ubuntu2.14.04.6\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2015-7976\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"The ntpq saveconfig command in NTP 4.1.2, 4.2.x before 4.2.8p6, 4.3, 4.3.25, 4.3.70, and 4.3.77 does not properly filter special characters, which allows attackers to cause unspecified impact via a crafted filename.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2015-7976\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"1:4.2.6.p5+dfsg-3ubuntu2.14.04.10\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"pcre3\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1:8.31-2ubuntu2.1\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2015-8387\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"PCRE before 8.38 mishandles (?123) subroutine calls and related subroutine calls, which allows remote attackers to cause a denial of service (integer overflow) or possibly have unspecified other impact via a crafted regular expression, as demonstrated by a JavaScript RegExp object encountered by Konqueror.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2015-8387\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"1:8.31-2ubuntu2.2\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"pcre3\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1:8.31-2ubuntu2.1\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2015-8385\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"PCRE before 8.38 mishandles the /(?|(\\\\k'Pm')|(?'Pm'))/ pattern and related patterns with certain forward references, which allows remote attackers to cause a denial of service (buffer overflow) or possibly have unspecified other impact via a crafted regular expression, as demonstrated by a JavaScript RegExp object encountered by Konqueror.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2015-8385\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"1:8.31-2ubuntu2.2\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"pcre3\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1:8.31-2ubuntu2.1\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2015-8386\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"PCRE before 8.38 mishandles the interaction of lookbehind assertions and mutually recursive subpatterns, which allows remote attackers to cause a denial of service (buffer overflow) or possibly have unspecified other impact via a crafted regular expression, as demonstrated by a JavaScript RegExp object encountered by Konqueror.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2015-8386\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"1:8.31-2ubuntu2.2\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"pcre3\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1:8.31-2ubuntu2.1\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2015-8394\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"PCRE before 8.38 mishandles the (?(\\u003cdigits\\u003e) and (?(R\\u003cdigits\\u003e) conditions, which allows remote attackers to cause a denial of service (integer overflow) or possibly have unspecified other impact via a crafted regular expression, as demonstrated by a JavaScript RegExp object encountered by Konqueror.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2015-8394\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"1:8.31-2ubuntu2.2\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"pcre3\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1:8.31-2ubuntu2.1\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2015-8382\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"The match function in pcre_exec.c in PCRE before 8.37 mishandles the /(?:((abcd))|(((?:(?:(?:(?:abc|(?:abcdef))))b)abcdefghi)abc)|((*ACCEPT)))/ pattern and related patterns involving (*ACCEPT), which allows remote attackers to obtain sensitive information from process memory or cause a denial of service (partially initialized memory and application crash) via a crafted regular expression, as demonstrated by a JavaScript RegExp object encountered by Konqueror, aka ZDI-CAN-2547.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2015-8382\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"1:8.31-2ubuntu2.2\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"ntp\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1:4.2.6.p5+dfsg-3ubuntu2.14.04.6\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2018-7170\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"ntpd in ntp 4.2.x before 4.2.8p7 and 4.3.x before 4.3.92 allows authenticated users that know the private symmetric key to create arbitrarily-many ephemeral associations in order to win the clock selection of ntpd and modify a victim's clock via a Sybil attack. This issue exists because of an incomplete fix for CVE-2016-1549.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2018-7170\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"eglibc\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.19-0ubuntu6.6\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2017-15804\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"The glob function in glob.c in the GNU C Library (aka glibc or libc6) before 2.27 contains a buffer overflow during unescaping of user names with the ~ operator.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubun