"The file_check_mem function in funcs.c in file before 5.23, as used in the Fileinfo component in PHP before 5.5.34, 5.6.x before 5.6.20, and 7.x before 7.0.5, mishandles continuation-level jumps, which allows context-dependent attackers to cause a denial of service (buffer overflow and application crash) or possibly execute arbitrary code via a crafted magic file.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2015-8865\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"1:5.14-2ubuntu3.4\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"file\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1:5.14-2ubuntu3.3\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2018-10360\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"The do_core_note function in readelf.c in libmagic.a in file 5.33 allows remote attackers to cause a denial of service (out-of-bounds read and application crash) via a crafted ELF file.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2018-10360\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"1:5.14-2ubuntu3.4\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"mysql-5.5\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"5.5.47-0ubuntu0.14.04.1\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2017-3302\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Crash in libmysqlclient.so in Oracle MySQL before 5.6.21 and 5.7.x before 5.7.5 and MariaDB through 5.5.54, 10.0.x through 10.0.29, 10.1.x through 10.1.21, and 10.2.x through 10.2.3.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2017-3302\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"5.5.55-0ubuntu0.14.04.1\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"eglibc\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.19-0ubuntu6.6\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-3706\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Stack-based buffer overflow in the getaddrinfo function in sysdeps/posix/getaddrinfo.c in the GNU C Library (aka glibc or libc6) allows remote attackers to cause a denial of service (crash) via vectors involving hostent conversion. NOTE: this vulnerability exists because of an incomplete fix for CVE-2013-4458.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-3706\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2.19-0ubuntu6.10\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"perl\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"5.18.2-2ubuntu1\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2017-6512\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Race condition in the rmtree and remove_tree functions in the File-Path module before 2.13 for Perl allows attackers to set the mode on arbitrary files via vectors involving directory-permission loosening logic.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2017-6512\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"5.18.2-2ubuntu1.4\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"cron\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"3.0pl1-124ubuntu2\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2017-9525\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"In the cron package through 3.0pl1-128 on Debian, and through 3.0pl1-128ubuntu2 on Ubuntu, the postinst maintainer script allows for group-crontab-to-root privilege escalation via symlink attacks against unsafe usage of the chown and chmod programs.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2017-9525\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"perl\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"5.18.2-2ubuntu1\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2020-12723\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"regcomp.c in Perl before 5.30.3 allows a buffer overflow via a crafted regular expression because of recursive S_study_chunk calls.  An application written in Perl would only be vulnerable to this flaw if it evaluates regular expressions supplied by the attacker. Evaluating regular expressions in this fashion is known to be dangerous since the regular expression engine does not protect against denial of service attacks in this usage scenario.]\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2020-12723\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"5.18.2-2ubuntu1.7+esm3\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"perl\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"5.18.2-2ubuntu1\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-6185\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"The XSLoader::load method in XSLoader in Perl does not properly locate .so files when called in a string eval, which might allow local users to execute arbitrary code via a Trojan horse library under the current working directory.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-6185\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"5.18.2-2ubuntu1.4\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"perl\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"5.18.2-2ubuntu1\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2014-4330\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"The Dumper method in Data::Dumper before 2.154, as used in Perl 5.20.1 and earlier, allows context-dependent attackers to cause a denial of service (stack consumption and crash) via an Array-Reference with many nested Array-References, which triggers a large number of recursive calls to the DD_dump function.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2014-4330\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"5.18.2-2ubuntu1.1\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"perl\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"5.18.2-2ubuntu1\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2015-8853\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"The (1) S_reghop3, (2) S_reghop4, and (3) S_reghopmaybe3 functions in regexec.c in Perl before 5.24.0 allow context-dependent attackers to cause a denial of service (infinite loop) via crafted utf-8 data, as demonstrated by \\\"a\\\\x80.\\\"\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2015-8853\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"5.18.2-2ubuntu1.4\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"perl\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"5.18.2-2ubuntu1\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2020-10543\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Perl before 5.30.3 on 32-bit platforms allows a heap-based buffer overflow because nested regular expression quantifiers have an integer overflow.  An application written in Perl would only be vulnerable to this flaw if it evaluates regular expressions supplied by the attacker. Evaluating regular expressions in this fashion is known to be dangerous since the regular expression engine does not protect against denial of service attacks in this usage scenario.  Additionally, the target system needs a sufficient amount of memory to allocate partial expansions of the nested quantifiers prior to the overflow occurring. This requirement is unlikely to be met on 64bit systems.]\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2020-10543\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"5.18.2-2ubuntu1.7+esm3\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"perl\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"5.18.2-2ubuntu1\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2020-10878\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Perl before 5.30.3 has an integer overflow related to mishandling of a \\\"PL_regkind[OP(n)] == NOTHING\\\" situation. A crafted regular expression could lead to malformed bytecode with a possibility of instruction injection.  An application written in Perl would only be vulnerable to this flaw if it evaluates regular expressions supplied by the attacker. Evaluating regular expressions in this fashion is known to be dangerous since the regular expression engine does not protect against denial of service attacks in this usage scenario.]\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2020-10878\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"5.18.2-2ubuntu1.7+esm3\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"perl\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"5.18.2-2ubuntu1\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2013-7422\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Integer underflow in regcomp.c in Perl before 5.20, as used in Apple OS X before 10.10.5 and other products, allows context-dependent attackers to execute arbitrary code or cause a denial of service (application crash) via a long digit string associated with an invalid backreference within a regular expression.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2013-7422\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"5.18.2-2ubuntu1.1\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"rsync\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"3.1.0-2ubuntu0.2\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2017-16548\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"The receive_xattr function in xattrs.c in rsync 3.1.2 and 3.1.3-development does not check for a trailing '\\\\0' character in an xattr name, which allows remote attackers to cause a denial of service (heap-based buffer over-read and application crash) or possibly have unspecified other impact by sending crafted data to the daemon.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2017-16548\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"3.1.0-2ubuntu0.4\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"shadow\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1:4.1.5.1-1ubuntu9.1\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2013-4235\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"shadow: TOCTOU (time-of-check time-of-use) race condition when copying and removing directory trees\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2013-4235\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"shadow\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1:4.1.5.1-1ubuntu9.1\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2017-12424\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"In shadow before 4.5, the newusers tool could be made to manipulate internal data structures in ways unintended by the authors. Malformed input may lead to crashes (with a buffer overflow or other memory corruption) or other unspecified behaviors. This crosses a privilege boundary in, for example, certain web-hosting environments in which a Control Panel allows an unprivileged user account to create subaccounts.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2017-12424\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"shadow\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1:4.1.5.1-1ubuntu9.1\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2018-7169\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"An issue was discovered in shadow 4.5. newgidmap (in shadow-utils) is setuid and allows an unprivileged user to be placed in a user namespace where setgroups(2) is permitted. This allows an attacker to remove themselves from a supplementary group, which may allow access to certain filesystem paths if the administrator has used \\\"group blacklisting\\\" (e.g., chmod g-rwx) to restrict access to paths. This flaw effectively reverts a security feature in the kernel (in particular, the /proc/self/setgroups knob) to prevent this sort of privilege escalation.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2018-7169\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"libjpeg-turbo\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1.3.0-0ubuntu2\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2018-11212\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"An issue was discovered in libjpeg 9a and 9d. The alloc_sarray function in jmemmgr.c allows remote attackers to cause a denial of service (divide-by-zero error) via a crafted file.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2018-11212\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"1.3.0-0ubuntu2.1\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"libjpeg-turbo\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1.3.0-0ubuntu2\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2018-11813\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"libjpeg 9c has a large loop because read_pixel in rdtarga.c mishandles EOF.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2018-11813\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"libjpeg-turbo\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1.3.0-0ubuntu2\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2018-11213\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"An issue was discovered in libjpeg 9a. The get_text_gray_row function in rdppm.c allows remote attackers to cause a denial of service (Segmentation fault) via a crafted file.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2018-11213\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"1.3.0-0ubuntu2.1\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"libjpeg-turbo\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1.3.0-0ubuntu2\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2014-9092\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"libjpeg-turbo before 1.3.1 allows remote attackers to cause a denial of service (crash) via a crafted JPEG file, related to the Exif marker.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2014-9092\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"1.3.0-0ubuntu2.1\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"libjpeg-turbo\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1.3.0-0ubuntu2\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-3616\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"The cjpeg utility in libjpeg allows remote attackers to cause a denial of service (NULL pointer dereference and application crash) or execute arbitrary code via a crafted file.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-3616\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"1.3.0-0ubuntu2.1\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"libjpeg-turbo\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1.3.0-0ubuntu2\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2018-14498\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"get_8bit_row in rdbmp.c in libjpeg-turbo through 1.5.90 and MozJPEG through 3.3.1 allows attackers to cause a denial of service (heap-based buffer over-read and application crash) via a crafted 8-bit BMP in which one or more of the color indices is out of range for the number of palette entries.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2018-14498\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"libjpeg-turbo\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1.3.0-0ubuntu2\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2018-1152\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"libjpeg-turbo 1.5.90 is vulnerable to a denial of service vulnerability caused by a divide by zero when processing a crafted BMP image.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2018-1152\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"1.3.0-0ubuntu2.1\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"libjpeg-turbo\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1.3.0-0ubuntu2\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2020-14152\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"In IJG JPEG (aka libjpeg) before 9d, jpeg_mem_available() in jmemnobs.c in djpeg does not honor the max_memory_to_use setting, possibly causing excessive memory consumption.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2020-14152\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"libjpeg-turbo\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1.3.0-0ubuntu2\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2018-11214\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"An issue was discovered in libjpeg 9a. The get_text_rgb_row function in rdppm.c allows remote attackers to cause a denial of service (Segmentation fault) via a crafted file.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2018-11214\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"1.3.0-0ubuntu2.1\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"apache2\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.4.7-1ubuntu4.9\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2017-15710\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"In Apache httpd 2.0.23 to 2.0.65, 2.2.0 to 2.2.34, and 2.4.0 to 2.4.29, mod_authnz_ldap, if configured with AuthLDAPCharsetConfig, uses the Accept-Language header value to lookup the right charset encoding when verifying the user's credentials. If the header value is not present in the charset conversion table, a fallback mechanism is used to truncate it to a two characters value to allow a quick retry (for example, 'en-US' is truncated to 'en'). A header value of less than two characters forces an out of bound write of one NUL byte to a memory location that is not part of the string. In the worst case, quite unlikely, the process would crash which could be used as a Denial of Service attack. In the more likely case, this memory is already reserved for future use and the issue has no effect at all.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2017-15710\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2.4.7-1ubuntu4.20\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"apache2\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.4.7-1ubuntu4.9\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2020-11985\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"IP address spoofing when proxying using mod_remoteip and mod_rewrite For configurations using proxying with mod_remoteip and certain mod_rewrite rules, an attacker could spoof their IP address for logging and PHP scripts. Note this issue was fixed in Apache HTTP Server 2.4.24 but was retrospectively allocated a low severity CVE in 2020.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2020-11985\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"eglibc\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.19-0ubuntu6.6\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-4429\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Stack-based buffer overflow in the clntudp_call function in sunrpc/clnt_udp.c in the GNU C Library (aka glibc or libc6) allows remote servers to cause a denial of service (crash) or possibly unspecified other impact via a flood of crafted ICMP and UDP packets.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-4429\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2.19-0ubuntu6.10\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"apache2\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.4.7-1ubuntu4.9\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2017-7679\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"In Apache httpd 2.2.x before 2.2.33 and 2.4.x before 2.4.26, mod_mime can read one byte past the end of a buffer when sending a malicious Content-Type response header.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2017-7679\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2.4.7-1ubuntu4.16\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"apache2\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.4.7-1ubuntu4.9\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2018-1283\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"In Apache httpd 2.4.0 to 2.4.29, when mod_session is configured to forward its session data to CGI applications (SessionEnv on, not the default), a remote user may influence their content by using a \\\"Session\\\" header. This comes from the \\\"HTTP_SESSION\\\" variable name used by mod_session to forward its data to CGIs, since the prefix \\\"HTTP_\\\" is also used by the Apache HTTP Server to pass HTTP header fields, per CGI specifications.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2018-1283\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2.4.7-1ubuntu4.20\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"apache2\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.4.7-1ubuntu4.9\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2018-17199\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"In Apache HTTP Server 2.4 release 2.4.37 and prior, mod_session checks the session expiry time before decoding the session. This causes session expiry time to be ignored for mod_session_cookie sessions since the expiry time is loaded when the session is decoded.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2018-17199\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2.4.7-1ubuntu4.22\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"apache2\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.4.7-1ubuntu4.9\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-4975\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Possible CRLF injection allowing HTTP response splitting attacks for sites which use mod_userdir. This issue was mitigated by changes made in 2.4.25 and 2.2.32 which prohibit CR or LF injection into the \\\"Location\\\" or other outbound header key or value. Fixed in Apache HTTP Server 2.4.25 (Affected 2.4.1-2.4.23). Fixed in Apache HTTP Server 2.2.32 (Affected 2.2.0-2.2.31).\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-4975\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2.4.7-1ubuntu4.14\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"apache2\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.4.7-1ubuntu4.9\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2020-1927\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"In Apache HTTP Server 2.4.0 to 2.4.41, redirects configured with mod_rewrite that were intended to be self-referential might be fooled by encoded newlines and redirect instead to an an unexpected URL within the request URL.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2020-1927\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"apache2\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.4.7-1ubuntu4.9\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2018-1301\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"A specially crafted request could have crashed the Apache HTTP Server prior to version 2.4.30, due to an out of bound access after a size limit is reached by reading the HTTP header. This vulnerability is considered very hard if not impossible to trigger in non-debug mode (both log and build level), so it is classified as low risk for common server usage.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2018-1301\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2.4.7-1ubuntu4.20\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"apache2\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.4.7-1ubuntu4.9\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2020-1934\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"In Apache HTTP Server 2.4.0 to 2.4.41, mod_proxy_ftp may use uninitialized memory when proxying to a malicious FTP server.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2020-1934\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"apache2\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.4.7-1ubuntu4.9\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2017-15715\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"In Apache httpd 2.4.0 to 2.4.29, the expression specified in \\u003cFilesMatch\\u003e could match '$' to a newline character in a malicious filename, rather than matching only the end of the filename. This could be exploited in environments where uploads of some files are are externally blocked, but only by matching the trailing portion of the filename.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2017-15715\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2.4.7-1ubuntu4.20\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"apache2\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.4.7-1ubuntu4.9\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2018-1312\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"In Apache httpd 2.2.0 to 2.4.29, when generating an HTTP Digest authentication challenge, the nonce sent to prevent reply attacks was not correctly generated using a pseudo-random seed. In a cluster of servers using a common Digest authentication configuration, HTTP requests could be replayed across servers by an attacker without detection.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2018-1312\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2.4.7-1ubuntu4.20\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"apache2\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.4.7-1ubuntu4.9\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-2161\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"In Apache HTTP Server versions 2.4.0 to 2.4.23, malicious input to mod_auth_digest can cause the server to crash, and each instance continues to crash even for subsequently valid requests.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-2161\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2.4.7-1ubuntu4.14\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"apache2\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.4.7-1ubuntu4.9\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2018-1303\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"A specially crafted HTTP request header could have crashed the Apache HTTP Server prior to version 2.4.30 due to an out of bound read while preparing data to be cached in shared memory. It could be used as a Denial of Service attack against users of mod_cache_socache. The vulnerability is considered as low risk since mod_cache_socache is not widely used, mod_cache_disk is not concerned by this vulnerability.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2018-1303\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2.4.7-1ubuntu4.20\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"libidn\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1.28-1ubuntu2\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2015-8948\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"idn in GNU libidn before 1.33 might allow remote attackers to obtain sensitive memory information by reading a zero byte as input, which triggers an out-of-bounds read.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2015-8948\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"1.28-1ubuntu2.1\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"libidn\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"1.28-1ubuntu2\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2015-2059\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"The stringprep_utf8_to_ucs4 function in libin before 1.31, as used in jabberd2, allows context-dependent attackers to read system memory and possibly have other unspecified impact via invalid UTF-8 characters in a string, which triggers an out-of-bounds read.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2015-2059\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"1.28-1ubuntu2.1\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"gnutls26\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.12.23-12ubuntu2.4\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-8610\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"A denial of service flaw was found in OpenSSL 0.9.8, 1.0.1, 1.0.2 through 1.0.2h, and 1.1.0 in the way the TLS/SSL protocol defined processing of ALERT packets during a connection handshake. A remote attacker could use this flaw to make a TLS/SSL server consume an excessive amount of CPU and fail to accept connections from other clients.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-8610\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2.12.23-12ubuntu2.6\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"gnutls26\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.12.23-12ubuntu2.4\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2017-7869\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"GnuTLS before 2017-02-20 has an out-of-bounds write caused by an integer overflow and heap-based buffer overflow related to the cdk_pkt_read function in opencdk/read-packet.c. This issue (which is a subset of the vendor's GNUTLS-SA-2017-3 report) is fixed in 3.5.10.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2017-7869\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2.12.23-12ubuntu2.8\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"eglibc\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.19-0ubuntu6.6\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2015-1781\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Buffer overflow in the gethostbyname_r and other unspecified NSS functions in the GNU C Library (aka glibc or libc6) before 2.22 allows context-dependent attackers to cause a denial of service (crash) or execute arbitrary code via a crafted DNS response, which triggers a call with a misaligned buffer.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2015-1781\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2.19-0ubuntu6.8\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"python2.7\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.7.6-8ubuntu0.2\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2018-1060\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"python before versions 2.7.15, 3.4.9, 3.5.6rc1, 3.6.5rc1 and 3.7.0 is vulnerable to catastrophic backtracking in pop3lib's apop() method. An attacker could use this flaw to cause denial of service.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2018-1060\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2.7.6-8ubuntu0.5\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"python2.7\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.7.6-8ubuntu0.2\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2018-1000030\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Python 2.7.14 is vulnerable to a Heap-Buffer-Overflow as well as a Heap-Use-After-Free. Python versions prior to 2.7.14 may also be vulnerable and it appears that Python 2.7.17 and prior may also be vulnerable however this has not been confirmed. The vulnerability lies when multiply threads are handling large amounts of data. In both cases there is essentially a race condition that occurs. For the Heap-Buffer-Overflow, Thread 2 is creating the size for a buffer, but Thread1 is already writing to the buffer without knowing how much to write. So when a large amount of data is being processed, it is very easy to cause memory corruption using a Heap-Buffer-Overflow. As for the Use-After-Free, Thread3-\\u003eMalloc-\\u003eThread1-\\u003eFree's-\\u003eThread2-Re-uses-Free'd Memory. The PSRT has stated that this is not a security vulnerability due to the fact that the attacker must be able to run code, however in some situations, such as function as a service, this vulnerability can potentially be used by an attacker to violate a trust boundary, as such the DWF feels this issue deserves a CVE.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2018-1000030\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2.7.6-8ubuntu0.5\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"python2.7\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.7.6-8ubuntu0.2\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2020-8492\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Python 2.7 through 2.7.17, 3.5 through 3.5.9, 3.6 through 3.6.10, 3.7 through 3.7.6, and 3.8 through 3.8.1 allows an HTTP server to conduct Regular Expression Denial of Service (ReDoS) attacks against a client because of urllib.request.AbstractBasicAuthHandler catastrophic backtracking.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2020-8492\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2.7.6-8ubuntu0.6+esm5\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"libbsd\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"0.6.0-2ubuntu1\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2016-2090\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Off-by-one vulnerability in the fgetwln function in libbsd before 0.8.2 allows attackers to have unspecified impact via unknown vectors, which trigger a heap-based buffer overflow.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2016-2090\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"0.6.0-2ubuntu1+esm1\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"python2.7\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.7.6-8ubuntu0.2\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2019-16935\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"The documentation XML-RPC server in Python through 2.7.16, 3.x through 3.6.9, and 3.7.x through 3.7.4 has XSS via the server_title field. This occurs in Lib/DocXMLRPCServer.py in Python 2.x, and in Lib/xmlrpc/server.py in Python 3.x. If set_server_title is called with untrusted input, arbitrary JavaScript can be delivered to clients that visit the http URL for this server.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2019-16935\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2.7.6-8ubuntu0.6+esm3\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"python2.7\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.7.6-8ubuntu0.2\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2020-14422\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"Lib/ipaddress.py in Python through 3.8.3 improperly computes hash values in the IPv4Interface and IPv6Interface classes, which might allow a remote attacker to cause a denial of service if an application is affected by the performance of a dictionary containing IPv4Interface or IPv6Interface objects, and this attacker can cause many dictionary entries to be created. This is fixed in: v3.5.10, v3.5.10rc1; v3.6.12; v3.7.9; v3.8.4, v3.8.4rc1, v3.8.5, v3.8.6, v3.8.6rc1; v3.9.0, v3.9.0b4, v3.9.0b5, v3.9.0rc1, v3.9.0rc2.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2020-14422\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2.7.6-8ubuntu0.6+esm6\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"python2.7\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.7.6-8ubuntu0.2\",\n            \"vulnerability\": \"CVE-2018-1061\",\n            \"namespace\": \"ubuntu:14.04\",\n            \"description\": \"python before versions 2.7.15, 3.4.9, 3.5.6rc1, 3.6.5rc1 and 3.7.0 is vulnerable to catastrophic backtracking in the difflib.IS_LINE_JUNK method. An attacker could use this flaw to cause denial of service.\",\n            \"link\": \"http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2018-1061\",\n            \"severity\": \"Low\",\n            \"fixedby\": \"2.7.6-8ubuntu0.5\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"featurename\": \"python2.7\",\n            \"featureversion\": \"2.7.6-8ubuntu0.2\",\n         